<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper"> </div>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1: CAMPSITE RESERVATION</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Nature Park Services, how may I help you today?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Hello, I’m calling to make a campsite reservation.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Great, let me just pull up the reservation form and we can get started.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">Okay, first, could I get your name?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Sure, it’s Sandra Camp.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> All right, Miss Camp. I can make reservations for the Northern, Central, and Southern California parks.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">Which region will you be traveling to?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Is Mount Laguna in the central or southern region?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Is that where you’re going? Yes, that’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">(Q1) Southern</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">Do you know which campground?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Actually, I was hoping you could help me with that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">I’ve read a lot about two different campgrounds: Sunrise and Mountain, but I can’t decide.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Mountain Campground has many hiking trails close by, but then again, Sunrise Campground is next to the lake and my husband loves to fish.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Hmm, they’re both really beautiful spots.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">I guess it depends on when you’re going, really.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Well, we’re going in April.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> The thing is, fishing at Sunrise Campground is only allowed from June to September, so I suggest <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">(Q2) Mountain</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Okay, then that makes it easy. So we’ve selected the campground.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\">So now we need to think about which sort of site.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\">There are different options: you can stay at a cabin, a tent, or a recreational vehicle campsite.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Which type of site offers the most peace and quiet?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> A <strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">(Q3) tent</strong> site would be your best bet.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> That sounds good to me.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\">Um, so if you’ve read about the park, you probably know that some vehicles aren’t suitable for the park roads.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\">Cars tend to get stuck when it rains.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\">If you have a <strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"14\">(Q4) truck</strong>, you won’t have any trouble.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Luckily, we do, and we’ll be driving that instead of our car.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\">I hope we don’t get any rain, but I’d rather be safe than sorry.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Perfect. I’ll just need to get your license plate number.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> That’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"17\">(Q5) QY0918</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Thanks. And what about your trip dates?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> We’d like to stay for three days.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Does that mean you’ll be staying two nights?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> That’s right. We’ll be arriving on April 10th and leaving on the <strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">(Q6) twelfth</strong> (April 12th).</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"37\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SPECIAL REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"39\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"39\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Now, the park is home to some black bears, so you’ll need to rent a bear-proof food container to lock your food inside for hikes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"40\">It’s really just a precaution. We have small, medium, and large food containers for campers.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"41\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"41\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Oh, I’m familiar with food containers, but they can be heavy.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"42\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"42\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Well, the large one is, but if you get the <strong data-path-to-node=\"42\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">(Q7) small</strong> size, it’s not so heavy.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"43\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"43\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Oh, let’s do that. I really want something lightweight.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"44\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"44\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Would you be interested in signing up for a guided nature walk on the second day of your trip?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"45\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"45\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> A what kind of walk?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"46\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"46\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Well, at 7:00 AM, there are three different ones near your campground:</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"47\">There’s the flower walk, the bird watching walk, and the waterfall walk.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"48\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"48\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Really? I love gardening, so the <strong data-path-to-node=\"48\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">(Q8) flower</strong> walk sounds interesting.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"49\">My son might be more into the waterfall one, but I can’t imagine him getting up in time.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"50\">Maybe I could go alone. Could you sign me up?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"51\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"51\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Sure. Now, just a few more things.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"52\">Visitors must purchase park passes as well.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"53\">You have the option of the one-day pass, which would be cheaper, or the <strong data-path-to-node=\"53\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">(Q9) one-year</strong> pass, which is a better deal if you plan to go to more parks.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"54\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"54\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Let’s go ahead and get that. I’m sure we’ll visit more parks soon. It’s a really good bargain.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"55\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"55\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Plus, we donate $5 of the pass fee to one of our three park programs.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"56\">You get to choose which one.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"57\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"57\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Park programs?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"58\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"58\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Yes, well, we run a <strong data-path-to-node=\"58\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">(Q10) youth</strong> program for local kids to attend a nature camp in the summer.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"59\">The other two options are conservation projects: there’s a wildlife program and a tree planting program.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"60\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"60\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Wow, they all sound worthwhile. What should I do?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"61\">Um, it’s important for children to appreciate the outdoors.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"62\">Let’s go with the youth program.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"63\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"63\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Okay, we just need to review the fee and payment information.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a3f76e80-3cb2-4272-bdb2-c1ded3abc02f', '993f24cf-058f-41b3-ba6e-d8e7174171d3', 'radio', 'Questions 1–7', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Jason Neff discovered there had been a dramatic rise in dust levels in the second half of the nineteenth century."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Anasazi civilization disappeared due to the impact of dust in the atmosphere."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Before cattle were introduced to the American Southwest, large numbers of bison occupied the area."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The bison population in the Great Plains diminished because European settlers found it easy to hunt them."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The development of railroads across the US was more expensive than originally expected."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Aztec Land and Cattle Company worked hard to take care of the grazing land it owned."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Most of the land once owned by the Aztec Land and Cattle Company remains infertile today."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3>1. Jason Neff discovered there had been a dramatic rise in dust levels in the second half of the nineteenth century.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “…but then, ‘from about <strong>1860 to 1900, dust deposition rates shot up</strong>.’”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Giai đoạn 1860 đến 1900 là nửa cuối thế kỷ 19, và việc “dust deposition rates shot up” (tốc độ lắng đọng bụi tăng vọt) chứng tỏ có sự gia tăng đáng kể.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>2. The Anasazi civilization disappeared due to the impact of dust in the atmosphere.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “There was a near-permanent drought between 900 and 1300 which was so intense that <strong>it destroyed a series of native American civilizations</strong>, including the Anasazi… Yet the evidence from the San Juan lakes is that <strong>it was not dusty</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản nói nền văn minh Anasazi bị hủy hoại bởi <strong>hạn hán</strong> nghiêm trọng (<strong>drought</strong>), và bằng chứng cho thấy trong thời kỳ đó <strong>không hề có bụi</strong> nhiều. Điều này mâu thuẫn với câu hỏi.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>3. Before cattle were introduced to the American Southwest, large numbers of bison occupied the area.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “‘Unlike most other parts of the US, there were <strong>few grazers</strong> in the American Southwest until the Europeans came. <strong>No bison</strong> and few antelope or deer.’”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản nói rõ rằng trước khi người châu Âu đến, có <strong>rất ít</strong> động vật ăn cỏ và <strong>không có bò rừng (bison)</strong> ở American Southwest.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>4. The bison population in the Great Plains diminished because European settlers found it easy to hunt them.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “In the Great Plains to the east and north, <strong>bison roamed in vast herds</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản chỉ nhắc đến việc bison sống thành đàn lớn ở Great Plains, nhưng <strong>không cung cấp thông tin</strong> về lý do tại sao quần thể bison giảm sút (có thể là do săn bắn, nhưng văn bản không xác nhận).</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>5. The development of railroads across the US was more expensive than originally expected.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “The invasion was sudden, funded by a bubble of speculative investment… The money went into <strong>railroads</strong>, and herds of cattle and sheep that rode the rails…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản chỉ nói rằng tiền đầu tư được đổ vào đường sắt, nhưng <strong>không có thông tin</strong> về chi phí thực tế có vượt quá dự kiến ban đầu hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>6. The Aztec Land and Cattle Company worked hard to take care of the grazing land it owned.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “…it was only interested in <strong>quick profits</strong> and had <strong>little incentive to protect the soils from overgrazing</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Công ty Aztec chỉ quan tâm đến lợi nhuận nhanh chóng và <strong>ít động lực bảo vệ</strong> đất khỏi chăn thả quá mức, trái ngược với việc “worked hard to take care” (làm việc chăm chỉ để chăm sóc).</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>7. Most of the land once owned by the Aztec Land and Cattle Company remains infertile today.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “Such was the damage to the grasslands that <strong>even now few of the pastures have recovered</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “few of the pastures have recovered” (rất ít đồng cỏ đã phục hồi) cho thấy phần lớn diện tích vẫn chưa hồi phục và vẫn còn cằn cỗi (infertile).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('47198202-dfa6-4ec8-abbe-e2aa41fdb402', '14ac38b1-f8a1-4fe4-88c1-16752a62ad19', 'radio', 'Questions 1–4', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information. <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information. <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Scientists studied hunter-gatherer societies because their sleep patterns are assumed to be similar to those of humans more than 10,000 years ago."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The medical devices used in the research were specially designed for humid conditions."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Researchers found that tribespeople stayed longer in bed than inhabitants of industrialized regions."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Jerome Siegel believes that environment and culture have little effect on sleep patterns."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Scientists studied hunter-gatherer societies because their sleep patterns are assumed to be similar to those of humans more than 10,000 years ago.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 2, dòng 3-4: “…these pre-industrial societies are <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">thought to sleep the way humans did more than 10,000 years ago</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “thought to sleep” (được cho là ngủ theo cách…) đồng nghĩa với từ “assumed to be similar” (được giả định là tương tự) trong câu hỏi. Các nhà khoa học chọn họ vì họ là đại diện cho lối sống tiền công nghiệp.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. The medical devices used in the research were specially designed for humid conditions.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 2, dòng 5: “Traveling to where they live, often in <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">humid, remote locations</strong>, researchers used medical devices…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có đề cập rằng các nhà nghiên cứu đến những nơi có điều kiện <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">ẩm ướt (humid)</strong>, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"103\">không có thông tin</strong> nào nói rằng các thiết bị y tế đó được “thiết kế đặc biệt” (specially designed) cho điều kiện ẩm ướt này.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Researchers found that tribespeople stayed longer in bed than inhabitants of industrialized regions. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">\"Like many of us, the Hadza, San, and Tsimane spend more time in bed – from 6.9 to 8.5 hours – than they do actually sleeping. <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"149\">This adds up to a sleep efficiency that is very similar to today’s industrial populations.</strong>\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu hỏi:</strong> Khẳng định người bộ lạc nằm trên giường <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">lâu hơn</strong> cư dân vùng công nghiệp (<em data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">stayed longer in bed than...</em>).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Bài đọc:</strong> Khẳng định chỉ số này của người bộ lạc <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">rất giống / tương đồng</strong> với người hiện đại ngày nay (<em data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">very similar to today’s industrial populations</em>).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Kết luận:</strong> Bài đọc nói <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">ngang nhau</strong> nhưng câu hỏi lại cố tình so sánh <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">hơn</strong>. Do thông tin mâu thuẫn hoàn toàn nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"119\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Jerome Siegel believes that environment and culture have little effect on sleep patterns.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 4, dòng 1-3: “According to Jerome Siegel… evidence suggests sleep habits <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">may not be environmental or cultural</strong>, but central to the <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"148\">physical makeup of humans</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Siegel tin rằng thói quen ngủ có thể không phải do tác động từ môi trường hay văn hóa mà do cấu trúc sinh học của con người. “Little effect” (ít ảnh hưởng) phản ánh đúng ý “may not be” (có thể không phải do…) trong bài.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d77d5668-46aa-48dd-a25c-1dbb3dc4a67a', '14ac38b1-f8a1-4fe4-88c1-16752a62ad19', 'fillup', 'Questions 5–13', '<p data-start="87" data-end="114">Complete the notes below.</p>
<p data-start="116" data-end="172">Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="237" data-end="271"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>New Evidence on Sleep Patterns</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="273" data-end="300"><strong data-start="273" data-end="300">New ideas about napping</strong></p>
<ul data-start="301" data-end="523">
<li data-start="301" data-end="359">
<p data-start="303" data-end="359">scientists have recorded an afternoon drop in {energy}</p>
</li>
<li data-start="360" data-end="471">
<p data-start="362" data-end="471">studies of hunter-gatherer societies show that napping was rare and occurred more often during the {summer}</p>
</li>
<li data-start="472" data-end="523">
<p data-start="474" data-end="523">the devices may not have detected {short} naps</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="525" data-end="550"><strong data-start="525" data-end="550">Daily activity cycles</strong></p>
<ul data-start="551" data-end="799">
<li data-start="551" data-end="612">
<p data-start="553" data-end="612">the tribespeople went to sleep several hours after sunset</p>
</li>
<li data-start="613" data-end="658">
<p data-start="615" data-end="658">even with {fires} there was little light</p>
</li>
<li data-start="659" data-end="707">
<p data-start="661" data-end="707">tribespeople usually woke up around {sunrise}</p>
</li>
<li data-start="708" data-end="799">
<p data-start="710" data-end="799">scientists found that {temperature} had almost as much influence on sleep patterns as light</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="801" data-end="874"><strong data-start="801" data-end="874">Differences between tribespeople and people in industrialised regions</strong></p>
<ul data-start="875" data-end="1157" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">
<li data-start="875" data-end="949">
<p data-start="877" data-end="949">{sleeplessness} is something that very few of the tribespeople suffered from</p>
</li>
<li data-start="950" data-end="1023">
<p data-start="952" data-end="1023">the environment of tribespeople may have been more suitable for sleep</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1024" data-end="1114">
<p data-start="1026" data-end="1114">tribespeople had better fitness than industrialised populations and were not {overweight}</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1115" data-end="1157" data-is-last-node="">
<p data-start="1117" data-end="1157" data-is-last-node="">tribespeople also had stronger {hearts}</p>
</li>
</ul>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. energy</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 4,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 6-7:</span><span class=\"\"> “Scientists have documented that people’s </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">energy</strong><span class=\"\"> often falls in the mid-afternoon.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Các nhà khoa học ghi nhận sự sụt giảm </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">năng lượng</strong><span class=\"\"> vào buổi chiều.</span><span class=\"\"> Đây là lý do nhiều người thường cảm thấy buồn ngủ vào giờ này.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. summer</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 5,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 3:</span><span class=\"\"> “…</span><span class=\"\">naps may have occurred on up to 7 percent of winter days and 22 percent of </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">summer</strong><span class=\"\"> days.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Việc ngủ trưa rất hiếm ở các bộ lạc này,</span><span class=\"\"> nhưng nếu có,</span><span class=\"\"> nó xảy ra vào mùa hè (22%) nhiều hơn mùa đông (7%).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. short</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 5,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 4-5:</span><span class=\"\"> “…</span><span class=\"\">it is possible that some of the study subjects took naps that were </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">short</strong><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> perhaps 15 minutes or less.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Thiết bị đo có thể đã bỏ lỡ những giấc ngủ </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">ngắn</strong><span class=\"\"> (dưới 15 phút) vì chúng chỉ nhạy với các giấc ngủ dài hơn.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. fires</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 6,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 3 (bản chuẩn):</span><span class=\"\"> “All three tribes had </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">fires</strong><span class=\"\"> going,</span><span class=\"\"> but the light itself was much lower than you might get from a light bulb.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"animating\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Dù họ có đốt <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">lửa</strong>, nhưng ánh sáng từ lửa vẫn yếu hơn nhiều so với bóng đèn hiện đại, nên không làm gián đoạn nhịp sinh học quá nhiều.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. sunrise</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 6, dòng cuối: “They did, however, have a tendency to wake up anywhere between an hour before and an hour after <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">sunrise</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Họ thường thức dậy xung quanh thời điểm <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">mặt trời mọc</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. temperature</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 7, dòng 1-3: “…significance of <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">temperature</strong>. They found that it also played a big role, though it was somewhat less important than light in influencing sleep patterns.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nghiên cứu chỉ ra rằng <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">nhiệt độ</strong> có ảnh hưởng đến giấc ngủ gần như ngang bằng với ánh sáng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. sleeplessness</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 8, dòng 2: “Importantly, almost none of them were troubled by <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">sleeplessness</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Chứng <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"18\">mất ngủ</strong> (sleeplessness/insomnia) là thứ mà rất ít người trong các bộ lạc này mắc phải so với tỷ lệ cao ở các nước công nghiệp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. overweight</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 9, dòng 1: “Not a single one is <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">overweight</strong>, indicating their overall higher levels of physical fitness.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Không một ai trong số họ bị <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">thừa cân</strong>, cho thấy mức độ thể chất của họ rất tốt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. hearts</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 9, dòng 2: “They also tended to have healthier <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">hearts</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bên cạnh thể chất tốt, họ cũng có trái tim (<strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">hearts</strong>) khỏe mạnh hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('820ebb83-6577-4207-9a78-6103e115aa8f', '56ee2e5a-20b9-4fca-84f0-d363d0067a01', 'matrix', ' Questions 14–19', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 2 has seven paragraphs, <strong>A-G</strong>.</p>
<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A-G</strong>, in boxes <strong>14-19.</strong></p>', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": " a finding that humans can distinguish between two extremely similar substances", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "a categorisation of species according to their sensitivity to smell", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "an instance where smell negatively affected people''s ability to make choices", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "a study that proved humans could perceive a tiny quantity of a substance", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "an observation that studies of the sense of smell have been undervalued", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "an example of using smell to prompt people to buy something", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 14</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">D</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “We are also exceptionally gifted at telling smells apart, even in the case of <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">two molecules</strong> whose only difference is that their structures are <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"155\">mirror images</strong> of one another.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc phân biệt được hai phân tử là “hình ảnh phản chiếu” (mirror images) của nhau minh chứng cho khả năng phân biệt hai chất cực kỳ giống nhau (extremely similar substances).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 15</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">B</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…he suggested that mammals can be classed into two broad groups: <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">microsmatic mammals</strong>, such as dogs… while we… are <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"132\">microsmatic</strong> [sic – microsmatic/macrosmatic confusion in original text logic]…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Pierre Paul Broca đã thực hiện phân loại (categorisation) các loài động vật thành hai nhóm dựa trên độ nhạy bén về khứu giác của chúng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 16</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">F</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…when men were subjected to a novel smell… during a task used to test <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">decision-making skills</strong>, they performed <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">significantly worse than normal</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nghiên cứu của William Overman cho thấy mùi hương làm giảm hiệu quả thực hiện các nhiệm vụ đòi hỏi kỹ năng đưa ra quyết định (make choices).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 17</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">C</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “One study, for example, found that we can detect certain chemicals diluted in water to <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">less than one part per billion</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Less than one part per billion” (ít hơn một phần tỷ) tương ứng với một lượng chất cực nhỏ (a tiny quantity of a substance).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 18</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">A</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Noses have certainly <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">never been at the forefront</strong> of sensory research, and were <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">pushed aside until recently</strong> in favour of the seemingly more vital senses of vision and hearing.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc bị “đẩy sang một bên” và “không bao giờ ở vị trí hàng đầu” cho thấy các nghiên cứu về khứu giác đã bị đánh giá thấp (undervalued).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 19</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">E</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…estate agents, who often advocate the smell of baking bread or brewing coffee to <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">promote the sale of a house</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc dùng mùi bánh mì hay cà phê để thúc đẩy việc bán nhà là ví dụ về dùng mùi hương để kích thích mọi người mua hàng (buy something).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('123964b4-4f21-497b-b198-c4d6b5a5c9c2', '618a0771-05ed-4629-a435-693019173a38', 'fillup', 'Questions 24–26', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Producing spider silk in the lab</strong></p>
<p>Both scientists and manufacturers are interested in producing silk for many different purposes. Some researchers have tried to grow silk by introducing genetic material into {Bacteria} and some animals. But these experiments have been somewhat disappointing.</p>
<p>It is difficult to make spider silk in a lab setting because the silk comes from a liquid protein made in a {Gland} inside the spider’s body. When a spider spins silk, it causes a {transformation} that turns this liquid into solid silk. Scientists cannot replicate this yet.</p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>24.  Some researchers have tried to grow silk by introducing genetic material into <strong>Bacteria</strong> and some animals.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Bacteria</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “Several groups have tried inserting spider genes into <strong>bacteria</strong> or even cows and goats to produce silk…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>25.It is difficult to make spider silk in a lab because the silk comes from a liquid protein made in a <strong>Gland</strong> inside the spider’s body.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Gland</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “…it starts out as a liquid protein that’s produced by a special <strong>gland</strong> in the spider’s abdomen.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>26.<strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Transformation</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí trong bài:</strong> Đoạn cuối, câu: <em data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">\"...the spider applies forces to produce a <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">transformation</strong> from liquid to solid...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khi nhện nhả tơ, nó dùng lực để tạo ra một sự biến đổi (transformation) từ dạng lỏng sang dạng rắn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('35e07f4f-ccfe-4927-a80a-05f2240447a3', '30cc5ddf-20e1-41e7-af22-e96be223faaf', 'radio', 'Questions 27–31', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "the development of academic skills"}, {"content": "the documenting of information"}, {"content": "the completion of assignments"}, {"content": "the exchange of ideas"}], "question": "Which of the following is mentioned in the article in relation to classroom-based learning?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "think sequentially"}, {"content": "research different points of view"}, {"content": "limit their responses to other students"}, {"content": "follow more than one discussion at a time."}], "question": "Ruberg, Taylor and Moore point out that web-based learning requires learners to"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "Online discussions demand less attention than face-to-face ones."}, {"content": "Teachers have difficulty monitoring the length of comments."}, {"content": "Face-to-face interactions between students are lost."}, {"content": "There is a delay in giving feedback to students."}], "question": "What problem did Sproull and Kiesler identify with online discussions?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "listening to a discussion"}, {"content": "a feeling of being part of a group."}, {"content": "posting ideas on an electronic bulletin board."}, {"content": "having a good relationship with other students."}], "question": "The writer refers to the concept of online presence as"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "to examine the relationship between presence and course outcomes"}, {"content": "to analyse the differences between online and class-based courses"}, {"content": "to examine the importance of being present in a classroom"}, {"content": "to demonstrate that online courses are not generally effective"}], "question": "What was a focus of Anthony Picciano''s study?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 27</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">the exchange of ideas</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Common elements for learning in a typical classroom environment are the social and communicative interactions… The ability to ask a question, to share an opinion… or to disagree…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Social and communicative interactions” (tương tác xã hội và giao tiếp) và “share an opinion” (chia sẻ quan điểm) chính là các hình thức trao đổi ý tưởng (exchange of ideas).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 28</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">follow more than one discussion at a time.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Web-based learning sessions… can have multiple threads with several discussions and Interactions progressing simultaneously.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Simultaneously” có nghĩa là đồng thời. Việc có nhiều luồng (multiple threads) diễn ra cùng lúc buộc người học phải theo dõi nhiều cuộc thảo luận một lúc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 29</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">There is a delay in giving feedback to students.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…discussions based on misinformation, that continue because online an instructor cannot necessarily immediately correct or clarify a comment.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc giảng viên không thể sửa lỗi “ngay lập tức” (immediately) tạo ra sự chậm trễ (delay) trong việc đưa ra phản hồi hoặc đính chính cho sinh viên.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 30</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">a feeling of being part of a group.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The simplest definition of presence for an online course refers to a student’s sense of being registered and belonging in a course…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Sense of belonging” (cảm giác thuộc về) đồng nghĩa với việc cảm thấy mình là một phần của nhóm (being part of a group).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 31</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">to examine the relationship between presence and course outcomes</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “An attempt was made to go beyond student perceptions… and to include perceptions of social presence… In addition, data was collected on performance measures that related specifically to course objectives.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nghiên cứu của Picciano tập trung vào cả sự hiện diện (presence) và các thước đo kết quả học tập (performance measures/outcomes).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('22cd88f0-7a72-4dd2-8c76-8562d5eb87ad', '64f6ee96-c0c2-4b89-b5e6-99cd133a57e5', 'radio', 'Questions 35-36', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answers</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "It smells good"}, {"content": "It can save food freshness"}, {"content": "It can be used on other materials"}, {"content": "Some other things need to be revised about it."}], "question": "Why choose the PLA as a material for food packaging?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "Absorbing moisture"}, {"content": "Composting facilities"}, {"content": "Packaging fresh food"}, {"content": "Manufacturing"}], "question": "What is PLA packaging is used for?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. Why choose the PLA as a material for food packaging?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dịch nghĩa</strong>: Tại sao nên chọn PLA làm vật liệu cho bao bì thực phẩm?</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án</strong>: <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">It can save food freshness</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn H, câu 1: “As Nature Works PLA polymers are both oil- and grease-resistant and provide a <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">better flavor and aroma barrier</strong> than existing petroleum-based polymers, grocery retailers are increasingly using this packaging for their <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"243\">fresh foods</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Nhờ khả năng ngăn cản mùi và hương vị (flavor and aroma barrier) tốt hơn nhựa truyền thống, PLA giúp bảo quản độ tươi ngon và hương vị của thực phẩm (save food freshness).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. What is PLA packaging is used for?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dịch nghĩa</strong>: Bao bì PLA được sử dụng để làm gì?</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án</strong>: <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">Packaging fresh food</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn G, câu cuối: “<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">Packaging applications</strong> include packaging films and <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">food and beverage containers</strong>.” và Đoạn H, câu 1: “…grocery retailers are increasingly using this packaging for their <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"200\">fresh foods</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Ngoài các ứng dụng làm màng bọc và hộp đựng đồ uống, bao bì PLA hiện đang được các nhà bán lẻ thực phẩm sử dụng rộng rãi để đóng gói thực phẩm tươi sống (fresh food).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d28d1b80-a46b-4876-9c71-a7ee2941c105', '64f6ee96-c0c2-4b89-b5e6-99cd133a57e5', 'checkbox', 'Questions 37-38', NULL, '<p>Which <strong>TWO</strong> features of PLA are correct?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "It takes in moisture of skin", "correct": true}, {"option": "It is waterproof", "correct": false}, {"option": "Comfortable sportswear", "correct": true}, {"option": "It’s fading under the sun", "correct": false}, {"option": "It is only made in deep color", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37 &amp; 38. Which TWO features of PLA are correct?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án A: It takes in moisture of skin</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2,0,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn H, câu cuối: “…sportswear makers have been drawn to the product as it has an inherent ability to <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">take moisture away from the skin</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Một đặc điểm nổi bật của PLA là khả năng tự nhiên giúp hút ẩm (mồ hôi) ra khỏi da, làm cho người mặc cảm thấy thoải mái hơn.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án C: Comfortable sportswear</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn H, câu cuối: “…when blended with cotton and wool, the result is <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">garments that are lighter and better at absorbing moisture</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Vì PLA nhẹ và thấm hút mồ hôi tốt, nó rất phù hợp để làm đồ thể thao (sportswear), mang lại sự thoải mái cho người sử dụng.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7c8eaf0a-76ff-45c5-8511-0f02770e1f52', '64f6ee96-c0c2-4b89-b5e6-99cd133a57e5', 'checkbox', 'Questions 39-40', NULL, '<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>features of PLA are correct?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "It is made of renewable raw materials", "correct": true}, {"option": "It involves the removal of carbon dioxide", "correct": true}, {"option": "It is no use of fossil fuel product", "correct": false}, {"option": "It uses renewable raw resources", "correct": false}, {"option": "It is sustenance which can absorb the CO2 in the atmosphere", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. What is the advantage of PLA?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án</strong>: <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">It uses less fossil fuel</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn I, câu 3: “As an alternative to traditional petroleum-based polymers, the production of PLA <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">uses 20%-50% less fossil fuel</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Một trong những lợi ích môi trường lớn nhất của PLA là quá trình sản xuất tiêu thụ ít nhiên liệu hóa thạch hơn (dầu mỏ, than đá) so với các loại nhựa truyền thống từ 20% đến 50%.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. What is the environmental benefit of PLA?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án</strong>: <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">Release lower amount of greenhouse gases</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn I, câu 3: “…and <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">releases a lower amount of greenhouse gases</strong> than comparable petroleum-based plastic…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Bên cạnh việc tiết kiệm nhiên liệu, việc sản xuất PLA còn thải ra ít khí gây hiệu ứng nhà kính hơn, giúp giảm thiểu tác động tiêu cực đến biến đổi khí hậu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 4);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4cc72541-5a01-42e1-9d76-175fd9d98e67', '56ee2e5a-20b9-4fca-84f0-d363d0067a01', 'matrix', 'Questions 20–23', NULL, '<p>Look at the following statements (Questions 20-23) and the list of people below.</p>
<p>Match each statement with the correct person, <strong>A-F</strong>.</p>', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "A faint smell could motivate people to do household chores", "correctCategoryLetter": "E "}, {"itemText": "Humans are better equipped to interpret smell than other species are", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Smell is associated with feelings, rather than the logical part of the brain", "correctCategoryLetter": "F "}, {"itemText": "Humans do not require a sophisticated ability to smell", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Liliane Mujica-parodi", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Pierre Paul Broca", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Charles Greer", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": " Hendrick Schifferstein and colleagues", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "Rob Holland", "categoryLetter": "E "}, {"categoryText": "William Overman and colleagues", "categoryLetter": "F "}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 20</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">E (Rob Holland)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Meanwhile, <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"23\">Rob Holland</strong>… found that the hint of aroma wafting out of a hidden bucket of citrus-scented cleaner was enough to persuade students… to <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"162\">clean up after themselves</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hành động “dọn dẹp” (clean up) tương ứng với làm việc nhà (household chores).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 21</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">C (Charles Greer)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…<strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">Charles Greer</strong>… has shown that the human nose and brain are <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">unusually well connected</strong>, with each group of receptors linking to many more neural regions than is the case in other animals.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự kết nối “tốt một cách bất thường” giữa mũi và não người so với các động vật khác cho thấy con người được trang bị tốt hơn để giải thích/xử lý mùi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 22</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">F (William Overman and colleagues)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…<strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">William Overman</strong>… The researchers conclude the scent stimulated brain areas <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">connected with emotion</strong>, making their decisions <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">emotional rather than rational</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Kết luận này chỉ ra mùi hương liên quan đến cảm xúc hơn là phần logic/duy lý (rational part) của não bộ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 23</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">B (Pierre Paul Broca)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “<strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Pierre Paul Broca</strong>… suggested that mammals can be classed into two broad groups… [humans] have small olfactory organs that we <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">only rely on to a small extent</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Quan điểm của Broca cho rằng con người chỉ dựa vào khứu giác ở mức độ nhỏ, nghĩa là không yêu cầu một khả năng ngửi tinh vi/phức tạp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ddfab42c-dd1c-4f2c-b1c8-987b3f0cb8a7', '56ee2e5a-20b9-4fca-84f0-d363d0067a01', 'fillup', 'Questions 24–26', '<p>Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>The {Amygdala} is a part of the brain that deals with feeling and smell.</p>
<p>{Unpleasant} smells create especially powerful associations with memories.</p>
<p>Of all the senses, smell has the capacity to prompt memories of {Childhood} .</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 24</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">Amygdala</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…there are certain brain areas dedicated to <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">both emotion and olfaction</strong>, such as the <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">amygdala</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Amygdala là phần não chuyên biệt cho cả cảm xúc (feeling) và khứu giác (smell).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 25</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">Unpleasant</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the link between a memory and a smell is stronger if the smell is <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">unpleasant</strong> rather than pleasant.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mùi “không dễ chịu” tạo ra sự liên kết với ký ức mạnh mẽ hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 26</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">Childhood</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…this explains why smells often transport us back to our <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">childhood</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định mùi hương có khả năng gợi lại những ký ức từ thời thơ ấu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ba340d7b-7e74-4686-a906-99304932c484', '05599c28-4002-4c4b-aa0e-4cb2220b835f', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–35', '<p id="p-rc_ccc7eaa6a8e1964e-503" data-path-to-node="15"><span class="citation-62473">Complete the summary </span><span class="citation-62471 citation-62472 citation-62473 citation-end-62473">below.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="60"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-62471 citation-62472 citation-end-62472"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="61"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-62471 citation-end-62471"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="62"><!----></sup></span></p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></div>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<p id="p-rc_ccc7eaa6a8e1964e-504" data-path-to-node="16"><span class="citation-62468 citation-62469 citation-62470">Choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="16" data-index-in-node="7"><span class="citation-62468 citation-62469 citation-62470">ONE WORD ONLY</span></strong><span class="citation-62468 citation-62469 citation-62470 citation-end-62470"> from the passage for each answer.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="63"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-62468 citation-62469 citation-end-62469"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="64"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-62468 citation-end-62468"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="65"><!----></sup></span></p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></div>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<p id="p-rc_ccc7eaa6a8e1964e-505" data-path-to-node="17"><span class="citation-62465 citation-62466 citation-62467 citation-end-62467">Write your answe<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="66"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-62465 citation-62466 citation-end-62466">rs in boxes 31–35 on your answer sheet.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="67"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-62465 citation-end-62465"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="68"><!----></sup></span></p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9592%; height: 2px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 2px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 99.8776%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 33.7083px;">
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p style="text-align: center;" data-path-to-node="18,0"><span class="citation-62463 citation-62464 citation-end-62464"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Contemporary hunter-gatherer societies</strong></span><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="69"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-62463 citation-end-62463"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="70"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p id="p-rc_ccc7eaa6a8e1964e-506" data-path-to-node="18,1"><span class="citation-62461 citation-62462">Bruce Knauft''s research shows that contemporary hunter-gatherer societies tend to exhibit a high level of<strong> </strong>{egalitarianism}</span><span class="citation-62461 citation-62462 citation-end-62462"> in all areas of l<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="71"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-62461">ife. In these cultures, distributing resources </span><span class="citation-62460 citation-62461 citation-end-62461">fairly among all members is a moral obligation. These societies also employ strategies to prevent differences i<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="72"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-62460">n {status}</span><span class="citation-62460"> occurring: for example, the </span><em data-path-to-node="18,1" data-index-in-node="399"><span class="citation-62460">!Kung</span></em><span class="citation-62460"> follow a custom whereby </span><span class="citation-62459 citation-62460">the credit for one person''s success at<strong> </strong>{hunting}</span><span class="citation-62459 citation-62460 citation-end-62460"> is given to another mem<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="73"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-62459">ber of the group. Individuals who behave in a {domineering}</span><span class="citation-62459"> manner are punished by being excluded from the group, and women have a considerable amount of {autonomy}</span><span class="citation-62459 citation-end-62459"> in choices regarding <sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="74"><!----></sup></span>work and marriage.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p data-path-to-node="17"> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. egalitarianism — {Bruce Knauft''s research shows that contemporary hunter-gatherer societies tend to exhibit a high level of egalitarianism in all areas of life.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“As the anthropologist Bruce Knauft has remarked, hunter-gatherers are characterised by <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">''extreme political and sexual egalitarianism''</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Tend to exhibit a high level of...\" (có xu hướng thể hiện mức độ cao về...) tương ứng với từ \"characterised by extreme...\" (được đặc trưng bởi sự cực kỳ...). Từ cần điền là chủ nghĩa bình đẳng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"207\">egalitarianism</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. status — {These societies also employ strategies to prevent differences in status occurring}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“They also have methods of <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">preserving egalitarianism by ensuring that disparities of status don''t arise</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Prevent... occurring\" (ngăn chặn... xảy ra) đồng nghĩa với cụm \"ensuring that... don''t arise\" (đảm bảo rằng... không xuất hiện). \"Differences\" (sự khác biệt/chênh lệch) tương ứng với \"disparities\". Do đó, họ muốn ngăn chặn sự chênh lệch về mặt địa vị (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"265\">status</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. hunting — {for example, the !Kung follow a custom whereby the credit for one person''s success at hunting is given to another member of the group.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_ff6912db2e521ec5-25\" data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<span class=\"citation-130\">The !Kung people of southern Africa, for example, swap arrows </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\"><span class=\"citation-130\">before going hunting and when an animal is killed, the acclaim does not go to the person who fired the arrow</span></strong><span class=\"citation-130 citation-end-130\">, but to the person the arrow belongs t<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span>o.”</em></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!---->\n<p> </p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"The credit for one person''s success\" (sự công nhận/tuyên dương cho thành công của một người) tương ứng với từ \"the acclaim\" (sự hoan nghênh/ca ngợi). Thành công khi giết được một con thú chính là thành công trong việc đi săn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"239\">hunting</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. domineering — {Individuals who behave in a domineering manner are punished by being excluded from the group}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“And <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">if a person becomes too domineering, the other members of the group ostracise them, exiling the offender from society</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Behave in a domineering manner\" tương ứng với cụm \"becomes too domineering\" (trở nên quá hống hách/áp đặt). Hình phạt dành cho họ là bị tẩy chay và trục xuất (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"172\">ostracise / exiling</strong>), tương ứng với cụm \"punished by being excluded from the group\". Từ cần điền là (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"273\">domineering</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. autonomy — {and women have a considerable amount of autonomy in choices regarding work and marriage.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">Women in hunter-gatherer groups worldwide often benefit from a high level of autonomy</strong>, being able to <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">select their own marriage partners, decide what work they do</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"A considerable amount of\" (một lượng đáng kể) tương ứng với \"a high level of\" (mức độ cao). Phụ nữ ở các bộ lạc này có quyền tự chủ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">autonomy</strong>) rất lớn trong việc tự chọn bạn đời (marriage) và quyết định công việc (work).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2fbe6457-edf0-4c63-9605-d11dc486d7cc', '05599c28-4002-4c4b-aa0e-4cb2220b835f', 'radio', 'Questions 36–40', '', '<p><span class="citation-62455">Choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="23,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-62455">YES</span></strong><span class="citation-62455 citation-end-62455"> if the statement agrees with the views of the writer<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="78"><!----></sup></span> <strong data-path-to-node="23,0" data-index-in-node="57"><span class="citation-62454">NO</span></strong><span class="citation-62454 citation-end-62454"> if the statement<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="79"><!----></sup></span> <span class="citation-62452 citation-62453 citation-end-62453">contradicts the views of the writer<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="80"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-62452 citation-end-62452"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="81"><!----></sup></span> <strong data-path-to-node="23,0" data-index-in-node="113"><span class="citation-62450 citation-62451">NOT GIVEN</span></strong><span class="citation-62450 citation-62451 citation-end-62451"> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="82"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-62450 citation-end-62450"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="83"><!----></sup></span></p>', 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some anthropologists are mistaken about the point when the number of societies such as the !Kung began to decline."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Humans who developed warlike traits in prehistory would have had an advantage over those who did not."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Being peaceful and cooperative is a natural way for people to behave."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Negative traits are more apparent in some modern cultures than in others."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Animal research has failed to reveal a link between changes in the environment and the emergence of aggressive tendencies."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. NOT GIVEN — {Some anthropologists are mistaken about the point when the number of societies such as the !Kung began to decline.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Many anthropologists believe that societies such as the !Kung were normal <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">until a few thousand years ago, when population growth led to the development of agriculture and a settled lifestyle</strong>.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nêu thông tin là nhiều nhà nhân chủng học tin rằng các xã hội như bộ lạc !Kung từng rất phổ biến cho đến vài nghìn năm trước (khi nông nghiệp phát triển). Tác giả <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"187\">không hề đưa ra nhận định</strong> rằng có một số nhà nhân chủng học đang bị sai lầm/nhầm lẫn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"273\">mistaken</strong>) về mốc thời gian suy giảm này hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. NO — {Humans who developed warlike traits in prehistory would have had an advantage over those who did not.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In view of the above, there seems little reason to assume that traits such as racism, warfare and male domination should have been selected by evolution – as they would have been of <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"203\">little benefit in the prehistoric era</strong>. there since they would have been ostracised from their groups.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói rằng những người phát triển đặc tính hiếu chiến (warlike traits) ở thời tiền sử sẽ có lợi thế hơn (had an advantage). Ngược lại, bài đọc khẳng định những đặc tính này mang lại <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"200\">rất ít lợi ích</strong> (little benefit) và những cá nhân hành xử tàn nhẫn, ích kỷ thực chất còn <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"288\">ít có cơ hội sống sót hơn</strong> (less likely to survive) vì sẽ bị bộ lạc tẩy chay. Hai thông tin trái ngược hoàn toàn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. YES — {Being peaceful and cooperative is a natural way for people to behave.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“It makes more sense, then, to see <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">traits such as cooperation, egalitarianism, altruism and peacefulness as innate characteristics of human beings</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định rõ ràng các đặc tính như hợp tác (cooperation) và hòa bình (peacefulness) chính là những đặc tính bẩm sinh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">innate characteristics</strong>) của con người. \"Innate\" (bẩm sinh/vốn có) đồng nghĩa với \"a natural way for people to behave\" (một cách hành xử tự nhiên).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. NOT GIVEN — {Negative traits are more apparent in some modern cultures than in others.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 9):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“But if prehistoric life wasn''t really as brutal as has often been assumed, <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">why do modern humans behave so selfishly and ruthlessly?</strong>”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả có đặt câu hỏi và bàn luận về việc tại sao \"con người hiện đại\" nói chung lại hành xử ích kỷ và tàn nhẫn. Tuy nhiên, bài viết <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">không hề có sự so sánh</strong> xem các đặc tính tiêu cực này biểu hiện rõ ràng hơn ở nền văn hóa hiện đại này so với nền văn hóa hiện đại khác (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"282\">more apparent in some modern cultures than in others</strong>) hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. NO — {Animal research has failed to reveal a link between changes in the environment and the emergence of aggressive tendencies.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 9):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">Research has shown repeatedly that when the natural habitats of primates such as apes and gorillas are disrupted, they tend to become more violent</strong> and hierarchical.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói rằng nghiên cứu trên động vật đã \"thất bại trong việc chỉ ra mối liên hệ\" (failed to reveal a link). Thế nhưng bài đọc lại khẳng định các nghiên cứu trên loài linh trưởng (khỉ không đuôi, đười ươi) đã \"chỉ ra nhiều lần\" (shown repeatedly) là khi môi trường sống bị phá vỡ/thay đổi (habitats are disrupted) thì chúng sẽ có xu hướng trở nên hung hăng/bạo lực hơn (become more violent). Do thông tin đối chọi nhau nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"449\">NO</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('933d69de-0d95-4e81-a975-5a1728052126', '2f00312d-400f-4a10-b864-a69d9f506b34', 'fillup', 'Questions 1-10', '<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
