', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>1. Celluloid&#8230; Common uses: photographic film</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>photographic film</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) &#8220;But perhaps the best-known celluloid product was <strong>photographic film</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>2. Name: Bakelite</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Bakelite</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) &#8220;Leo Baekeland&#8230; invented a different kind of plastic, by causing phenol and formaldehyde to react together. Baekeland called it <strong>Bakelite</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>3. Bakelite&#8230; Common uses: electrical switches</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>electrical switches</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) &#8220;&#8230;it was soon being used in the manufacture of <strong>electrical switches</strong> as well as a variety of domestic items.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>4. Polythene&#8230; Country of origin: Britain</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Britain</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) &#8220;In the 1930s, chemists in <strong>Britain</strong> discovered that the gas ethylene would polymerize under heat and pressure to form a thermoplastic they called polythene.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>5. Rigid PVC&#8230; Properties: Is fireproof</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>fireproof</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) &#8220;&#8230;produced rigid PVC (polyvinyl chloride), a <strong>fireproof</strong> plastic suitable for drains and gutters.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>6. Polystyrene&#8230; Properties: Resembles glass</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>glass</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) &#8220;<strong>Polystyrene</strong>, a hard, clear material <strong>like glass</strong>, was developed during the 1930s in Germany&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>7. Polyurethane&#8230; Usually manufactured as a foam</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>foam</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) &#8220;<strong>Polyurethane</strong>, developed in the same country, was commonly produced as a <strong>foam</strong> which was very useful in the production of insulating materials.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('080f81fc-d182-4714-85f3-c23280525f64', 'e0405caa-d516-499c-b82e-9d57cc95974b', 'radio', 'Questions 8–13', '<p>Choose TRUE if the statement agrees with the information  FALSE if the statement contradicts the information  NOT GIVEN if there is no information on this</p>
', '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information  <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information  <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The chemical structure of rubber is very different to that of plastics"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "John Wesley Hyatt was an industrial chemist"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Celluloid and Bakelite react in the same way to heat"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "If an object is made of several plastics, these prove hard to break down and reuse"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Adding starch to plastic makes it more durable"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Containers which are designed to decompose need particular storage conditions."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>8. The chemical structure of rubber is very different to that of plastics.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) &#8220;Chemically, rubber is a <strong>polymer</strong>&#8230; The same bonding principle-<strong>polymerization</strong>-is the basis of the creation of a huge range of <strong>plastics</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cả cao su và nhựa đều là polymer, dựa trên cùng một nguyên tắc liên kết hóa học, do đó cấu trúc của chúng tương đồng chứ không khác biệt rất nhiều.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>9. John Wesley Hyatt was an industrial chemist.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) &#8220;The prize was won by <strong>John Wesley Hyatt</strong>, with a material called celluloid.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản nêu tên John Wesley Hyatt nhưng <strong>không cung cấp thông tin</strong> về nghề nghiệp hay lĩnh vực chuyên môn của ông.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>10. Celluloid and Bakelite react in the same way to heat.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) &#8220;<strong>Celluloid can be repeatedly softened and reshaped by heat</strong>, and is known as a thermoplastic. &#8230;Bakelite&#8230; was the first of the <strong>thermosets</strong>-plastic that can be cast and moulded while hot, but <strong>cannot be softened by heat and reshaped once they have set</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Celluloid (thermoplastic) có thể làm mềm, Bakelite (thermoset) thì không thể, tức là chúng phản ứng khác nhau.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>11. If an object is made of several plastics, these prove hard to break down and reuse.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) &#8220;Nor is it very easy to recycle plastics, as <strong>different types of plastic are often found in the same items and call for different treatments</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nhiều loại nhựa khác nhau trong cùng một vật phẩm cần quy trình xử lý khác nhau, khiến việc tái chế (break down and reuse) rất khó khăn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>12. Adding starch to plastic makes it more durable.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 9) &#8220;Plastics can be made biodegradable by incorporating into their structure a material such as <strong>starch, which is attacked by bacteria and causes the plastic to fall apart</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Thêm tinh bột làm nhựa bị phân hủy (fall apart), tức là <strong>ít bền</strong> hơn, mâu thuẫn với &#8220;more durable&#8221; (bền hơn).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>13. Containers which are designed to decompose need particular storage conditions.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 9) &#8220;&#8230;although bottles made of such materials have to be <strong>stored in the dark</strong>, to ensure they do not disintegrate before they have been used.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các chai lọ làm từ vật liệu phân hủy sinh học cần được lưu trữ trong bóng tối (particular storage conditions).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('48a5367f-e3e5-4934-b8aa-e7b37196968c', '6d435446-b99b-409d-822b-3b2bc9a7a34e', 'radio', 'Questions 21–24', NULL, '<p data-start="90" data-end="116">Choose the correct answer.</p>
<p data-start="118" data-end="158"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">The Just-in-Time Supply System (JIT)</span></strong></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "given credit to the originators of the JIT idea"}, {"content": "discussed why the Japanese adopted the JIT idea"}, {"content": "explained how supermarkets used the JIT idea"}], "question": "Ron suggests that in his presentation he should have"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "a description of classic business theory"}, {"content": "an introductory definition of JIT"}, {"content": "a statement of the aims of JIT"}], "question": "The tutor says that in his presentation Ron omitted"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "a website"}, {"content": "journal articles"}, {"content": "a textbook"}], "question": "Ron says that he found his information on standardising parts from"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "difficult to apply because of the absence of countable things"}, {"content": "regarded by most members of staff as unfashionable"}, {"content": "unlikely to be accepted by important clients"}], "question": "The tutor suggests that in the service sector, JIT is"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 3: FEEDBACK ON BUSINESS PRESENTATION</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Thanks, Ron, for coming to my office to discuss the presentation you gave yesterday to the Business Management Seminar. We’ll go over what you did with the aim of helping you improve your next presentation.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Sounds good.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Now, the topic was the Just-in-Time, or J-I-T supply system used by a lot of manufacturers, first in Japan and then in the West, I think?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Yes, but actually one thing <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">(21) I should have made clearer and talked about was the fact that the Americans actually pioneered the idea of Just-in-Time [Answer: A – credit to the originators]</strong></span>, though it wasn’t called that. Henry Ford and his cars, in fact, at the turn of the 20th century. And later, a big US supermarket chain used it, and this was where Toyota in Japan got the idea for its car making.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Yes, that would have been a good addition. And now before we go any further, I think I would suggest that <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">(22) you should have stopped and clearly defined Just-in-Time for your seminar colleagues [Answer: B – introductory definition]</strong></span>. You said its aim was to reduce waste, and you mentioned that classic business theory assumes that stock or inventory of parts are counted as assets, but Just-in-Time sees them as unnecessary waste. But you never told us that J-I-T simply means waiting until the last moment to order new supplies as you need them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Yes, you’re right. I should have done that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Now, you talked a bit about standardizing parts as a way of streamlining JIT. Where did you get your data from?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Well, I tried an internet website on the subject, which is called the Lean Clearing House, but it was too technical for me. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"129\">(23) So in the end, I got my data from a textbook called “Learning from Toyota” [Answer: C – textbook]</strong></span>. I found some journal articles too, but they didn’t seem very useful.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Yes, well, there is a US government report on it I’ve seen. I’ll get a copy for you.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Great, I look forward to reading through it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> And while you’re at it, you might want to find out about cases where JIT might not be suitable, and that’s in service industries like tourism or healthcare, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">(24) where customers are paying for something that they can’t actually see or count [Answer: A – absence of countable things]</strong></span>. Although J-I-T is fashionable today, some people would say it hasn’t proved so successful in the service sector as it has with the manufacturing of goods that can be quantified.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> That would be interesting. I’ll see what I can find out.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"15\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CRITIQUE OF TECHNICAL ASPECTS (Questions 25–30)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Now, unless you have any more questions, let’s turn to a critique of the technical aspects of the presentation. I’m afraid I’ll emphasize the things I think you might want to work on. It was a good talk, but with a little work, your next presentation should be excellent.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Fine, that would be helpful. Actually, I wasn’t happy with my <strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">delivery</strong>. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">(25) I sometimes seemed to talk fast and sometimes slow [Answer: B – too irregular]</strong></span>. I was on edge, I guess.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Yes, you were. And as well as that, your <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">purpose</strong> wasn’t very specific. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">(26) In future, you need to lay out exactly what you’re going to cover and why [Answer: H – too vague]</strong></span>. Make it clear and concise and not so general.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> And what about my <strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"23\">transitions</strong> from one section to the next?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Well, you didn’t link the sections, did you? You went too quickly from one to the next.<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">(27) It was all just too abrupt [Answer: D – too sudden]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> OK, I’ll try to improve that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Now, your <strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"17\">PowerPoint visuals</strong> were lovely, but sometimes I got the feeling that, nice as they were as pictures, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">(28) they didn’t have much to do with what you were talking about [Answer: G – too loosely related]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Right, you’re right.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> And you know, another thing I could see from the other students’ reactions: <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">(29) they just didn’t understand some of the vocabulary I was using [Answer: E – too technical]</strong></span>. Remember your audience were laymen, mostly without knowledge of JIT, so you need to simplify and try to put things in everyday English.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> I never seem to do that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> And lastly, I’ll just mention your <strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">body language</strong>. You didn’t use gestures, and you just stood straight without any animation. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">(30) It didn’t make you seem very interested in the subject [Answer: F – too unenthusiastic]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> I know, even though I really do like the subject. Sorry.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Well, despite all this, I enjoyed your presentation and I could see you put lots of work into it. I look forward to an even better presentation from you next time.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Well, thanks for your help.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('738b10df-cec1-4d05-acde-2708041a67af', '1c29c23e-44ee-491f-88f2-e0c0c89a5617', 'radio', 'Questions 11-16', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B </strong>or <strong>C</strong>.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A 15 years ago"}, {"content": "B 30 years ago"}, {"content": "C 60 years ago"}], "question": "When was Eyesaver founded?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A to offer common equipment"}, {"content": "B to offer medication to children with eye diseases"}, {"content": "C to offer operational help to people who had eye problems"}], "question": "What was the original aim of the program?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A monthly donation"}, {"content": "B donation from rich people"}, {"content": "C money collected on the street"}], "question": "The main funding comes from"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A glasses for the patients"}, {"content": "B money donation"}, {"content": "C voluntary work"}], "question": "14 What does the speaker expect listeners to provide?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A to show people their donation can make a difference"}, {"content": "B to show people how easily eye problems can be cured"}, {"content": "C to educate people about common eye diseases"}], "question": "What is the main purpose of this program?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A computers"}, {"content": "B recordings"}, {"content": "C training"}], "question": "16 Eyesaver advertises for the program through"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 2: EYESAVER CHARITY INTRODUCTION</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Speaker:</strong> Hello everyone, thanks for attending tonight’s event. Let me start with the early history of our charity, Eyesaver.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">Eyesaver was founded by a retired optometrist, Timothy Gains. I have spent much of my working life at Eyesaver. I am 60 years old now, and I started working for this organization 15 years ago when I left a corporate position to help people with eye problems.</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c2bd08e547ad031e-104\" data-path-to-node=\"5\">Now, our charity<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"17\">(11) has been helping people for three decades [Answer: 30 years ago]</strong></span>. <span class=\"citation-1631 citation-1632 citation-end-1632\">You may know that we are now doing various other things to help people with eye problems. That includes medications for children with eye diseases and operational help to those in the public who have eye proble</span><span class=\"citation-1631 citation-end-1631\">ms.</span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c2bd08e547ad031e-105\" data-path-to-node=\"6\"><span class=\"citation-1630 citation-end-1630\">But when Mr. Gains just foun</span>ded Eyesaver, he wanted the program to <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">(12) <span class=\"citation-1628 citation-1629\">be able to offer common eye equipment to those who needed it</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-1628 citation-1629 citation-end-1629\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">.</span></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c2bd08e547ad031e-106\" data-path-to-node=\"7\"><span class=\"citation-1626 citation-1627 citation-end-1627\">We receive occasional donations from corporations and charity groups now. We have over 1,500 volunteers who work on the streets with the little red donat</span><span class=\"citation-1626 citation-end-1626\">ion boxes, which many of you are familiar with, and</span> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"205\">(13) this is the main source of funding for us [Answer: money collected on the street]</strong></span>. <span class=\"citation-1625 citation-end-1625\">Besides, we are planning to work to secure donations from wealthy benefactors.</span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c2bd08e547ad031e-107\" data-path-to-node=\"8\"><span class=\"citation-1624 citation-end-1624\">Many people are passionate about charity cause and have been inquiring how to donate money to us. I really appreciate that, but</span> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">(14) <span class=\"citation-1621 citation-1622 citation-1623\">our main need is to collect glasses for our patients</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-1621 citation-1622 citation-1623 citation-end-1623\">. Many of you have multiple pairs of old glasses in your possession, and we encourage you to gather these pairs which you no longer need and donate them to our cause.</span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c2bd08e547ad031e-108\" data-path-to-node=\"9\"><span class=\"citation-1618 citation-1619 citation-1620 citation-end-1620\">In doing thi</span><span class=\"citation-1618 citation-1619 citation-end-1619\">s, you’ll be able to make sure that someone else can see better. Most of us cannot imagine a life in which we are unable to see well. This i</span><span class=\"citation-1618 citation-end-1618\">s why your eyeglass donations are so critical to our mission.</span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c2bd08e547ad031e-109\" data-path-to-node=\"10\"><span class=\"citation-1617 citation-end-1617\">And as a side note, we offer full-time positions; let me know i</span>f you are interested. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">(15) Our goal is to make people aware that even the smallest of donations can help change a person’s life [Answer: to show people their donation can make a difference]</strong></span>, <span class=\"citation-1615 citation-1616 citation-end-1616\">so your donation can be a turning point for them.</span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c2bd08e547ad031e-110\" data-path-to-node=\"11\"><span class=\"citation-1613 citation-1614 citation-end-1614\">The other day, when I was talking to some people on the street, they were surprised to find out how easily some eye problems can be cured. And I’m proud to say that our next program wil</span><span class=\"citation-1613 citation-end-1613\">l aim at educating people about common eye diseases. We are able to prevent many fatal eye problems.</span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c2bd08e547ad031e-111\" data-path-to-node=\"12\"><span class=\"citation-1612 citation-end-1612\">In order to publicize our charity progra</span>m, we surely need to do some advertising. When we first started our program, we used computers to create awareness for our cause. For instance, promoting seminars in which we informed people as to how they could help us to solve eye problems.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c2bd08e547ad031e-112\" data-path-to-node=\"13\">But in recent years, the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">(16) <span class=\"citation-1610 citation-1611\">main means of advertising our program is through audio recordings</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-1610 citation-1611 citation-end-1611\">. We have found it cost-efficient and effective. It’s good to know that many of our staff are recommending our program to their friends and colleagues. But I am</span><span class=\"citation-1610 citation-end-1610\"> afraid that our training cannot show people the whole picture of our pr</span>ogram.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"14\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PARTNERSHIPS AND ROLES (Questions 17–20)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Speaker:</strong> Finally, I would like to tell you about some organizations which have played important roles in the development and success of Eyesaver.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">Our affiliation with the <strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">National Vision Funding Group</strong> has <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">(17) allowed us to gain fame and to become even more significant [Answer: E – take the reputation to a higher level]</strong></span>, so many people around the country are coming for our services.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\">Our association with the <strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">Eye for the Future</strong> organization has allowed us to run cooperative ads by which we <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">(18) seek producers of equipment to work with us [Answer: D – help look for equipment manufacturers]</strong>.</span> Meanwhile, some of our staff has been sent to this organization for some special training. Their skills should be improved very soon.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\">Also, we have had a long-time cooperation with <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">Sam’s Eyecare Institution</strong> (trong script bạn gửi ghi là Sam’s IKEA, nhưng tên đúng trong bài nghe thường là Eyecare). Our relationship with it has given us the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"206\">(19) opportunity to link with many different academic institutions, including colleges and universities [Answer: C – earn support from colleges]</strong></span> with good reputation.</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c2bd08e547ad031e-113\" data-path-to-node=\"20\">And we have a similar friendship with a group called <strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">Youth Health</strong>. Our connection with that group <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">(20) allows us to link directly with young kids [Answer: B – involve more children in need]</strong></span>, <span class=\"citation-1608 citation-1609 citation-end-1609\">since this is a crucial stage in their growth.</span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c2bd08e547ad031e-114\" data-path-to-node=\"21\"><span class=\"citation-1606 citation-1607 citation-end-1607\">We plan to contact with some colleges and hope that with their help, more college students could get to know our program. So as you can see, we have all bases covered in linking with students, as we have affiliations directly with both administrators and the students themselves.</span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c2bd08e547ad031e-115\" data-path-to-node=\"22\"><span class=\"citation-1604 citation-1605 citation-end-1605\">Thank you</span><span class=\"citation-1604 citation-end-1604\"> so much for your attention today as we try to stamp out eye problems. We will appreciate your donations, no matter how large or how small. We believe </span>with our efforts, the world will be a brighter and more beautiful place.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('536aaaa5-3376-4f34-a26f-4e001e037863', '1c29c23e-44ee-491f-88f2-e0c0c89a5617', 'matching', 'Questions 17-20', NULL, '<p>What role does each of the following organisations play for the development of Eyesaver?<br>Write the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>F</strong></p>', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p> </p>\n<p>National Vision Funding Group {take the reputation to a higher level}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Eye for the Future {help look for equipment manufacturers}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Sam''s Eyecare Institution {earn support from colleges}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Youth Health {involve more children in need}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "gain more donation"}, {"optionText": "involve more children in need"}, {"optionText": "earn support from colleges"}, {"optionText": "help look for equipment manufacturers"}, {"optionText": "take the reputation to a higher level"}, {"optionText": "recruit and support staff"}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "National Vision Funding Group", "correctAnswer": "E"}, {"questionPart": "Eye for the Future", "correctAnswer": "D"}, {"questionPart": "Sam''s Eyecare Institution", "correctAnswer": "C"}, {"questionPart": "Youth Health", "correctAnswer": "B"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('85ae27cf-f976-4b44-baf3-e0d663b44fd8', 'd25a9b5b-5959-4f63-a6c5-29021ff6e9f8', 'matching', 'Questions 14–20', '<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below</p>
', '<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i Global resistance to lean manufacturing"}, {"optionText": "ii The historical context"}, {"optionText": "iii Procedures for controlling quality"}, {"optionText": "iv The pros and cons of different production systems"}, {"optionText": "v The impact on profits"}, {"optionText": "vi Procedures for controlling supply"}, {"optionText": "vii The origin of the term"}, {"optionText": "viii A crucial difference in levels of quality"}, {"optionText": "ix Working conditions"}, {"optionText": "x Interdependent strategies for controlling expenditure"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>14. Paragraph A</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: ii. The historical context</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn A đặt Lean Production vào bối cảnh lịch sử, so sánh nó với Mass Production (Henry Ford) và Craft Production, và nêu nguồn gốc của nó (Eiji Toyoda và Taiichi Ohno) ở Nhật Bản.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>15. Paragraph B</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: iv. The pros and cons of different production systems</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn B so sánh ba hệ thống sản xuất chính (Craft, Mass, Lean), tập trung vào ưu điểm (pros) và nhược điểm (cons) của từng loại (ví dụ: Craft quá đắt, Mass quá cứng nhắc và gây chán nản cho nhân viên).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>16. Paragraph C</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: vii. The origin of the term</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn C giải thích thuật ngữ &#8220;Lean Production&#8221; được đặt tên như vậy là do nó sử dụng <strong>ít hơn mọi thứ</strong> (&#8220;less of everything&#8221; / &#8220;half the human effort&#8230; half the manufacturing space&#8230;&#8221;).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>17. Paragraph D</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: viii. A crucial difference in levels of quality</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn D tập trung vào sự khác biệt nổi bật giữa hai hệ thống: Mass Production đặt mục tiêu &#8220;good enough&#8221; (chấp nhận một số lỗi), còn Lean Production <strong>không chấp nhận thỏa hiệp</strong> (&#8220;unwilling to compromise standards&#8221;) về chất lượng (far fewer defects).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>18. Paragraph E</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: x. Interdependent strategies for controlling expenditure</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn E nêu mục tiêu chính là <strong>giảm chi phí</strong> (cost reduction / expenditure), nhưng phải đạt được ba mục tiêu trung gian khác: kiểm soát số lượng (quantity control), đảm bảo chất lượng (quality assurance) và tôn trọng con người (respect for humanity). Ba mục tiêu này <strong>phụ thuộc lẫn nhau</strong> (&#8220;none of these three objectives can be achieved separately&#8221;).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>19. Paragraph F</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: vi. Procedures for controlling supply</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn F mô tả cơ chế <strong>just-in-time</strong> (JIT). JIT là một thủ tục kiểm soát việc <strong>cung cấp</strong> (supply) linh kiện và vật liệu sao cho chúng đến đúng thời điểm và số lượng cần thiết.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>20. Paragraph G</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: iii. Procedures for controlling quality</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn G mô tả <strong>autonamation</strong> (tự động hóa), cơ chế kiểm tra sự bất thường (abnormalities) trong quá trình sản xuất. Mục đích là đảm bảo <strong>chất lượng</strong> (quality control) song song với JIT, ngăn ngừa sự nhân lên của các lỗi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('030c1812-61b3-45eb-8719-9c01310cc1a5', 'd25a9b5b-5959-4f63-a6c5-29021ff6e9f8', 'fillup', 'Questions 21–26', '<p>Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>A small number of unusual cars are still produced by the {craft|craft production} method. Lean production requires staff who are {multi-skilled} Lean production employs fewer people, and uses less {manufacturing space} equipment and time. Storage facilities are not needed if a procedure known as {just-in-time} is implemented in the lean production method. Autonamation is a procedure for spotting any {abnormalities} in the products on a production line.At Toyota factories, {lights} are suspended above manual production lines in order to show where production has to be halted.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>21. A small number of unusual cars are still produced by the craft production method.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>craft production</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) &#8220;A present day example of this method is the customised production of a few exotic sports cars&#8230; The concept of <strong>craft production</strong> remains very popular&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>22. Lean production requires staff who are multi-skilled.&#8221;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>multi-skilled</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) &#8220;&#8230;companies appoint teams of <strong>multi-skilled</strong> workers to all levels of the organisation&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>23. Lean production employs fewer people, and uses less manufacturing space equipment and time.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>manufacturing space</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) &#8220;&#8230;it uses less of everything – half the human effort in the factory, <strong>half the manufacturing space</strong>, half the investment in tools&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>24. Storage facilities are not needed if a procedure known as just-in-time is implemented in the lean production method.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>just-in-time</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) &#8220;If <strong>just-in-time</strong> is fully realised throughout the company, then superfluous inventories are completely eliminated from the factory, making stores or warehouses unnecessary.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>25. Autonamation is a procedure for spotting any abnormalities in the products on a production line.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>abnormalities</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) &#8220;<strong>Autonamation</strong> is the automatic checking for <strong>abnormalities</strong> in the production process.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>26. At Toyota factories, lights are suspended above manual production lines in order to show where production has to be halted.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>lights</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) &#8220;&#8230;the worker pushes a button to stop the whole line, and <strong>lights</strong>, which are hung so high in the factory that they are visible to everyone, indicate the position of the problem.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4193b9d4-f7ab-4771-b264-2723b5b36ee7', '7b6b1330-0948-4b80-a769-acd09500a075', 'matrix', 'Questions 27–32', NULL, '<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>F</strong>, in boxes <strong>27-32.<br></strong></p>
<p><em><strong>NB </strong>You may use any letter more than once.</em></p>', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Reasons why watching sport can bring emotional satisfaction", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "An explanation of why beginners struggle with sports tasks", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "A factor that can work alongside mirroring in sports competitions to maintain peak performance", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "A comparison between the mirror neurons of human beings and primates", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Mention of integrating visual and motor processes to understand athletic movements", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "Reference to the first discovery of brain activity associated with mirror neurons", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>27. reasons why watching sport can bring emotional satisfaction</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: F</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) &#8220;Most spectators tune in for the <strong>emotional roller coaster</strong>&#8230; This emotional connection finds its roots in mirror neurons, which allow spectators to perceive athletes&#8217; victorious movements and to <strong>share in the emotion of their triumphs</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>28. an explanation of why beginners struggle with sports tasks</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: B</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) &#8220;&#8230;for novices, smoothly manoeuvring the asymmetrical metal club presents a nearly impossible challenge. This is because <strong>novices rely on conscious effort</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc dựa vào nỗ lực có ý thức (conscious effort) khiến người mới (novices) gặp khó khăn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>29. a factor that can work alongside mirroring in sports competitions to maintain peak performance</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: E</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) &#8220;The most accomplished athletes possess a premotor cortex capable of <strong>envisioning victorious movements</strong> [imagination], supplemented by the physical attributes required to translate those movements into reality. In this way, action and <strong>imagination coalesce to drive performance</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Khả năng hình dung (imagination) kết hợp với hành động thúc đẩy hiệu suất.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>30. a comparison between the mirror neurons of human beings and primates</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: C</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) &#8220;They point out that mirror neurons are activated when a <strong>primate</strong> performs a particular action&#8230; <strong>Humans possess an even more intricate</strong> mitor neuron system that reflects the external world in our brains&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>31. mention of integrating visual and motor processes to understand athletic movements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: E</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) &#8220;They asserted that to comprehend the movements of sports stars, we need to <strong>align the visual representation of the observed action with our own motor representation</strong> of the same action.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>32. reference to the first discovery of brain activity associated with mirror neurons</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: D</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) &#8220;This neural mirroring was <strong>initially identified in 1954</strong> by French physiologists Gastaut and Bert, who noticed specific alpha and mu brain wave patterns in humans.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a122ac7e-277c-4324-9295-dace150267ca', '7b6b1330-0948-4b80-a769-acd09500a075', 'radio', 'Questions 33–35', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A They meticulously plan each phase of their movements."}, {"content": "B They engage in regular practice to retain and refine their skills"}, {"content": "C They actively consider and analyse the actions of their peers"}, {"content": "D They perform their actions without conscious contemplation"}], "question": "What point does the writer make about professional athletes in Paragraph B?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A the critical role of imitation in the formation of consciousness"}, {"content": "B the improvement of sporting ability through watching sport."}, {"content": "C the stimulation of a resonance in the observer''s motor system"}, {"content": "D the motivation of the observer''s interest and love for golf."}], "question": "In this passage, the writer mentions the example of a remarkable golfer to illustrate"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A to improve our physical ability by analyzing the athletes’ technical strategies"}, {"content": "B to unite viewers from different nations"}, {"content": "C to experience intense positive emotions by immersing oneself in sport"}, {"content": "D to become a sports professional."}], "question": "The principal motivation for watching sport mentioned by the writer is"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>33. What point does the writer make about professional athletes in Paragraph B?</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: D. They perform their actions without conscious contemplation.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) &#8220;Experts, by contrast, instinctively execute perfectly balanced movements&#8230; Their swing occurs with the serenity of a refined autopilot, <strong>requiring no conscious control</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>34. In this passage, the writer mentions the example of a remarkable golfer to illustrate</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: B. the improvement of sporting ability through watching sport.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) &#8220;It turns out that <strong>watching a remarkable golfer improves our own golfing skills</strong>, and witnessing a skilled sprinter actually bolsters our running speed.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>35. the principal motivation for watching sport mentioned by the writer is</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: C. to experience intense positive emotions by immersing oneself in sport.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) &#8220;Most spectators tune in for the <strong>emotional roller coaster</strong>&#8230; which allow spectators to perceive athletes&#8217; victorious movements and to <strong>share in the emotion of their triumphs</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bdc40b68-13ee-4338-ba92-d45176a266ab', '7b5d9ec7-98de-4b42-89c7-21b9fcef3fe4', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–7', '<p data-start="116" data-end="180">Complete the table below</p>
