<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="116" data-end="180"> </p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1: PRESTON COMMUNITY CENTRE CLASSES</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Hello, this is Preston Community Centre.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> Oh hello. My name is Andrew Shepherd. I’m ringing about the classes you offer.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Okay Mister Shepherd. Are there any classes in particular that you’re interested in?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> Yes, you’ve got a class called Photography, I believe?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> That’s right. It’s the first time we offer this class because many people inquired about it last term. It’ll be held in a library, not far from our community center.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> Right. I know it’s on the weekend, right?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Yes, it’s on Saturday, and it will occupy the whole <strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">(1) morning</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> Okay, um… what do I need to bring?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Obviously, you have to bring your own camera. Some people bring a lot of accessories, like an extra lens, but there’s really no need for this class. It’s mainly focusing on composition really, and getting the most out of the basic camera.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> That’s exactly what I want. Okay then, I’ve heard there’s a class on cooking, right?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Yes, it’s called <strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">(2) French</strong> Cooking class. As the name suggests, it will teach you cooking skills in French cuisine.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> Oh great. Where will that be held?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> This class is special, so we arrange it in a kitchen where we can get the necessary cooking equipment. Let me see… yes, the Anita Kitchen. As for the time of the course, it used to be on the second Tuesday of every month, but there’s a small adjustment this time. Although it’s still held on a monthly basis, the exact time will be changed to the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"356\">(3) first</strong> Tuesday.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> Well actually, it’s my wife who’s really interested, and I think it’s a good fit for her because our daughter has to take a guitar lesson every Tuesday, so my wife is available.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> That’s good. But I have to remind you that aprons are not provided in this class, so when you do come, please bring one with you in case you get dirty when cooking. What’s more, don’t forget to bring some <strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"212\">(4) money</strong> with you, as the ingredients for cooking, like vegetables or meat, have to be paid by yourself.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> Okay, useful information to know. Then, there’s another class that my wife would like to join. That’s the beading class.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Oh, I’ve taken the class myself. The tutor is excellent. Last term it was held in a tennis club, which is going to be redecorated soon, so we plan to change this class to a <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"180\">(5) golf</strong> club this time. And it’ll be held on the evening of every Wednesday.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> Do I have to bring the beads with me?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Yes, that’s the only material needed for this class.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> Okay, I think this class is also a good choice for her. Um, do you have any other classes that I can join?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> If you like, I think you can take our <strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">(6) painting</strong> class. It’s a popular class, so this term we’re going to move it to a high school so that we can get more room.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> What time will it be?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> It’ll be on every Monday evening.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> The time’s good for me. Do I have to bring the paints?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Well, paints will be provided by the tutor. I know that… um, the information says you’ll just need some <strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">(7) brushes</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> I see.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">DETAILS OF BEADING CLASS (Questions 8–10)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> Okay, just another question about the beading class. I’ve just remembered my wife asked me to find out the exact time. When will the first class begin?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Well, the deadline for registration is April the 30th, and we’re not going to start the class until <strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">(8) 15 May</strong> (or May 15th).</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> OK. What’s the fee for this class?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> It was $95 last term, but the cost will be a little more this term. Well, let me check the details… okay, it’ll be $100 this term.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> Just $5 more sounds reasonable. Then about the location… it’s in the club, which room exactly?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Room <strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">(9) J52</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> Okay, just one more question. Is parking convenient?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> I’m sorry to tell you that parking space is only available for the club’s premiere members. But if you drive, there’s a parking lot opposite the club, just beside the <strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"174\">(10) station</strong>. You need to pay only a small parking fee.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"39\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"39\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Andrew:</strong> Okay, that’s all I want to know. I’ll call you later after I discuss it with my wife. Thank you very much.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"40\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"40\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> You’re welcome. Bye bye.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('dfba1cbd-7850-4008-a434-212749347507', '33d01a2c-0245-4828-8e45-e33a00c2a07f', 'matrix', 'Questions 14–18', NULL, '<p>Look at the following statements (Questions 14-18) and the list of people below.</p>
<p>Match each statement with the correct person, <strong>A-D</strong>.</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A-D</strong>, in boxes 14-18.</p>
<p><strong>NB </strong>You may use any letter more than once.</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of people", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "High-level workers tend to react positively to stress.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Stress levels are increased by trying to please customers.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Support from other workers may relieve stress.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Lack of independence at work is often responsible for stress.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Workers commonly expect their workloads to lessen over time.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Neil Plumridge", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Gal Zauberman and John Lynch", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Jan Elsner", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Tony LaMontagne", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"5\">14. High-level workers tend to react positively to stress.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “Jan Elsner, a psychologist who specialises in executive coaching, says that <strong>doing well on a demanding workload is typical of senior executives</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Jan Elsner nói rằng việc <strong>làm tốt công việc với khối lượng đòi hỏi cao là điển hình của các giám đốc điều hành cấp cao</strong> (<em>senior executives</em>), cho thấy họ có xu hướng phản ứng tích cực (<em>react positively</em>) với áp lực công việc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"8\">15. Stress levels are increased by trying to please customers.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “‘I’ll <strong>promise a client that I’ll do something tomorrow</strong>, and then I’ll promise another client that I’ll do the same thing, when I know it’s not going to happen.’”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Neil Plumridge mô tả việc hứa hẹn với khách hàng (<em>promise a client</em>) những điều không thực tế đã gây ra căng thẳng cho chính anh ấy, điều này phù hợp với việc cố gắng làm hài lòng khách hàng (<em>trying to please customers</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"11\">16. Support from other workers may relieve stress.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “He also <strong>relies on the advice of colleagues</strong>, saying that his peers coach each other on business problems: ‘Just a fresh pair of eyes over an issue can help,’ he states.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Neil Plumridge <strong>dựa vào lời khuyên của đồng nghiệp</strong> (<em>relies on the advice of colleagues</em>), cho thấy sự hỗ trợ từ đồng nghiệp có thể giúp giảm căng thẳng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"14\">17. Lack of independence at work is often responsible for stress.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>D</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn H) “His recent research shows that the <strong>major predictor of stress is the level of job control a person has</strong>… The worst jobs combine challenging work and <strong>low control</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tony LaMontagne nói rằng yếu tố dự báo chính gây căng thẳng là mức độ kiểm soát công việc (<em>job control</em>). Công việc có <strong>ít kiểm soát</strong> (<em>low control</em>) hay thiếu tự chủ (<em>lack of independence</em>) là nguyên nhân chính gây ra căng thẳng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"17\">18. Workers commonly expect their workloads to lessen over time.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “A study in the JOURNAL OF EXPERIMENTAL PSYCHOLOGY shows that <strong>people always believe that they will be less busy in the future</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nghiên cứu của Gal Zauberman và John Lynch chỉ ra rằng mọi người luôn tin rằng họ sẽ <strong>ít bận rộn hơn trong tương lai</strong> (<em>less busy in the future</em>), tức là họ kỳ vọng khối lượng công việc sẽ giảm bớt theo thời gian.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('383b2484-4721-4ea4-89fb-105e60397610', '33d01a2c-0245-4828-8e45-e33a00c2a07f', 'radio', 'Questions 19–21', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "an inability to keep to his schedule"}, {"content": "inattention to family celebrations"}, {"content": "a lack of concentration on a task"}, {"content": "a period of insufficient sleep"}], "question": "Which of the following is NOT mentioned by Neil Plumridge as an indication that his workload is too heavy?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "rethinking ideas of what can be achieved"}, {"content": "extending the deadline for completing the task"}, {"content": "using more workers on a project"}, {"content": "taking more time off for sport or other recreation"}], "question": "Which method of lessening work stress is NOT suggested by Neil Plumridge?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "taking a worker''s mind off his troubles."}, {"content": "changing physical response to stress."}, {"content": "resting more effectively."}, {"content": "encouraging executives to take breaks."}], "question": "According to Jan Elsner, meditation offers a method of"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">19. Which of the following is NOT mentioned by Neil Plumridge as an indication that his workload is too heavy?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C. A lack of concentration on a task</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) Plumridge đề cập đến ba dấu hiệu: <strong>ngủ</strong> (<em>sleep</em> – less than six hours’ sleep), <strong>sắp xếp lịch trình</strong> (<em>scheduling</em> – having to reschedule appointments), và <strong>gia đình</strong> (<em>family</em> – misses a family birthday or anniversary).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cả A (reschedule), B (misses family), và D (insufficient sleep) đều được nhắc đến. <strong>Thiếu tập trung</strong> (<em>lack of concentration</em>) <strong>không</strong> nằm trong ba dấu hiệu cảnh báo của anh ấy.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">20. Which method of lessening work stress is NOT suggested by Neil Plumridge?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>D. taking more time off for sport or other recreation</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) Plumridge nói về việc <strong>tái đánh giá khối lượng công việc</strong> (<em>reassess workloads</em>): “allocating extra staff to a job,” “allowing more time,” or “changing expectations.” Anh ấy cũng nói về việc nhờ đồng nghiệp hỗ trợ.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Anh ấy đề xuất A (changing expectations), B (allowing more time), và C (allocating extra staff). Anh ấy <strong>không</strong> đề xuất các hoạt động thư giãn vật lý như chơi thể thao (<em>sport or other recreation</em>). Thực tế, Đoạn E mở đầu bằng việc các chuyên gia nói rằng <strong>chìa khóa không phải là tập trung vào thư giãn</strong> (<em>relief</em> – a game of golf or a massage).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">21. According to Jan Elsner, meditation offers a method of:</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B. changing physical response to stress</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “She points to research showing that meditation can <strong>alter the biochemistry of the brain and the way that brains and bodies react to stress</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Thiền định có thể thay đổi hóa sinh của não và cách cơ thể phản ứng với căng thẳng, điều này đồng nghĩa với việc <strong>thay đổi phản ứng vật lý</strong> (<em>changing physical response</em>) đối với căng thẳng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('22986522-1e7a-4aa7-9089-f7408148ac9a', '33d01a2c-0245-4828-8e45-e33a00c2a07f', 'fillup', 'Questions 22–26', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p class="quests-inner-desc">Complete the summary below.</p>
<p class="quests-inner-desc">Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p class="quests-inner-desc" style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Stress: its effects and how to reduce it</strong></span></p>
<p class="quests-inner-desc">Statistics on workers’ compensation show that people take more time off work due to stress than for any other {injury} at work. On average, workers who take time off because of stress stay away for {16.6 weeks} . This absence comes at a high price – while the number of insurance claims due to stress amount to only {7% | seven percent | 7 percent} of the total, they account for a much higher proportion of the cost of claims payments.Experts believe that seeking to relieve stress through physical therapies such as sport or {massage} may be less effective than simply reviewing your {workloads} .</p>
</div>
</div>
', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">22. Statistics on workers’ compensation show that people take more time off work due to stress than for <strong>any workplace injury</strong>.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>injury</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “Figures for National Workers’ Compensation… show that stress causes the <strong>most lost time of any workplace injury</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Căng thẳng gây ra số ngày nghỉ việc nhiều nhất so với <strong>bất kỳ chấn thương nơi làm việc nào khác</strong> (<em>any workplace injury</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">23. On average, workers who take time off because of stress stay away for <strong>16.6 weeks</strong>.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>16.6 weeks</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “…employees suffering stress are absent from work for an average of <strong>16.6 weeks</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Trung bình, nhân viên nghỉ làm vì căng thẳng trong <strong>16.6 tuần</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\">24. …the number of insurance claims due to stress amount to only <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>7%</strong> of the total, they account for a much higher proportion of the cost of claims payments.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>7%</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “…claims for stress-related psychological injury accounted for <strong>7% of insurance claims</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các khiếu nại liên quan đến căng thẳng chiếm <strong>7%</strong> tổng số yêu cầu bảo hiểm.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\">25. Experts believe that seeking to relieve stress through physical therapies such as sport or <strong>a massage</strong> may be less effective…</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>a massage</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “Experts say the key to dealing with stress is not to focus on relief – a game of golf or <strong>a massage</strong> – but to reassess workloads.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các chuyên gia cho rằng việc tìm kiếm sự giảm căng thẳng thông qua các liệu pháp vật lý như thể thao hoặc <strong>mát-xa</strong> (<em>a massage</em>) có thể kém hiệu quả.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\">26. …than simply reviewing your <strong>workloads</strong>.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>workloads</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “…but to reassess <strong>workloads</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Điều quan trọng là <strong>đánh giá lại khối lượng công việc</strong> (<em>reassessing your workloads</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b1f76435-4fc7-4711-b114-cce518f4c2f6', 'b0da8e59-9788-4261-ba04-170f83eae054', 'matching', ' Questions 27–32', NULL, '<p>Complete the summary below using the list of words, <strong>A-K</strong>, below.</p>', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Provine’s early findings on yawns</strong></p>\n<p>Through his observation of yawns, Province was able to confirm that {K Half-yawns} do not exist.</p>\n<p>Just like a {H sneeze}, yawns cannot be interrupted after they have begun. This is because yawns occur as a {D fixed action pattern} rather than a stimulus response as was previously thought.</p>\n<p>In measuring the time taken to yawn, provine found that a typical yawn lasts about {J 6 seconds} He also found that it is a common for people to yawn a number of times in quick succession with the yawns usually being around {E 68 seconds} apart. When studying whether length and rate were connected. Province concluded that people who yawn less do not necessarily produce {B long yawns} to make up for this.</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A form and function"}, {"optionText": "B long yawns"}, {"optionText": "C 3 seconds"}, {"optionText": "D fixed action pattern"}, {"optionText": "E 68 seconds"}, {"optionText": "F short yawns"}, {"optionText": "G reflex"}, {"optionText": "H sneeze"}, {"optionText": "I short duration"}, {"optionText": "J 6 seconds"}, {"optionText": "K Half-yawns"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. Provine was able to confirm that {K: half-yawns} do not exist.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “There are no <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">half-yawns</strong>: this is an example of the typical intensity of fixed action patterns…” (Đoạn 4).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định không tồn tại cái gọi là “ngáp một nửa” vì đây là một mô hình hành động cố định.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. Just like a {H: sneeze}, yawns cannot be interrupted after they have begun.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…but, once started, a yawn progresses with the inevitability of a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">sneeze</strong>.” (Đoạn 4).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một khi đã bắt đầu, cơn ngáp sẽ diễn ra cho đến hết, giống hệt như một cái <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">hắt hơi (sneeze)</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. This is because yawns occur as a {D: fixed action pattern} rather than a stimulus response.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “It is an excellent example of the instinctive <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">‘fixed action pattern’</strong>… It is not a reflex…” (Đoạn 4).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc phân biệt ngáp không phải là phản xạ (reflex) mà là một <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">mô hình hành động cố định (fixed action pattern)</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. Provine found that a typical yawn lasts about {J: 6 seconds}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The standard yawn runs its course over about <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">six seconds</strong> on average…” (Đoạn 4).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. …yawn a number of times in quick succession with the yawns usually being around {E: 68 seconds} apart.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…which is generally about <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">68 seconds</strong> but rarely more than 70.” (Đoạn 4).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các cơn ngáp thường đến theo đợt và cách nhau khoảng 68 giây.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. …people who yawn less do not necessarily produce {B: long yawns} to make up for this.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “There is no relation between yawn frequency and duration: producers of short or long yawns <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"103\">do not compensate</strong> by yawning more or less often.” (Đoạn 4).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Người ngáp ít không nhất thiết phải ngáp những cái <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">ngáp dài (long yawns)</strong> để bù đắp (make up for/compensate).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('48d06fd4-c1aa-4a12-b427-120cf6d3dc29', 'b0da8e59-9788-4261-ba04-170f83eae054', 'radio', 'Questions 33–37', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "Ending a yawn requires use of the nostrils."}, {"content": "You can yawn without breathing through your nose."}, {"content": "Breathing through the nose produces a silent yawn."}, {"content": "The role of the nose in yawning needs further investigation."}], "question": "What did Provine conclude from his ‘closed nose yawn’ experiment?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "Yawning is unconnected with fatigue."}, {"content": "A yawn is the equivalent of a deep intake of breath."}, {"content": "You have to be able to open your mouth wide to yawn."}, {"content": "Breathing with the teeth together is as efficient as through the nose."}], "question": "Provine’s clenched teeth yawn’s experiment shows that"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "Can be stopped after it has stated."}, {"content": "Is the result of motor programing."}, {"content": "Involves both inhalation and exhalation."}, {"content": "Can be accomplished only through the nose."}], "question": "The nose yawn experiment was used to test whether yawning"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "Yawning may involve only one side of the face."}, {"content": "The yawing response indicates that recovery is likely."}, {"content": "Movement in paralysed arm is stimulated by yawning."}, {"content": "Yawning can be used as an example to prevent muscle wasting."}], "question": "In people paralyzed on one side because of brain damage"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "Yawning is a sign of boredom."}, {"content": "We yawn is spite of the development of our species."}, {"content": "Yawning is a more passive activity than we Imagine."}, {"content": "We are stimulated to yawn when our brain activity is low."}], "question": "In the last paragraph, the writer concludes that"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. What did Provine conclude from his ‘closed nose yawn’ experiment?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong><span class=\"\"> You can yawn without breathing through your nose.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">i) The closed nose yawn</strong><span class=\"\">:</span><span class=\"\"> &#8220;This indicates that the inhalation&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> and the exhalation&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> need not involve the nostrils – the mouth provides a sufficient airway.</span><span class=\"\">&#8220;</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Khi bịt mũi,</span><span class=\"\"> người tham gia vẫn ngáp bình thường được vì miệng đã cung cấp đủ đường thở.</span><span class=\"\"> Điều này chứng minh mũi không đóng vai trò bắt buộc trong cơ chế của cơn ngáp.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Provine’s clenched teeth yawn experiment shows that</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong><span class=\"\"> You have to be able to open your mouth wide to yawn.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">ii) The clenched teeth yawn</strong><span class=\"\">:</span><span class=\"\"> &#8220;This shows that gaping of the jaws is an essential component&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> and unless it is accomplished,</span><span class=\"\"> the program will not run to completion.</span><span class=\"\">&#8220;</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Việc cắn chặt răng khiến người ta cảm thấy bị &#8220;kẹt&#8221; giữa chừng.</span><span class=\"\"> Do đó,</span><span class=\"\"> việc há rộng hàm (gaping of the jaws) là điều kiện cần để hoàn thành một cơn ngáp trọn vẹn.</span></p>\n<p class=\"attachment-container search-images\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<div class=\"image-container ng-star-inserted\">\n<div class=\"overlay-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<div class=\"placeholder loading ng-star-inserted\"> </div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. The nose yawn experiment was used to test whether yawning</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án của bạn:</strong><span class=\"\"> Is the result of motor programming.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đánh giá:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đáp án này </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">Đúng</strong><span class=\"\"> về mặt bản chất khoa học nhưng cần giải thích rõ hơn dựa trên văn bản.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">iii) The nose yawn</strong><span class=\"\">:</span><span class=\"\"> &#8220;The motor program for yawning will not run to completion without feedback that these parts of the program [inhalation through oral airway and gaping of jaws] have been accomplished.</span><span class=\"\">&#8220;</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,3,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Thí nghiệm này cho thấy não bộ có một &#8220;chương trình vận động&#8221; (motor program) cài sẵn.</span><span class=\"\"> Nếu chỉ hít vào bằng mũi mà không qua miệng,</span><span class=\"\"> não không nhận được tín hiệu phản hồi rằng &#8220;các bước đã hoàn thành&#8221;,</span><span class=\"\"> dẫn đến việc cơn ngáp không thể kết thúc.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. In people paralyzed on one side because of brain damage</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong><span class=\"\"> Movement in paralysed arm is stimulated by yawning.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn gần cuối:</span><span class=\"\"> &#8220;&#8230;</span><span class=\"\">when these people yawn,</span><span class=\"\"> they are startled&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> to observe that their otherwise paralyzed arm rises and flexes automatically in what neurologists term an ‘associated response’.</span><span class=\"\">&#8220;</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Khi ngáp,</span><span class=\"\"> các kết nối vô thức giữa não và hệ vận động (không bị tổn thương bởi đột quỵ) được kích hoạt,</span><span class=\"\"> khiến cánh tay bị liệt tự động cử động mà người bệnh không tự điều khiển được.</span></p>\n<p class=\"attachment-container search-images\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<div class=\"image-container ng-star-inserted\">\n<div class=\"overlay-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<div class=\"placeholder loading ng-star-inserted\"> </div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. In the last paragraph, the writer concludes that</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án của bạn:</strong> We are stimulated to yawn when our brain activity is low.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đánh giá: Cần lưu ý.</strong> Trong đoạn cuối của văn bản bạn cung cấp, tác giả không nói trực tiếp đến &#8220;brain activity is low&#8221;.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn cuối: &#8220;Yawning appears to be associated with a <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">change of behavioral state</strong>, switching from one activity to another.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả kết luận ngáp liên quan đến việc <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">thay đổi trạng thái hành vi</strong> (như từ làm việc sang nghỉ ngơi, hoặc ngược lại). Ngoài ra, nó là một hành vi &#8220;cổ xưa và vô thức&#8221; (ancient and unconscious behavior) kết nối con người với thế giới động vật.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a2a41e83-e493-48f2-9cf1-276de6a26828', 'e65347b9-00b3-4550-8626-5cd8621436ea', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–10', '<p>Complete the table below.<br>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Asia-Pacific Tours Activity Holidays</strong></p>
<table class="MsoNormalTable" style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; width: 80.0063%; height: 212.177px;" border="1" cellpadding="0">
<thead>
<tr style="height: 22.9271px;">
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 13.2981%;">
<p><strong>Tour</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 70.6899%;">
<p><strong>Details</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 15.9227%;">
<p><strong>Cost</strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 42.0938px;">
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 13.2981%;">
<p><strong>Example</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 70.6899%;">
<p>• a cookery course at a 5-star hotel</p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 15.9227%;"> </td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 42.5208px;">
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 13.2981%;">
<p><strong>Vietnam</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 70.6899%;">
<p>• either {diving} lessons or a one-day trek in the {jungle}</p>
<p>• attend a {dance} performance</p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 15.9227%;">
<p>£ {1450|1,450}</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 62.1146px;">
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 13.2981%;">
<p><strong>Hong Kong</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 70.6899%;">
<p>• go to the hills to look at {birds} in a country park</p>
<p>• followed by {dinner} in a monastery</p>
<p>• visit an {electronics} factory with the chance to shop</p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 15.9227%;">
<p>£1,320</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 42.5208px;">
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 13.2981%;">
<p><strong> {Japan}</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 70.6899%;">
<p>• visit a museum of traditional {costume}</p>
<p>• tour of a big {fish } market</p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 15.9227%;">
<p>£1,800</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 1: ASIA-PACIFIC TOURS ACTIVITY HOLIDAYS</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">Agent:</strong> Asia Pacific tours can I help you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">Woman:</strong> Yes, I’ve been looking at your website and I’d like some more information about your activity holidays.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"161\">Agent:</strong> Certainly. You know of course the prices of the tours include stays in 3 star hotels and they include airfares.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"280\">Woman:</strong> Great. What about your tour of <strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"318\">Vietnam</strong>? My sister went there last year and loved it.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Yes, it’s a really beautiful place and probably our fastest growing destination. Now that package includes several opportunities to take courses.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Don’t you have a cookery course of some kind?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> We certainly do. If you love eating out in Vietnam, like most people do, and want to know how to prepare a meal, you can learn how from a master in a 5 star hotel. On another day you have a choice of two activities.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">The first is instruction in <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">(1) diving</strong></span> in the South China Sea. Not a certificate course but just an introduction. Most people think it’s wonderful.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">Or if you want to stay dry but still want some exercise, you can spend the day on a trek through the <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">(2) jungle</strong></span> near the beach. It’s not difficult and everyone seems to enjoy it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Anything cultural on offer?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> We used to take people to a Vietnamese opera, but that didn’t prove so popular.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">So now we include a <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">(3) dance</strong></span> show, and our clients all rave about that. They say the colours are just magnificent.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Hmm, what’s the cost?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> I’ve just noticed it’s now a special price. The holiday used to be £1,600,</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\">but it’s just been reduced to £<span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">(4) 1,450</strong></span>. So you do save quite a bit. And as I said, it seems to be our up and coming tour.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Well, let’s see. Perhaps you could tell me a little about the Hong Kong tour. I noticed it includes a walk in the hills of one of their country parks where you have the chance to see<span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"190\">(5) birds</strong> </span>of all sorts.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Yes, that’s a very popular activity. People don’t realize that Hong Kong isn’t just a crowded city. That’s a half day activity, and you go with a trained escort.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\">And it includes <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">(6) dinner</strong></span> in a monastery where you end your day.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\">And then, we wouldn’t want you to miss out altogether on shopping, so there’s another day</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\">when we take you round an <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">(7) electronics</strong></span> factory. Now that might sound like an odd thing to do, but it’s actually really fascinating, and not like your usual ceramics factory. And you can buy their products there quite cheaply.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\">Now, the whole Hong Kong package is just £1,320 per person.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">(Questions 8-10)</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Sounds interesting.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong>But let me find out about one more place. I’ve always wanted to go to Korea, but not on this trip and I’ve been to Thailand which I loved,</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\">but what about your <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">(8) Japan</strong></span> package?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Good choice. Well, that tour includes a terrific trip to a museum of traditional <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">(9) costume</strong></span>. The exhibits are gorgeous. They’ve got an absolutely priceless collection.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> And I think the website says you take your clients to a market, don’t you? A crafts market, I think.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Well, we do go to a market but it’s one that sells <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">(10) fish</strong></span>, and it’s one of the largest in the world.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\">And you have the chance to sample the wares in a little restaurant nearby. We also give you plenty of free time to wander around the city with our guides if you want.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> And what’s the cost of all that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> £1,800.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Well you’ve been ever so helpful. I’ve noted all the details down and I’ll get back to you when I’ve made up my mind.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> If we can give you any more help, do ring back.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Thanks, I will.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('02110ddf-1fe7-4929-bb0b-47b5e0fac747', 'd99087c2-5edf-4d31-9c1a-e869b405820d', 'matching', 'Questions 35–39', '', '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, <strong>A–H</strong>, below.</p>', 'matching_name', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "accepting that literature exists in a variety of forms today."}, {"optionText": "verbalising the words in their heads."}, {"optionText": "discovering the reading techniques used by others."}, {"optionText": "the style of written stories changing over time."}, {"optionText": "the lack of some specific abilities."}, {"optionText": "a deeper knowledge of the intricacies of reading."}, {"optionText": "children teaching adults to play computer games."}, {"optionText": "creating a variety of images in their minds."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Young people’s accounts of how they read lead to", "correctAnswer": "F"}, {"questionPart": "The risk of solipsism is reduced by", "correctAnswer": "C"}, {"questionPart": "Strong visualisers judge books on the basis that they are", "correctAnswer": "H"}, {"questionPart": "Children’s insights are important in", "correctAnswer": "A"}, {"questionPart": "When adults read a book more easily than they play a digital game, it simply suggests", "correctAnswer": "E"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. Young people’s accounts of how they read lead to: F (a deeper knowledge of the intricacies of reading)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Young people’s accounts… enable a <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">more sophisticated description</strong> of many of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">complex processes</strong> involved in reading.” (Đoạn 9)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Lời kể của trẻ em giúp tạo ra mô tả tinh vi (sophisticated) về các quy trình phức tạp (complex processes), tương ứng với “kiến thức sâu hơn về những sự phức tạp” (deeper knowledge of the intricacies).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. The risk of solipsism is reduced by: C (discovering the reading techniques used by others)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Asking other readers how they read, however, <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">reduces that risk [of solipsism]</strong>.” (Đoạn 9)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Solipsism” là việc áp đặt cách đọc của mình lên người khác. Để giảm rủi ro này, tác giả khuyên nên hỏi (khám phá) cách người khác đọc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. Strong visualisers judge books on the basis that they are: H (creating a variety of images in their minds)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…if I am a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">strong visualizer</strong>… I may judge books by their capacity to <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">evoke a vivid visual response</strong>.” (Đoạn 9)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những người có khả năng hình dung tốt sẽ đánh giá sách dựa trên việc sách đó có gợi lên được những hình ảnh sống động trong đầu họ hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. Children’s insights are important in: A (accepting that literature exists in a variety of forms today)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Children’s insights are even more important… understanding the significance of print literature as <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">one aspect of literary culture</strong>.” (Đoạn 11)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trẻ em coi sách chỉ là một phần của hệ sinh thái gồm cả game, phim. Nhận thức này giúp người lớn chấp nhận văn học có nhiều hình thức khác nhau (variety of forms).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. When adults read a book more easily than they play a digital game, it simply suggests: E (the lack of some specific abilities)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…This does not indicate that a book is better, but that <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">a particular set of skills is absent</strong>.” (Đoạn 11)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc người lớn không chơi game thạo bằng đọc sách chỉ đơn giản là họ thiếu đi một bộ kỹ năng cụ thể (absent skills/lack of abilities), chứ không phải game kém giá trị hơn sách.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a176ed04-e3ed-4cd9-9350-3c66cef4a5ba', 'd99087c2-5edf-4d31-9c1a-e869b405820d', 'radio', 'Question 40', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter <strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="26">A, B, C</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="37">D</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A to evaluate how the process of reading fits into children’s literature studies"}, {"option_text": "B to discuss the impact of the increasing commercial influence on children’s literature studies"}, {"option_text": "C to review the challenges in the field of children’s literature studies and suggest how to proceed"}, {"option_text": "D to provide arguments in favor of including computerized forms in children’s literature studies"}], "question": "What was the writer’s main purpose in writing this article?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. What was the writer’s main purpose in writing this article?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">C (to review the challenges in the field of children’s literature studies and suggest how to proceed)</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15,1,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Review the challenges:</strong> Tác giả liệt kê hàng loạt khó khăn như: sự áp đặt của người lớn, tính giáo huấn (didactic), áp lực thương mại, sự cạnh tranh của truyền thông mới và sự phân mảnh trong ngành học.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Suggest how to proceed:</strong> Tác giả đưa ra giải pháp ở các đoạn cuối: Hãy lắng nghe độc giả trẻ em để hiểu thấu đáo bản chất việc đọc và đánh giá công bằng các loại hình giải trí mới (như game).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1ddc2716-f274-475a-8dbb-e915364612cf', '6d435446-b99b-409d-822b-3b2bc9a7a34e', 'matching', 'Questions 25–30', '', '<p>What criticism is made of each of the following technical aspect of Ron’s presentation?<br data-start="1026" data-end="1029">Choose <strong>SIX </strong>correct answers, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>H</strong></p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Technical aspects of presentation</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>speed of delivery {too irregular}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>purpose {too vague}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>transitions {too sudden}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>visuals {too loosely related}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>vocabulary {too technical}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>body language {too unenthusiastic}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "too informal"}, {"optionText": "too irregular"}, {"optionText": "too predictable"}, {"optionText": "too sudden"}, {"optionText": "too technical"}, {"optionText": "too unenthusiastic"}, {"optionText": "too loosely related"}, {"optionText": "too vague"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2338ba3b-96da-45b6-aa15-f10787cd3265', '01ca7db3-7e31-49b4-818c-ed95abaa4f62', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<p data-start="101" data-end="169">Complete the note below.</p>
<p data-start="101" data-end="169">Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="171" data-end="207"><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Using natural building materials</span></strong></p>
<p data-start="209" data-end="300">With all methods of building using natural materials, a good {foundation} is needed</p>
<h3 data-start="307" data-end="325">Rammed earth</h3>
<p>• A framework made from wood filled with soil<br data-start="371" data-end="374">• The best soil has large quantities of {sand}</p>
<h3 data-start="439" data-end="462">Adobe (mud brick)</h3>
<p data-start="463" data-end="542">• The most suitable soil for adobe bricks contains lots of {clay}</p>
<p data-start="544" data-end="556">Advantages</p>
<ul data-start="557" data-end="646">
<li data-start="557" data-end="589">
<p data-start="559" data-end="589">cheap and {convenient}</p>
</li>
<li data-start="590" data-end="646">
<p data-start="592" data-end="646">little {training} is needed for brick-making</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="648" data-end="662">Disadvantage</p>
<ul data-start="663" data-end="723">
<li data-start="663" data-end="723">
<p data-start="665" data-end="723">a lot of water, time and {labour} are required</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="730" data-end="747">Straw bales</h3>
<p data-start="748" data-end="927">• Bales – large rectangular blocks of straw</p>
<p data-start="748" data-end="927">• A {roof} needs to be constructed first</p>
<p data-start="748" data-end="927">• The bales are covered with plaster for protection against {insects}</p>
<p data-start="929" data-end="940">Advantage</p>
<ul data-start="941" data-end="982">
<li data-start="941" data-end="982">
<p data-start="943" data-end="982">the bales act as efficient insulation</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="989" data-end="1001">Bamboo</h3>
<p data-start="1002" data-end="1034">• This is a versatile material</p>
<p data-start="1036" data-end="1047">Advantage</p>
<ul data-start="1048" data-end="1112">
<li data-start="1048" data-end="1112">
<p data-start="1050" data-end="1112">the shape of the bamboo stalks gives them {strength}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1114" data-end="1129">Disadvantages</p>
<ul data-start="1130" data-end="1183">
<li data-start="1130" data-end="1154">
<p data-start="1132" data-end="1154">not widely available</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1155" data-end="1183">
<p data-start="1157" data-end="1183">risk of {fire}</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 4: NATURAL BUILDING MATERIALS</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> There is growing interest in building structures using natural materials these days. I’ll begin this lecture by looking at how some of these materials work, some advantages and problems associated with each.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">However, I must start by saying that all these materials and construction techniques require, first and foremost, a solid <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">(31) foundation</strong></span>, which will most often need to be made of concrete. Thus the goal of using 100% natural materials may have to be slightly compromised.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"5\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">RAMMED EARTH</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> One type of natural building material is what is known as rammed earth. Rammed earth is a construction method whereby a framework constructed of wood is set in place to act as temporary walls, and then damp earth or soil is placed within this framework. As it is added, the earth is packed down and subjected to intense compression, either by hand or by using specialized machinery.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">Across parts of Africa today, you can see military fortifications built in this way over 10,000 years ago still standing in remarkably good condition. The most appropriate type of soil for this construction method is one with a high concentration of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"250\">(32) sand</strong></span> in it, though other kinds of soil are sometimes successfully used. Rammed earth buildings are well suited to dry, arid climates.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"9\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">ADOBE (MUD BRICK)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Another form of natural construction is called the Adobe method, or sometimes the mud brick method. This utilizes bricks which can be made from a variety of soils, but are most suitable when made from a soil rich in <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"226\">(33) clay</strong></span>. The bricks have got to be carefully made to prevent them from cracking.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">The main advantage of this Adobe brick method is that the materials are cheap and also that it’s <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">(34) convenient</strong></span> for people in many geographical areas. Thus, Adobe buildings have been traditional forms of construction in many societies and today can be found all over the world. The construction method is also popular because making the bricks requires minimal <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"362\">(35) training</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">However, the Adobe method does have its drawbacks. For proper preparation of the bricks, large quantities of water are required, and because these bricks are manufactured by hand, the process demands significant investment of time as well as <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"242\">(36) labor</strong></span> (hoặc labour), which can be backbreaking and exhausting.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"14\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">STRAW BALES</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> A natural building material which has been popularized in the US is the use of straw bales to create walls. Straw is, of course, dried stalks of plants, especially tall grasses. The straw is shaped into large rectangular blocks called bales, tightly bound together, and these are excellent for use in the building of walls.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">When building with straw bales, the first thing that needs to be done is to construct a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">(37) roof</strong> </span>supported by poles so that work can continue even if it rains. Then the straw bales are stacked up to form walls. The bales are then coated with a layer of plaster which seals and protects them and keeps the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"306\">(38) insects</strong></span> out of them. The most common reason for their use in building today is the fact that they provide a very effective means of insulation for the building.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"18\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">BAMBOO</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Another great building material is bamboo. This highly versatile plant is one of the fastest-growing plants in the world. One of its primary advantages is due to the hollow, round, and segmented shape of its individual stalks, which give it its <strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"255\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(39) strength</span></strong>. And because of its lightweight, it is easy to handle.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\">A significant drawback, however, is that the large varieties of bamboo which are best suited for construction grow only in tropical and subtropical regions of the world. And also, because it catches <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"199\">(40) fire</strong></span> easily, bamboo can be problematic and potentially dangerous.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\">Now let’s take a look at possible sources of…</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7b0d5139-6861-4c09-a214-1fdc48eadf4f', 'b0da8e59-9788-4261-ba04-170f83eae054', 'radio', 'Questions 38–40', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES</strong> if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, choose <strong>NO</strong> if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, or <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Research students were initially reluctant to appreciate the value of Provine’s studies."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "When foetuses yawn and stretch they are learning how to control movement."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "According to Provine, referring to only one function is probably inadequate to explain why people yawn."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>38. YES<br />\n(Đoạn 1, “When Robert R. Provine began studying yawning in the 1960s, it was difficult for him to convince research students of the merits of ‘yawning science’.”)<br />\n→ Câu này cho thấy các sinh viên nghiên cứu ban đầu hoài nghi và không đánh giá cao giá trị nghiên cứu về ngáp của Provine. → Đáp án là YES.</p>\n<p>39. NOT GIVEN<br />\n(Đoạn nói về nghiên cứu của J.I.P. deVries về thai nhi: “Studies … observed a link between yawning and stretching.”)<br />\n→ Đoạn này chỉ nói có mối liên hệ giữa ngáp và duỗi người ở thai nhi, nhưng không nói rằng hành động này giúp chúng học cách kiểm soát chuyển động. → Đáp án là NOT GIVEN.</p>\n<p>40. YES<br />\n(Đoạn cuối, “Provine speculated that, in general, yawning may have many functions, and selecting a single function from the available options may be an unrealistic goal.”)<br />\n→ Provine tin rằng chỉ quy việc ngáp về một chức năng duy nhất là không đủ, vì nó có thể phục vụ nhiều mục đích khác nhau. → Đáp án là YES.</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7d7e363b-12ce-4db1-970d-3a849cd1b998', '7b5d9ec7-98de-4b42-89c7-21b9fcef3fe4', 'fillup', 'Questions 8–10', '<p data-start="654" data-end="729">Complete the notes below.</p>
<p data-start="654" data-end="729">Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="731" data-end="760"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Details of Beading Class</strong></span></p>
<ul data-start="762" data-end="900">
<li data-start="762" data-end="806">
<p data-start="764" data-end="806">The first class starts on: {15 May| May 15th}</p>
</li>
<li data-start="807" data-end="834">
<p data-start="809" data-end="834">Cost of the class: $100</p>
</li>
<li data-start="835" data-end="862">
<p data-start="837" data-end="862">Room No.: {J52}</p>
</li>
<li data-start="863" data-end="900">
<p data-start="865" data-end="900">Parking: next to a {station} </p>
</li>
</ul>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('28d49711-3f4a-4e45-bcf3-709bf4e7e43c', '052ea3ed-d3ba-4c07-8824-3a48a4774c27', 'matrix', 'Questions 11–16', NULL, '<p data-start="90" data-end="167">Label the map below.<br data-start="110" data-end="113">Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>I<br></strong></p>
<h3 data-start="169" data-end="188"><img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="686" height="514"></h3>
<p data-start="90" data-end="167"><strong> </strong></p>', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Art books", "correctCategoryLetter": "I"}, {"itemText": "Gardening books", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "History books", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Children''s books", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "Reading area", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "Self-help books", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}, {"categoryText": "I", "categoryLetter": "I"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 2: BOOKSHOP TOUR AND NEW PROMOTIONS</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Good evening everyone, thanks for coming in. This won’t take long. Because we have quite a few new staff members, we thought it would be helpful to call you all in while the shop’s closed to give you a short tour. After the tour, we’ll introduce you to some of the book promotions we have this month.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">Have you all got a copy of the map? Okay, let’s move to the store entrance. I can point out each section to you quite easily from there. There are the two cashiers straight ahead.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">And on our right, close to the wall, is a large area divided into sections to attract students from the art college nearby. We decided to have <strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"143\">(11) art books [I]</strong> at the front of this section.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">In the middle of this large section is the home section. The books here range from design to renovation. And at the back of this section, we have a small selection of <strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"167\">(12) gardening books [H]</strong>. At first, we thought we’d locate it on its own on the other side of the cashiers, but we ultimately decided to have it at the back there, and it’s well signposted.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">Straight ahead and directly behind the cashiers, there’s the magazine and newspaper stand, which is closest to us. Behind this, you can see two sections side by side: <strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"167\">(13) history [D]</strong> on one side and biographies on the other. In our other stores, these sections are usually located at the very back, but sales haven’t been great, so to try to attract more interest, we decided to make them more visible.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">Also within this central area, just behind biographies, we’ve placed our two fiction sections. The <strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">(14) children’s section [G]</strong> is the larger area over on the right, and the adult’s section, the smaller one on the left.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">You’ll see over in the far left-hand corner of the store, we have our coffee shop which has become very popular. Behind this, running right along the back of the store, we’ve introduced a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"188\">(15) reading area [E]</strong>. We’ve added chairs and cushions to create a cosy atmosphere.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">And finally, immediately to the left of the entrance, you’ll see <strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">(16) self-help books [A]</strong>. These are here because we currently have a number of special offers connected with these topics. When the specials are finished, we’ll relocate this section to behind the coffee shop. Okay, I think that’s it. I’ll let you have a browse around in a minute.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">NEW BOOKS (Questions 17–20)</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Next, I’d like to quickly introduce you to some of the new books we have in stock.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">Firstly, Elizabeth Honey’s written a new book called <strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">Penny Pinchers</strong>. It’s a wonderful story set in early Australia, and I thoroughly recommend it. <strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"147\">(17) It includes some beautiful drawings [E – has good illustrations]</strong> based on the artwork of the era.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">Next is <strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">The Running Boy</strong>. It’s about a boy who gets himself into some difficult situations at school. I think Simon Darling, the writer, has done a fantastic job in this <strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"169\">(18) debut book [A – a first-time author]</strong>. He’s currently working on his second novel, a crime story aimed at the adult market.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\">The next book I have here is <strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">The Hidden Code</strong>, which <strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">(19) won several prizes at the last Book Convention [B – an award-winning book]</strong>. Marketed as a book for older children, it deals with realistic problems faced by young people today.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">And finally, my personal favourite, <strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">The Orange Moon</strong>. This is the <strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">(20) final book in a set of novels [F – part of a series]</strong> about the lives of a fictional group of friends living in outback Australia. I hear this is being adapted to a movie suitable for the whole family, which I’m sure will be very popular.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c19bd00c-4334-402a-bbfc-ed0d5737fd37', '052ea3ed-d3ba-4c07-8824-3a48a4774c27', 'matching', 'Questions 17–20', '', '<p data-start="465" data-end="571">What does the speaker say about each new book?<br data-start="511" data-end="514">Choose <strong>FOUR</strong> correct answers, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>F</strong></p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>New books</strong></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Penny Pinchers {has good illustrations}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Running Boy {a first-time author}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Hidden Code {an award-winning book}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Orange Moon {part of a series}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "a first-time author"}, {"optionText": "an award-winning book"}, {"optionText": "a true story"}, {"optionText": "has a sad ending"}, {"optionText": "has good illustrations"}, {"optionText": "part of a series"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('cb14e86c-1911-42c8-a7ad-43cc0b57058e', 'e4c40f58-5c1b-4aaf-af7d-7127832f5e78', 'radio', 'Questions 21–24', NULL, '<p data-start="90" data-end="116">Choose the correct answer.</p>
<p data-start="118" data-end="157"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Bachelor of Communications Degree</span></strong></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "will help him get work in other countries"}, {"content": "has easier courses than the Public Relations major"}, {"content": "could lead to a well-paid job in New Zealand"}], "question": "Simon thinks the Global Communications major"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "too challenging for him"}, {"content": "uninteresting as a subject"}, {"content": "similar to other courses on the major"}], "question": "Simon says that the Economic Principles course was"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "give students a better understanding of the whole major"}, {"content": "are less useful than the courses dealing with culture"}, {"content": "should remain optional to students"}], "question": "Anna thinks that the foreign language courses"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "it was a language she had previously studied"}, {"content": "it would enable her to travel"}, {"content": "it could be useful in commerce"}], "question": "What reason does Anna give for her choice of foreign language?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 3: BACHELOR OF COMMUNICATIONS DISCUSSION</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> Excuse me, are you Anna Jenkins?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Yes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> My name is Simon. I’m on the Bachelor of Communications course, Year 1, and I really need some advice from someone who’s ahead of me. I was told you were in Year 3.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> That’s right. How’s it going?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> Hmm, I’m not convinced I chose the right major. At present, I’m doing Public Relations. That’s why I want to talk to you. You’re doing the Global Communications major, right?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Yes. Are you going to change to that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> Possibly, if it helps my career.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Won’t the Public Relations course do that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> If I just wanted to work in New Zealand, yes. I mean, I’ve heard of graduates finding work here almost immediately and with good salaries. But <strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"150\">(21) I’d like to go abroad, and I imagine the Global major would give me the skills so I could go and work anywhere [Answer: A]</strong>. I know it’ll be hard work starting again, but I would be motivated.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> I see. But I’m still not sure you need to change majors to achieve your goal. Aren’t some of the courses the same for both majors?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> Some are the same, yes. But I’m not sure I’m cut out for the business aspects of Public Relations. Economic Principles, for example. I understand what it’s all about—I did economics at high school—but <strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"208\">(22) I just found it dull [Answer: B – uninteresting]</strong>. I want to study something creative, something that connects you to people.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Well, the Global major certainly does that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> Is it right you have to learn a language?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Well, it was compulsory when I started, but it’s up to you now.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> Do you think it’s necessary to learn one?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Well, so much of the major is looking at ways that culture and language influence communication, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">(23) if you learn a second language yourself, you definitely get more of an insight into what the theory is all about [Answer: A]</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> But I’m no good at languages. Which one is the easiest?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> I’m not sure that’s the best rationale for a choice. In my first year, we could go for Chinese, Japanese or Maori. <strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">(24) I went for Chinese because New Zealand has so many trade deals with China now [Answer: C – commerce]</strong>. But Japanese would be good if you think you might end up in tourism. I did Maori at high school and it was fascinating, but it would restrict you to doing business within New Zealand.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"21\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">LECTURERS AND COURSES (Questions 25–30)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> What did you think of your lectures?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Oh, I have to say they’re great. And when we were working on our individual proposals for the internships, <strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">(25-26) they pushed us to keep working on producing the best work possible [Answer: E – improve]</strong>. And even though I kept having to adapt it, I actually felt proud of mine eventually.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> Yes, ours push us too, which is good. Sometimes you don’t know what you’re capable of, and it makes you a lot more enthusiastic. Sometimes if the lecturer sits down with you for a chat, it’s more motivating than a written report.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> I completely agree. And I suppose one thing I really like is <strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">(25-26) the way they encourage us to challenge their opinions [Answer: A – freedom of thought]</strong>, as long as we can come up with a sound argument to support our case. I think that’s helped me develop some useful critical thinking skills.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> That’s good. I think whatever major you do, all the lecturers want to encourage that. At least, that’s my experience. What did you enjoy most about the Global Communications major?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Well, <strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Communication 1</strong> was really useful. I was never very confident at speaking in front of large groups, but that showed us how to use different voice techniques and <strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"173\">(27) how to give interactive presentations [Answer: D – talking in public]</strong>. I had to give a presentation to some executives during my internship and I did quite well after that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> Sounds interesting.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"6\">Psychology</strong> was absolutely fascinating. You get to look at what motivates people and <strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">(28) how people operate within a big team [Answer: B – working in large groups]</strong>. That’s really essential when you’re trying to get all the people to cooperate on a project that has the pressure of a deadline.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> In the brochure, <strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">Interpersonal Skills</strong> looks good.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> I didn’t do that course.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Simon:</strong> It says it’s about how to listen properly, how to <strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">(29) manage conflict in relationships—you know, when colleagues are arguing [Answer: C – co-workers]</strong>. The first step to improve things is better communication. That’s pretty logical. And this one, <strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"254\">Communication 3</strong>…</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"6\">(30) What kinds of behaviour are likely to cause offence or misunderstanding between nationalities in the global business world [Answer: E – cultural differences]</strong>. Yes, I enjoyed that.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1a185a95-032d-4eae-baab-b3a4b109df48', '55d7a72b-0635-427b-a1e9-7b7972690c1b', 'radio', 'Questions 1–6', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Applicants to the department must have previously studied art history."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Students can choose two optional courses instead of the Theory and Methods course."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The course organisers had more problems collecting art objects from some historical periods than others."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Theory and Methods course focuses on the way art is made and perceived"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Students will be able to do any of the optional courses that are listed."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Students may be able to take an unlisted course if they get the appropriate approval."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"5\">1. Applicants to the department must have previously studied art history.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (General Information) “We welcome applicants from a broad range of backgrounds and <strong>do not require students to have a first degree in art history</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Khóa học không yêu cầu sinh viên phải có bằng cấp đầu tiên về lịch sử nghệ thuật, mâu thuẫn với nhận định rằng họ <em>phải</em> (<em>must</em>) học trước đó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"7\">2. Students can choose two optional courses instead of the Theory and Methods course.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (General Information) “In addition to a <strong>compulsory course on Theory and Methods</strong>, students take <strong>two one-term optional courses</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Khóa học Lý thuyết và Phương pháp (<em>Theory and Methods</em>) là <strong>bắt buộc</strong> (<em>compulsory</em>). Sinh viên phải học khóa này <em>và</em> hai khóa tự chọn, không phải thay thế khóa bắt buộc bằng hai khóa tự chọn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"9\">3. The course organisers had more problems collecting art objects from some historical periods than others.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (General Information) “Images and objects produced in many contexts – ranging from the scientific to the popular – have been brought together to show how visual styles at different periods and in different places can be understood…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói rằng các đối tượng nghệ thuật đã được thu thập từ nhiều bối cảnh và thời kỳ khác nhau, nhưng <strong>không có thông tin</strong> nào nói về <strong>vấn đề</strong> (<em>problems</em>) hay khó khăn trong việc thu thập từ các thời kỳ lịch sử.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"11\">4. The Theory and Methods course focuses on the way art is made and perceived.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Theory and Methods) “The course is organised around a series of issues that relate to the <strong>production of art and people’s responses to it</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> “Sản xuất nghệ thuật” (<em>production of art</em>) tương đương với cách nghệ thuật được tạo ra (<em>is made</em>), và “phản ứng của mọi người” (<em>people’s responses</em>) tương đương với cách nghệ thuật được cảm nhận (<em>is perceived</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"13\">5. Students will be able to do any of the optional courses that are listed.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Choosing Courses) “The optional courses listed below are <strong>not available every year</strong> and prospective students are advised to check on the availability of specific courses.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các khóa học không có sẵn hàng năm (<em>not available every year</em>), và có thể có <strong>hạn chế</strong> (<em>restrictions</em>) trong việc kết hợp, mâu thuẫn với việc sinh viên có thể học <strong>bất kỳ</strong> (<em>any</em>) khóa học nào.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"15\">6. Students may be able to take an unlisted course if they get the appropriate approval.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Choosing Courses) “Students wishing to take a course that <strong>does not appear in the list</strong> but is offered by the Faculty of History will need to get <strong>permission from the relevant Course Tutor</strong>. An application should then be made by the candidate’s supervisor.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Khóa học không có trong danh sách (<em>unlisted course</em>) có thể được theo học nếu sinh viên nhận được <strong>sự cho phép</strong> (<em>permission/appropriate approval</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('55cb5618-1752-42cf-ab80-9f69f2aad1a7', '55d7a72b-0635-427b-a1e9-7b7972690c1b', 'fillup', 'Questions 7–13', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Optional courses</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Authenticity and Replication</strong></p>
<p>– genuine art is studied in addition to that considered {fraudulent}</p>
<p>– art objects are studied in {museums}</p>
<p><strong>French Painting 1880-1912</strong></p>
<p>– the course covers the period up to when {Cubism} started to be prominent</p>
<p>– the course looks at the connections between art and new developments such as {cinema}</p>
<p><strong>Medieval European Art</strong></p>
<p>– the course looks at two issues: artistic creativity and processes for teaching technique</p>
<p>– the course considers how artists could be original when taught by an expert in a {workshop}</p>
<p><strong>Reception of Classical European Art</strong></p>
<p>– life-sized and miniature sculpture is examined</p>
<p>– painting is examined by looking at the decoration of {vases}</p>
<p>– architecture is assessed by studying 19th century models bought by {travelers}</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong>7. – genuine art is studied in addition to that considered fraudulent.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>fraudulent</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) “…including works seen as genuine as well as works <strong>regarded as fraudulent</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Khóa học nghiên cứu cả các tác phẩm nghệ thuật chính hãng (<em>genuine</em>) và các tác phẩm bị coi là <strong>gian lận</strong> (<em>fraudulent</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong>8. – art objects are studied in museums.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>museums</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) “The course will make particularly extensive use of trips to <strong>museums</strong> to view actual objects and images.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Khóa học sẽ tận dụng các chuyến đi đến <strong>bảo tàng</strong> (<em>museums</em>) để xem các đối tượng và hình ảnh thực tế.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong>9. – the course covers the period up to when Cubism started to be prominent.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Cubism</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “…at which point <strong>Cubism</strong> began to have a major impact on the thinking of French artists.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Khóa học kết thúc khi trường phái <strong>Lập thể</strong> (<em>Cubism</em>) bắt đầu có ảnh hưởng lớn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong>10. – the course looks at the connections between art and new developments such as  cinema.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>cinema</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “The rise of new forms of image distribution, including <strong>cinema</strong>, will be addressed…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Khóa học xem xét sự phát triển của nghệ thuật gắn với các phát triển mới, bao gồm <strong>điện ảnh</strong> (<em>cinema</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong>11. – the course considers how artists could be original when taught by an expert in a  workshop.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>workshop</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “During this period, young, would-be artists acted as assistants to a master painter in his <strong>workshop</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Khóa học nghiên cứu cách các nghệ sĩ trẻ có thể sáng tạo khi được đào tạo dưới sự hướng dẫn của một bậc thầy trong <strong>xưởng vẽ</strong> (<em>workshop</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong>12. – painting is examined by looking at the decoration of vases.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>vases</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “Painting is studied through the designs painted on <strong>vases</strong>, particularly Athenian and South Italian…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Hội họa được nghiên cứu qua các thiết kế được vẽ trên <strong>bình gốm</strong> (<em>vases</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong>13. – architecture is assessed by studying 19th century models bought by travelers.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>travelers</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “…ancient Greek temples that were excavated in the nineteenth century and also replicated in miniature for sale to <strong>travelers</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Kiến trúc được đánh giá qua các mô hình được bán cho <strong>du khách</strong> (<em>travelers</em>) trong thế kỷ 19.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('32ebe1a1-41e3-4c7e-86b2-4a2b58d9b5bb', '828e2266-0466-489e-b82d-6e94f16dfd91', 'fillup', 'Questions 14-16', '<p>Label the diagram below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>
<p><span class="fill-history-correct">{chain}</span></p>
<p><span class="fill-history-correct">{gear}</span></p>
<p><span class="fill-history-correct">{motor}</span></p>
', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"4\">14.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>chain</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “The traditional lifting mechanism is a long length of <strong>chain</strong> running up the hill under the track.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cơ chế nâng truyền thống là một đoạn <strong>dây xích</strong> (<em>chain</em>) chạy dọc theo đồi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"6\">15.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>gear</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “The chain is fastened in a loop, which is wound around a <strong>gear</strong> at the top of the hill and another one at the bottom of the hill.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Dây xích được quấn quanh một <strong>bánh răng</strong> (<em>gear</em>) ở cả đỉnh và đáy đồi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"8\">16.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>motor</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “The gear at the bottom of the hill is turned by a <strong>motor</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bánh răng ở phía dưới được vận hành bằng một <strong>động cơ</strong> (<em>motor</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e3235a56-467f-4fa1-b5d4-22111d6fbcbf', '828e2266-0466-489e-b82d-6e94f16dfd91', 'fillup', 'Questions 17–21', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>History of roller coasters</strong></p>
<p>Modern roller coasters are descended from 16th-century Russian slides with a surface of {ice} .</p>
<p>People climbed to the top, and travelled down in sleds. In France, because of the higher temperatures, the wooden surface on the slides was {waxed} and {wheels} were attached to the cars to ease the descent.</p>
<p>The first US roller coaster was used for transporting {coal} down a mountainside in carts. Initially, these were pulled by mules but in time power was produced by {steam engines}</p>
</div>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"5\">17. Modern roller coasters are descended from 16th-century Russian slides with a surface of <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>ice</strong>.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>ice</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “Their direct ancestors were ice slides, popular in Russia in the 16th and 17th centuries. They consisted of a long, steep, wooden slide covered in <strong>ice</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tổ tiên trực tiếp của tàu lượn siêu tốc là các máng trượt Nga có bề mặt được bao phủ bằng <strong>băng</strong> (<em>ice</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"8\">18. In France, because of the higher temperatures; the wooden surface on the slides was <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>waxed</strong>…</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>waxed</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “For most of the year, the warmer climate would melt the ice, so the French started building <strong>waxed slides</strong> instead.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Do khí hậu ấm hơn, người Pháp đã phải thay máng trượt bằng băng bằng máng trượt bằng gỗ được <strong>đánh bóng</strong> (<em>waxed</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"10\">19. …and <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>wheels</strong> were attached to the cars to ease the descent.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>wheels</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “To help the sleds move down these slides, they added <strong>wheels</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Để giúp xe trượt di chuyển dễ dàng hơn trên máng trượt đã được đánh bóng, họ đã thêm <strong>bánh xe</strong> (<em>wheels</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"13\">20. The first US roller coaster was used for transporting <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>coal</strong> down a mountainside in carts.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>coal</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn H) “The first American roller coaster was built in the mountains of Pennsylvania… originally to provide an easy way to send <strong>coal</strong> to the railway 29 km down to mountain.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tàu lượn siêu tốc đầu tiên ở Mỹ ban đầu được dùng để vận chuyển <strong>than đá</strong> (<em>coal</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"16\">21. Initially, these were pulled by mules but in time power was produced by <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>steam engines</strong>.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>steam engines</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn H) “They were eventually replaced with <strong>steam engines</strong>, to make the system more efficient.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Ban đầu dùng la (<em>mules</em>), sau đó chúng được thay thế bằng <strong>động cơ hơi nước</strong> (<em>steam engines</em>) để hệ thống hoạt động hiệu quả hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ab4e2913-700e-430a-baef-7a02e6128757', '828e2266-0466-489e-b82d-6e94f16dfd91', 'radio', 'Questions 22–26', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The earliest modifications to the basic slide were made in France."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Roller coasters continued to increase in popularity throughout the 1920s and 1930s."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "New roller coaster technology was introduced in the 1970s in response to public demand."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Roller coasters were less popular for most of the 1980s than in the 1970s and 1990s."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The design of roller-coaster rides became more varied in the 1990s."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"26\">22. The earliest modifications to the basic slide were made in France.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “It seems that the idea was then imported into France. For most of the year, the warmer climate would melt the ice, so the French started building waxed slides instead. <strong>To help the sleds move down these slides, they added wheels</strong>, and in 1817, for the first time, a train was attached to the track.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc người Pháp thêm <strong>bánh xe</strong> (<em>wheels</em>) và gắn tàu hỏa vào đường ray là những <strong>sự sửa đổi</strong> (<em>modifications</em>) đầu tiên được thực hiện sau khi ý tưởng được nhập khẩu từ Nga.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"28\">23. Roller coasters continued to increase in popularity throughout the 1920s and 1930s.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn J) “By the 1920s, roller coasters were in full swing… <strong>Following the Great Depression, a decline in roller coaster production began in the early 1930s</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Sau Đại suy thoái, một sự <strong>suy giảm</strong> (<em>decline</em>) trong sản xuất tàu lượn siêu tốc đã bắt đầu vào đầu những năm 1930, mâu thuẫn với việc tiếp tục <strong>gia tăng</strong> (<em>increase in popularity</em>) trong suốt những năm 1930.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"30\">24. New roller coaster technology was introduced in the 1970s in response to public demand.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn J) “…a second roller-coaster boom in the 1970s and the beginning of the 1980s revitalized the amusement park industry, and <strong>introduced a slew of innovative tubular steel coasters</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc xác nhận công nghệ mới (tàu lượn thép ống) đã được giới thiệu trong thời kỳ bùng nổ thứ hai vào những năm 1970, nhưng <strong>không nói rõ</strong> liệu sự đổi mới này có phải là <strong>phản ứng trực tiếp trước nhu cầu công chúng</strong> (<em>in response to public demand</em>) hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"32\">25. Roller coasters were less popular for most of the 1980s than in the 1970s and 1990s.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn J-K) Có sự bùng nổ vào <strong>những năm 1970</strong> và đầu 1980 (Đoạn J). Sau đó, điều này “was followed by a <strong>decline in interest for the rest of the decade</strong>” (tức là phần lớn những năm <strong>1980</strong> còn lại) (Đoạn K). Sau đó, “since the <strong>early 1990s</strong> the amusement-park industry has experienced another coaster boom.” (Đoạn K).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Mức độ phổ biến <strong>suy giảm</strong> (<em>decline in interest</em>) trong phần lớn những năm 1980, nằm giữa hai giai đoạn <strong>bùng nổ</strong> (<em>boom</em>) vào cuối thập niên 70/đầu 80 và đầu thập niên 90.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"34\">26. The design of roller-coaster rides became more varied in the 1990s.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"35\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn K) “since the early 1990s the amusement-park industry has experienced another coaster boom of sorts. New launching techniques and other technological developments have <strong>opened up a world of options for designers</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Sự phát triển công nghệ đã <strong>mở ra một thế giới các lựa chọn</strong> (<em>opened up a world of options</em>) cho các nhà thiết kế, điều này đồng nghĩa với việc thiết kế tàu lượn trở nên <strong>đa dạng hơn</strong> (<em>more varied</em>) trong những năm 1990.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('082f1d31-e4be-4d1f-adc6-b51cf722076c', 'e4c40f58-5c1b-4aaf-af7d-7127832f5e78', 'checkbox', 'Questions 25–26', NULL, '<p data-start="951" data-end="978">Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p data-start="980" data-end="1059">Which <strong>TWO </strong>things do Anna and Simon both appreciate about their lecturers?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "They encourage freedom of thought", "correct": true}, {"option": "They help individual students in seminars", "correct": false}, {"option": "They are willing to adapt courses", "correct": false}, {"option": "They are enthusiastic about their subject", "correct": false}, {"option": "They encourage students to improve", "correct": true}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e66aea5e-116c-45ef-9d16-30d3c487543e', '06c45174-aeed-48b2-adcd-fd1b63b1e5eb', 'matching', 'Questions 27-33', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 3 has seven paragraphs, <strong>A-G</strong>.</p>
<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below.</p>
<p>Write the correct number, i-viii, in boxes 27-33 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. Hurricanes in history"}, {"optionText": "ii. How hurricanes form"}, {"optionText": "iii. How a laboratory exercise re-route a hurricane"}, {"optionText": "iv. Exciting ways to utilise future technologies"}, {"optionText": "v. Are hurricanes unbeatable?"}, {"optionText": "vi. Re-visit earlier ideas"}, {"optionText": "vii. How lives might have been saved"}, {"optionText": "viii. A range of low-tech methods"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"4\">27. Paragraph A</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>v. Are hurricanes unbeatable?</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) Đoạn này mô tả sức mạnh tàn phá khủng khiếp của bão và kết thúc bằng câu hỏi: “<strong>But can we ever find a way to control these formidable forces of nature?</strong>“</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi cuối cùng tóm tắt ý chính của đoạn: Liệu bão có phải là không thể đánh bại (<em>unbeatable</em>)?</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"6\">28. Paragraph B</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>ii. How hurricanes form</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) Đoạn này giải thích quá trình bão phát triển: từ cụm dông bão (<em>thunderstorm clusters</em>), không khí ẩm nóng bốc lên, sự ngưng tụ (<em>condensation</em>), giải phóng nhiệt, và cuối cùng hình thành mắt bão (<em>eye</em>) và xoáy.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nội dung đoạn mô tả chi tiết <strong>cách bão hình thành</strong> (<em>How hurricanes form</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"8\">29. Paragraph C</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>vi. Re-visit earlier ideas</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) Tác giả nói rằng các nghiên cứu hiện tại được truyền cảm hứng từ <strong>trực giác trong quá khứ</strong> (<em>past intuition</em>) về lý thuyết hỗn loạn (<em>chaos theory</em>) 30 năm trước. Tác giả có thể <strong>làm mới niềm hứng thú</strong> (<em>renew my enthusiasm</em>) nhờ công nghệ máy tính.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này nói về việc <strong>thăm lại những ý tưởng trước đây</strong> (<em>Re-visit earlier ideas</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"10\">30. Paragraph D</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>iii. How a laboratory exercise re-route a hurricane</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) Tác giả mô tả việc sử dụng <strong>thí nghiệm mô phỏng trên máy tính</strong> (<em>simulation experiments on computers</em>) cho bão Iniki và <strong>thành công ngay lập tức</strong> trong việc thay đổi đường đi (<em>altering the path</em>).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nội dung đoạn mô tả cách một thí nghiệm (trên máy tính/phòng thí nghiệm) đã <strong>chuyển hướng</strong> (<em>re-route</em>) một cơn bão.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"12\">31. Paragraph E</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>vii. How lives might have been saved</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) Đoạn này mô tả sự thay đổi nhỏ trong nhiệt độ và gió đã khiến bão Iniki <strong>“went off the track to the west… leaving Kauai untouched”</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc bão bị lệch hướng và không đổ bộ vào Kauai ngụ ý rằng <strong>sinh mạng có thể đã được cứu</strong> (<em>How lives might have been saved</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"14\">32. Paragraph F</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>iv. Exciting ways to utilise future technologies</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) Đoạn này thảo luận về các <strong>trạm năng lượng mặt trời quay quanh Trái đất trong tương lai</strong> (<em>Future earth-orbiting solar power stations</em>) có thể được điều chỉnh để phát chùm vi sóng làm nóng không khí và thay đổi hướng bão.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đây là một <strong>cách thức thú vị để tận dụng công nghệ tương lai</strong> (<em>Exciting ways to utilise future technologies</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"16\">33. Paragraph G</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>viii. A range of low-tech methods</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) Đoạn này mô tả các hình thức can thiệp có thể là: “exquisitely targeted <strong>clouds bearing silver iodide</strong> or other rainfall-inducing elements…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc sử dụng các phương pháp tương đối đơn giản như mây mang bạc iodide để thay đổi lượng mưa là một <strong>loạt các phương pháp công nghệ thấp</strong> (<em>A range of low-tech methods</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5895f082-c243-4bef-9b09-55a0bdb8cfe9', '06c45174-aeed-48b2-adcd-fd1b63b1e5eb', 'fillup', 'Questions 34-38', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 34-38 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p>Hurricanes originate as groups of {thunderstorm} over the tropical oceans. Low-latitude seas continuously provide heat and moisture to the atmosphere, producing warm, humid air above the sea surface. When this air rises, the water vapour in it condenses to form clouds and precipitation. {condensation}  releases heat—the solar heat it took to evaporate the water at the ocean surface. This so-called latent {heat} of condensation makes the air more buoyant, causing it to ascend still higher in a self-reinforcing feedback process. Eventually, the tropical depression begins to organise and strengthen, forming the familiar {eye} —the calm central hub around which a hurricane spins. On passing over {land} , the hurricane’s sustaining source of warm water is cut off, which leads to the storm’s rapid weakening.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"21\">34. Hurricanes originate as groups of <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>thunderstorms</strong> over the tropical oceans.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>thunderstorm</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “Hurricanes grow in the form of <strong>thunderstorm</strong> clusters above the tropical seas.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bão phát triển từ các cụm <strong>dông bão</strong> (<em>thunderstorm</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"23\">35. …the water vapour in it condenses to form clouds and precipitation. <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>Condensation</strong> releases heat…</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Condensation</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “<strong>Condensation</strong> gives out heat in the process…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Quá trình <strong>ngưng tụ</strong> (<em>Condensation</em>) giải phóng nhiệt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"25\">36. This so-called latent <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>heat</strong> of condensation makes the air more buoyant…</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>heat</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “This so-called invisible <strong>heat</strong> of condensation makes the air more buoyant…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nhiệt (<em>heat</em>) tiềm ẩn của sự ngưng tụ làm cho không khí nổi hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"27\">37. …forming the familiar <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>eye</strong> —the calm central hub around which a hurricane spins.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>eye</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “…forming the familiar <strong>eye</strong> — the calm centre hub that a hurricane spins around.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cấu trúc trung tâm được hình thành là <strong>mắt bão</strong> (<em>eye</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"29\">38. On passing over <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>land</strong>, the hurricane’s sustaining source of warm water is cut off…</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>land</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “When reaching the <strong>land</strong>, the hurricane no longer has a continuous supply of warm water, which causes it to swiftly weaken.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Khi đi qua <strong>đất liền</strong> (<em>land</em>), nguồn nước ấm cung cấp cho bão bị cắt đứt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('71c8a991-2773-4ae5-9898-d53472e4fc6b', '06c45174-aeed-48b2-adcd-fd1b63b1e5eb', 'radio', 'Questions 39-40', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B, C or D.</p>
<p>Write the correct letter in boxes 39 and 40 on your answer sheet.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. the huge damage hurricane triggers"}, {"content": "B. the developments in computer technologies"}, {"content": "C. the requirement of some local people"}, {"content": "D. the chaos theory learnt as a student"}], "question": "What encouraged the writer to restart researching hurricane control?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. surprised that their intervention had not achieve a lot."}, {"content": "B. ecstatic with the achievement the first experiment had"}, {"content": "C. surprised that their intervention had the intended effect"}, {"content": "D. regretful about the impending success."}], "question": "What was the writer''s reaction after their first experiment?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"34\">39. What encouraged the writer to restart researching hurricane control?</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"35\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B. the developments in computer technologies</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) &#8220;Back then, I was not able to test my ideas, but thanks to the <strong>advancement of computer simulation and remote-sensing technologies</strong> over the last 10 years, I can now renew my enthusiasm in large-scale weather control.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Sự phát triển của <strong>công nghệ mô phỏng máy tính</strong> (<em>computer simulation technologies</em>) đã cho phép tác giả quay lại nghiên cứu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"36\">40. What was the writer’s reaction after their first experiment?</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"37\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C. surprised that their intervention had the intended effect</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) &#8220;The current forecasting technologies were far from perfect, so <strong>it took us by surprise that our first simulation turned out to be an immediate success</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả đã <strong>bất ngờ</strong> (<em>surprised</em>) vì sự can thiệp (<em>intervention</em>) trong mô phỏng (<em>simulation</em>) đã <strong>thành công ngay lập tức</strong> (<em>immediate success</em>), đạt được mục tiêu (<em>intended effect</em>) là thay đổi đường đi của bão.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e110730d-21ea-4a77-98b7-2b6f13491b6a', 'e4c40f58-5c1b-4aaf-af7d-7127832f5e78', 'matching', 'Questions 27–30', NULL, '<p>Which skills are developed in the following courses?<br data-start="1352" data-end="1355" />Choose <strong>FOUR </strong>correct answers, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>F</strong></p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Courses</strong></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Communication 1 {talking in public}</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Psychology {working in large groups}</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Interpersonal Skills {reducing problems between co-workers}</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Communication 3 {understanding cultural differences}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "making decisions under pressure"}, {"optionText": "working in large groups"}, {"optionText": "reducing problems between co-workers"}, {"optionText": "talking in public"}, {"optionText": "understanding cultural differences"}, {"optionText": "using logical argument"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c2d3e3f8-e1ac-43a7-a5d2-81a37ba3c0b0', '4b0dce98-f804-469e-a1f0-ba4271af7e34', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<p data-start="91" data-end="155">Complete the notes below.<br data-start="116" data-end="119" />Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="157" data-end="191"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Inventing a Universal Language</span></strong></p>
<h3 data-start="193" data-end="211">Introduction</h3>
<p data-start="212" data-end="411">• Most languages were not invented – they evolved.<br data-start="262" data-end="265" />• Early invented languages were used for religious purposes or for {trade}.<br data-start="339" data-end="342" />• We know of about 900 invented languages, but many have been lost.</p>
<h3 data-start="413" data-end="434">William Spencer</h3>
<p data-start="435" data-end="627">• He wrote books about {science} so he needed an accurate language.<br data-start="499" data-end="502" />• At first he tried to base his language on {numbers}.<br data-start="553" data-end="556" />• Later he classified words in the same way that was used for plants.</p>
<h3 data-start="629" data-end="650">Ludwig Zamenhof</h3>
<p data-start="651" data-end="934">• He mixed together existing European languages.<br data-start="699" data-end="702" />• He wrote {songs} to help develop his new language.<br data-start="753" data-end="756" />• He wanted simplicity, e.g. one prefix to make words {negative}.<br data-start="817" data-end="820" />• He sent {letter} to his friends to publicise his language.<br data-start="878" data-end="881" />• He created the most successful invented language.</p>
<h3 data-start="936" data-end="954">Bruce Goldie</h3>
<p data-start="955" data-end="1137">• Each word of his language was based on a {picture}.<br data-start="1005" data-end="1008" />• His language did not get academic recognition at first.<br data-start="1065" data-end="1068" />• Children in a Canadian {hospital} learned to read using his language.</p>
<h3 data-start="1139" data-end="1192">Conclusion: why have invented languages failed?</h3>
<p data-start="1193" data-end="1325">• They cannot express {emotions}.<br data-start="1222" data-end="1225" />• English became the global language.<br data-start="1262" data-end="1265" />• They are now invented by {writers}, just for entertainment.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 4: INVENTING A UNIVERSAL LANGUAGE</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Good morning. Welcome back to the series of linguistics lectures. Today I will be talking about the idea of inventing a universal language.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">What does that mean? Well, most human languages were never invented; instead they evolved over time, and the result is, you know, they’re irregular and difficult to learn. So for centuries, people have dreamed of inventing a perfect universal language.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">The early invented languages that did exist were either created by priests to be used for religious purposes or developed to help establish <strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">(31) trade</strong> between different nations. Scholars have found evidence that around 900 languages have been invented over the centuries in various parts of the world, but the linguist Erika Okrent believes that the exact figure is unclear because she suspects many of these languages are now lost—no record of them survives.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"6\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">WILLIAM SPENCER</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> The first really serious attempt to invent a language was made by William Spencer in the 17th century. Like so many others, he was frustrated by the irregularities in all existing languages. Accuracy was particularly important for Spencer because he wrote books—his subject was <strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"288\">(32) science</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">As a result, he wanted to create a language where words had only one meaning, so everyone would understand precisely what they meant. At first he thought the only way to do this was, instead of using the usual letters of the alphabet—A, B, C and so on—he tried to substitute <strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"275\">(33) numbers</strong> for them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">However, this attempt failed, mostly because he couldn’t describe complex ideas in this way. So Spencer went back to using the alphabet, but he grouped words together in a different way. When his dictionary was published in 1668, the words weren’t classified in alphabetical order. What he’d done was he’d used the same system with which plants were divided up into groups based on their type.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"11\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">LUDWIG ZAMENHOF</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Another important attempt to invent a universal language was made by Ludwig Zamenhof, who was born in 1859. Zamenhof’s language reflects his own background; he grew up speaking Polish, English, French, German and Russian. So rather than create a completely new language, he mixed together five or six existing European languages.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">Then Zamenhof used an interesting technique to help him develop his new language: he used it to write quite a few different <strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"124\">(34) songs</strong>, and this made his work more enjoyable. He also thought that most European languages were too complicated, which meant that it was very difficult for people to learn them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">Zamenhof wanted to create a more simple language, so for example, he had a single prefix that was used before adjectives or verbs to make them <strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"143\">(35) negative</strong>, which is obviously much easier than English.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\">Then finally he published a book introducing his language to the world in 1887. Unfortunately, like other invented languages, no one was very interested at first. So again Zamenhof used an interesting approach in order to publicise the completed language: he made a list of everyone he knew and posted a <strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"304\">(36) letter</strong> to all of them using the new language. Many people were surprised how easily they could understand it, and the language began to attract attention. Zamenhof’s language was never used all around the world as he had hoped, but still, it’s probably the most successful of all the invented languages.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"17\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">BRUCE GOLDIE</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> In the 20th century, an Australian named Bruce Goldie tried something completely different. Goldie thought that a universal language would be easier to use if the starting point for each word was a <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"208\">(37) picture</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\">Goldie spent more than 20 years designing his new language and eventually published a book giving all the details in 1949. He also went on a lecture tour to promote it, but although the general public were often quite interested, much to Goldie’s disappointment, his language was ignored by all of the major universities despite frequent attempts to make them interested.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\">It wasn’t until the 1970s that his language had some success. This was in Canada in fact, where it was used to teach a group of disabled children in a <strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"151\">(38) hospital</strong> to read, and as a result, Goldie got some recognition for his work.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"22\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CONCLUSION</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> So what can we say in conclusion? Well, the truth is all attempts to create a universal language have failed, and there are a number of reasons for this.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\">Firstly, most universal languages have been seen as rather technical and plain. They’re not good at conveying <strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">(39) emotion</strong> (hoặc emotions), so they’ve never been very popular. Another reason is the spread of English as a global language in the 20th century, particularly resulting from the film industry in Hollywood.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\">Then lastly, the type of people who invented the languages began to change. In the past it had been academics, but more recently, the languages have often been created by <strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"171\">(40) writers</strong>, usually for entertainment, so they haven’t been taken seriously.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a466a288-6073-46c3-aab6-fc63b3eb389f', '50c59e77-9f9f-4e17-a481-9518bdacfe5c', 'matrix', 'Questions 1-6.', NULL, '<p>Classify the following developments as characterising</p>
<p>Write the correct letter, A, B or C, in boxes 1-6 on your answer sheet</p>
', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of options", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "becoming interested in people of the other gender", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "beginning to choose a future career", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "needing to feel the same as one’s friends", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "beginning to form a self-image separate from the family context", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "having less need for the good opinion of friends", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "exposing oneself to dangers", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "early adolescence", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "middle adolescence", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "late adolescence", "categoryLetter": "C"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Becoming interested in people of the other gender</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> B (middle adolescence)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 2, dòng cuối: &#8220;The effect of this rapid change is that <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">mid-adolescents</strong> are body-conscious, and their concerns are directed towards their <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"153\">opposite-sexed peers</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ rõ rằng ở giai đoạn giữa tuổi vị thành niên (mid-adolescence), sự quan tâm của các em bắt đầu hướng về những người bạn khác giới.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Beginning to choose a future career</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> B (middle adolescence)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 7, dòng 3: &#8220;<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">Mid-adolescents</strong> must identify, at least at a preliminary level, what their <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"103\">adult vocational goals</strong> are&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc xác định mục tiêu nghề nghiệp (vocational goals) ở mức độ sơ bộ được thực hiện bởi các thanh thiếu niên ở giai đoạn giữa (mid-adolescents).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Needing to feel the same as one’s friends</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> A (early adolescence)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 10, dòng 3 và 6: &#8220;&#8230;it seems to hit a peak of importance during <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">early adolescence</strong>&#8230; ‘Fitting in’, not being different, and being accepted seem somehow pressing to this age group.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nhu cầu &#8220;hòa nhập&#8221; (fitting in) và không trở nên khác biệt so với bạn bè đạt mức độ quan trọng cao nhất vào giai đoạn đầu tuổi vị thành niên (early adolescence).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Beginning to form a self-image separate from the family context</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> A (early adolescence)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 8, dòng 2: &#8220;During the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">early adolescent years</strong> a young person begins to recognise their uniqueness and to establish themselves as <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"145\">separate individuals, independent of their parents</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Quá trình tách biệt hình ảnh bản thân khỏi sự phụ thuộc vào cha mẹ để tạo lập bản sắc riêng bắt đầu ngay từ những năm đầu tuổi vị thành niên.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Having less need for the good opinion of friends</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> C (late adolescence)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 10, dòng 4: &#8220;Certainly by <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">late adolescence</strong> or early adulthood the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">need for peer approval has diminished</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> &#8220;Diminished&#8221; có nghĩa là giảm đi. Nhu cầu được bạn bè chấp thuận hay coi trọng sẽ giảm bớt khi trẻ bước vào giai đoạn cuối tuổi vị thành niên (late adolescence).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Exposing oneself to dangers</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> B (middle adolescence)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 11, dòng 3: &#8220;Risky behaviours are sufficiently pervasive among adolescents to suggest that <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">risk-taking</strong> may be a normal developmental process of <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">middle adolescence</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hành vi mạo hiểm (risk-taking/exposing oneself to dangers) được coi là một quá trình phát triển bình thường của giai đoạn giữa tuổi vị thành niên.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fc7706a2-8ec6-4d01-8b69-6015ec63eb78', '50c59e77-9f9f-4e17-a481-9518bdacfe5c', 'matching', 'Questions 7-10', NULL, '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, A-E, below.</p>
<p>Write the correct letter,<strong> A-E</strong> in boxes 7-10 on your answer sheet.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A. reflects an adolescent’s emerging self-perception."}, {"optionText": "B. cannot solve a problem without an example."}, {"optionText": "C. is designed to become more challenging."}, {"optionText": "D. formulates a personal set of moral beliefs and values."}, {"optionText": "E. varies according to the individual."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Havighurst proposed a set of tasks which", "correctAnswer": "A. reflects an adolescent’s emerging self-perception.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": " A course of study at high school", "correctAnswer": "C. is designed to become more challenging.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "The speed of development of thinking ability during adolescence", "correctAnswer": "E. varies according to the individual.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Adolescence is a time when the young person", "correctAnswer": "D. formulates a personal set of moral beliefs and values.", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">7. Havighurst proposed a set of tasks which <strong>A. reflects an adolescent’s emerging self-perception.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) “Each of the Havighurst tasks can also be seen as elements of the <strong>overall sense of self</strong> that adolescents carry with them…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Giáo sư Havighurst cho rằng mỗi nhiệm vụ phát triển là một phần của cảm nhận tổng thể về bản thân (<em>sense of self</em>). Cụm từ “<strong>emerging self-perception</strong>” (nhận thức về bản thân đang hình thành) trong đáp án A đồng nghĩa với “sense of self” trong bài.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">8. A course of study at high school <strong>C. is designed to become more challenging.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “School curricula are frequently dominated by the inclusion of <strong>more abstract, demanding material</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nêu rõ chương trình học ở trường trung học (<em>school curricula</em>) thường bao gồm những tài liệu <strong>đòi hỏi cao hơn và trừu tượng hơn</strong> (<em>more abstract, demanding</em>). Điều này khớp với ý <strong>trở nên thách thức hơn</strong> (<em>more challenging</em>) ở đáp án C.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">9. The speed of development of thinking ability during adolescence <strong>E. varies according to the individual.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>E</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “…not all adolescents make the intellectual transition <strong>at the same rate</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “<strong>not at the same rate</strong>” (không cùng tốc độ/tỷ lệ) có nghĩa là mỗi người có một tốc độ phát triển khác nhau. Đáp án E “<strong>varies according to the individual</strong>” (thay đổi tùy theo từng cá nhân) là cách diễn đạt tương đương hoàn hảo.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">10. Adolescence is a time when the young person <strong>D. formulates a personal set of moral beliefs and values.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>D</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…they also <strong>adopt an integrated set of values and morals</strong>… the adolescent restructures those beliefs into a <strong>personal ideology</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Ở tuổi vị thành niên, trẻ em không còn chỉ tuân theo quy tắc của cha mẹ mà tự hình thành/xây dựng (<em>restructures/formulates</em>) một hệ thống tư tưởng và giá trị đạo đức cá nhân (<em>personal ideology/moral beliefs and values</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bbf71ca5-0f55-4f05-a36c-323a09ee857f', '9e1776dd-ee65-4b43-a2d4-8cadedf709d7', 'matching', ' Questions 14–20', '', '<p>Reading passage 2 has six paragraphs.</p>
<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below.</p>
<p>Choose the correct number, <strong>i-ix</strong>. in the boxes 14-20.</p>', 'matching_sentence_endings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i Fluctuations in bittern numbers over time"}, {"optionText": "ii Research findings on habitat needs of adult bitterns"}, {"optionText": "iii Predators in the natural world"}, {"optionText": "iv The importance in the natural world"}, {"optionText": "v Initial habitat investigation and decisions"}, {"optionText": "vi The need for co-operation to ensure nature preservation"}, {"optionText": "vii Impressive results of initial intervention"}, {"optionText": "viii Determining how many bitterns there are"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Đoạn 1 (Paragraph 1) — Đáp án: i (Fluctuations in bittern numbers over time)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí thông tin:</strong> Xuyên suốt đoạn 1.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “By 1886… close to extinction. Fortunately, it recovered… in 1950… rose to a peak… By the 1980s… in trouble again… By 1997… imminent extinction”.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này liệt kê lịch sử thay đổi số lượng chim bittern theo thời gian: từ gần tuyệt chủng năm 1886, hồi phục vào 1950, rồi lại suy giảm vào những năm 1980 và 1997. Từ “Fluctuations” (sự biến động) mô tả chính xác quá trình tăng giảm này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Đoạn 2 (Paragraph 2) — Đáp án: viii (Determining how many bitterns there are)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí thông tin:</strong> Dòng 3-6 đoạn 2.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Our first challenge was to develop standard methods to <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">monitor their numbers</strong>… developed a method to <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">count them</strong> using the sound patterns unique to each individual”.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nội dung chính của đoạn tập trung vào thách thức và phương pháp khoa học (sử dụng âm thanh) để đếm và xác định số lượng cá thể chim bittern hiện có.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Đoạn 3 (Paragraph 3) — Đáp án: v (Initial habitat investigation and decisions)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí thông tin:</strong> Dòng 1-2 và dòng 6 đoạn 3.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Our first direct <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">understanding</strong> of what breeding bitterns require… Based on this work, <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">broad recommendations</strong>… were made, and funding was provided…”.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này nói về việc bắt đầu tìm hiểu (investigation) nhu cầu môi trường sống và đưa ra các quyết định (decisions) như đưa ra khuyến nghị quản lý và cấp ngân quỹ để bảo tồn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Đoạn 4 (Paragraph 4) — Đáp án: ii (Research findings on habitat needs of adult bitterns)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí thông tin:</strong> Dòng 2-12 đoạn 4.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “This showed clear <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">preferences</strong> for feeding in the wetter reedbed areas… we located 87 bittern nests and found that female bitterns <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"144\">preferred</strong> to nest in…”.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này trình bày các kết quả nghiên cứu cụ thể về sở thích môi trường sống của chim trưởng thành (cả con trống và con mái) trong việc kiếm ăn và làm tổ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Đoạn 5 (Paragraph 5) — Đáp án: vii (Impressive results of initial intervention)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí thông tin:</strong> Dòng 1-3 đoạn 5.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">success</strong> of the habitat prescriptions… has been <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">spectacular</strong>. For instance… numbers gradually <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">increased from one to ten</strong>…”.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này nêu bật kết quả rực rỡ (spectacular/impressive) sau khi thực hiện các biện pháp can thiệp môi trường (intervention), minh chứng bằng việc số lượng chim tăng mạnh tại Minsmere.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Đoạn 6 (Paragraph 6) — Đáp án: iv (The importance in the natural world)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí thông tin:</strong> Dòng 5-13 đoạn 6.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…recommendations on habitat and water conditions to promote <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">native fish populations</strong>… Young bitterns were found to seek out new sites… secure a more sustainable UK bittern population… less vulnerable to chance events…”.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này nhấn mạnh tầm quan trọng của việc duy trì chuỗi thức ăn tự nhiên (cá bản địa) và tạo ra mạng lưới các khu vực cư trú mới để bảo vệ loài chim này trước các biến cố tự nhiên như mực nước biển dâng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Đoạn 7 (Paragraph 7) — Đáp án: vi (The need for co-operation to ensure nature preservation)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí thông tin:</strong> Dòng 5-11 đoạn 7.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…success has only been achieved through the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">trust, hard work and dedication of all the managers, owners and wardens</strong> of sites that have implemented…”.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu kết luận của bài viết khẳng định rằng thành công không chỉ dựa vào khoa học mà cần sự hợp tác (co-operation) và tận tâm của tất cả những người liên quan (chủ đất, quản lý, người bảo vệ).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f4ff02f4-7ab8-4f15-8a40-e6a1b44ad56e', '50c59e77-9f9f-4e17-a481-9518bdacfe5c', 'radio', 'Questions 11-13', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Most pre-adolescent children are capable of abstract thought."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": " Adolescents ‘limited skills’ with words may give a false impression of their ability."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Whether or not an adolescent is accepted by their age-group is an important clue to other aspects of their social adjustment"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">11. FALSE</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 3</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…children’s thinking is dominated by a <strong>concrete example</strong>… their thinking is <strong>constrained to what is real and physical</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn 3 khẳng định tư duy của trẻ em bị giới hạn (<em>constrained</em>) vào những gì thực tế và hữu hình. Điều này mâu thuẫn trực tiếp với ý kiến cho rằng chúng có thể tư duy trừu tượng. Do đó đáp án là <strong>FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">12. TRUE</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 6</strong></li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “As their <strong>conceptual development may outstrip their verbal development</strong>, adolescents may appear <strong>less competent than they really are</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn 6 giải thích rằng sự phát triển tư duy (<em>conceptual</em>) nhanh hơn khả năng ngôn ngữ (<em>verbal</em>), dẫn đến việc trẻ trông có vẻ kém cỏi hơn (<em>less competent</em>) năng lực thực sự. Điều này khớp với câu hỏi nên đáp án là <strong>TRUE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">13. TRUE</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 10</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “This degree to which an adolescent is able to make friends… is a <strong>major indicator of how well the adolescent will adjust in other areas</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn 10 khẳng định việc kết bạn là một <strong>chỉ số chính</strong> (<em>major indicator</em>) cho sự thích nghi tốt ở các mảng khác. Điều này khớp với nội dung câu hỏi nên đáp án là <strong>TRUE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f766eb01-f505-43df-8541-da2ec972eae7', '6e15d426-65f0-4fd5-af10-e5f33a0b20e4', 'matrix', 'Questions 1–7', '', '<p data-start="2384" data-end="2510">For which cycle trail are the following statements true?</p>
<p data-start="2384" data-end="2510">Write the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>E</strong>, in boxes 1–7 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p data-start="2512" data-end="2557"> </p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "People who like finding out about industrial history may find this cycle trail interesting", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Cyclists might find it advisable to get off their bikes on this trail and go a short distance on foot", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "It is possible to buy something to eat when cycling along this trail", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "People can stop on this trail and see some farm animals", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Cyclists can stop for a while on this trail and sit by the sea", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "A very old building is close to this trail and is open to the public", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Riders can extend the distance they cycle if they take this trail", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Đáp án: {D} The Cycle Trail in the Forest of Dean</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “The path is on a </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">former railway route</strong><span class=\"\"> from the time when the area was involved in </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">coal mining</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> “Coal mining” (khai thác than) và “former railway” (tuyến đường sắt cũ) chính là các yếu tố thuộc về </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">industrial history</strong><span class=\"\"> (lịch sử công nghiệp).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Đáp án: {C} A walking and cycling path in Birmingham</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “One hump-backed bridge is </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">best walked across</strong><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> but the rest of the route is flat…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Cụm từ “best walked across” đồng nghĩa với việc khuyên người đạp xe nên </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"84\">xuống xe và đi bộ</strong><span class=\"\"> một đoạn ngắn (go a short distance on foot).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Đáp án: {E} The Wirral Trail, Liverpool</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “The trail is safe,</span><span class=\"\"> flat and with </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">plenty of cafés</strong><span class=\"\"> on the way.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Có nhiều “cafés” đồng nghĩa với việc bạn có thể </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">mua đồ ăn</strong><span class=\"\"> (buy something to eat) khi đang đạp xe trên tuyến đường này.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Đáp án: {C} A walking and cycling path in Birmingham</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “…</span><span class=\"\">has a family-friendly visitor attraction especially known for its </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">sheep</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> “Sheep” (cừu) là một loại </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">farm animals</strong><span class=\"\"> (động vật trang trại).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Đáp án: {E} The Wirral Trail, Liverpool</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “…</span><span class=\"\">have a rest on the </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">beach</strong><span class=\"\"> at Caldy or Thurstaston…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Nghỉ ngơi trên bãi biển (beach) tương ứng với việc </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">ngồi bên bờ biển</strong><span class=\"\"> (sit by the sea).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Đáp án: {B} The Montgomery Canal cycle path, Wales</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “…</span><span class=\"\">include a visit to the nearby </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">thirteenth-century Powis Castle</strong><span class=\"\"> and its beautiful gardens.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Một lâu đài từ thế kỷ 13 là một </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">very old building</strong><span class=\"\"> (tòa nhà rất cũ) và việc có thể ghé thăm (visit) nghĩa là nó mở cửa cho công chúng.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Đáp án: {A} Bo’ness to Blackness Castle, Edinburgh</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “Simply return by the same path or </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">continue on</strong><span class=\"\"> to South Queensferry for a </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">longer day out</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> “Continue on for a longer day out” đồng nghĩa với việc người đạp xe có thể </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">kéo dài khoảng cách</strong><span class=\"\"> (extend the distance).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3d159133-e9d6-4e6a-a803-f9b58d655061', '6e15d426-65f0-4fd5-af10-e5f33a0b20e4', 'fillup', 'Questions 8-14', '<p> Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>from the text for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Design graduates – how to get work in the fashion industry</strong></span></p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 33.375px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 100%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 33.375px;">
<td style="text-align: center; border-color: #000000;">
<p>Consider whether to specialise in a less popular area, such as {accessories} rather than clothing.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: center;">🔽</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8573%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: center; border-color: #000000;">
<p>Try to get an internship in a business where you will be a good {fit}.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: center;">🔽</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 100%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: center; border-color: #000000;">
<p>Having identified a business where you want to work, go and hand in the application personally, even if this involves significant {expense}.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: center;">🔽</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 52.9688px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8573%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 52.9688px;">
<td style="text-align: center; border-color: #000000;">
<p>To get your work seen, make sure you produce a {profile} on various digital platforms and approach specialist {agencies} involved in recruiting fashion designers.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: center;">🔽</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8573%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: center; border-color: #000000;">
<p>Review the {training} you have done and make sure it is as comprehensive as possible by gaining further expertise.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: center;">🔽</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 100%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p style="text-align: center;">Do not rely on your ability alone, and establish as many useful {contacts} as possible.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. Đáp án: {accessories}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…not as many menswear, sportswear or <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">accessories</strong> designers. Opportunities might be greater in those categories.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài viết khuyên chọn những mảng ít người làm hơn quần áo (clothing), và “accessories” (phụ kiện) là một ví dụ được liệt kê.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. Đáp án: {fit}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Try to find the company that’s the <strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">right fit</strong> for you…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bạn nên tìm thực tập tại nơi mà bạn là một sự <strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">kết hợp phù hợp</strong> (good fit).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. Đáp án: {expense}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Of course that can lead to considerable <strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">expense</strong>, but it often results in success.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc tự mình mang hồ sơ ra nước ngoài có thể tốn kém một khoản <strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">chi phí</strong> (expense) đáng kể.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. Đáp án: {profile}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Create your <strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">profile</strong> on each one [online networking sites]…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để tác phẩm được nhìn thấy, bạn cần tạo <strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">hồ sơ</strong> (profile) trên các nền tảng kỹ thuật số.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Đáp án: {agencies}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Apply to as many fashion hiring <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">agencies</strong> as you can…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Specialist agencies” chính là các đại lý tuyển dụng chuyên về mảng thời trang.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. Đáp án: {training}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Consider your <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">training</strong> and fill in any gaps in it.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Review your training” đồng nghĩa với việc xem xét lại quá trình đào tạo của bản thân để bổ sung những kỹ năng còn thiếu (như CAD).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Đáp án: {contacts}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “It’s all down to developing new <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">contacts</strong> and utilising the ones you already have.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đừng chỉ dựa vào tài năng (ability), hãy thiết lập nhiều <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">mối quan hệ</strong> (contacts) hữu ích nhất có thể.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3f3a6932-6fc6-42c7-b29d-4a90f055e644', '59db2669-a42a-49f1-8758-619030c8cfdb', 'matrix', 'Questions 28–36', '', '<p data-start="176" data-end="243">Write the correct letter, A–G, in boxes 28–36 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p data-start="245" data-end="290"><strong data-start="245" data-end="251">NB</strong> You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "a map which indicates land ownership", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "a meeting which suggests knowledge of a large geographical area", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "a portable map used for sea travel", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "a mapmaker’s knowledge of astronomy", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "a goal shared by ancient and modern mapmakers", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "a map with a different orientation to modern maps", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "the first mapmakers’ symbols to represent military features", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "the first attempt to produce a map of the world", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "the first map to recognise that the earth was not flat", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. A map which indicates land ownership — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…real estate maps… privately-owned fields, each recorded with the name of the owner…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Land ownership” (quyền sở hữu đất đai) tương ứng với cụm “privately-owned fields” và “name of the owner”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. A meeting which suggests knowledge of a large geographical area — {E}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Aristagoras went to Sparta… to persuade the king… map showed areas representing the present-day Balkans, Greece, Cyprus, Turkey and Iran.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cuộc gặp gỡ giữa Aristagoras và vua Sparta cho thấy họ có kiến thức về một khu vực địa lý rộng lớn (từ Balkans đến Iran).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. A portable map used for sea travel — {A}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The smaller charts were carried by the islanders in their <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">canoes</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Portable” (có thể mang theo) tương ứng với “carried”, và “sea travel” (du hành biển) tương ứng với việc sử dụng “canoes” (xuồng).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. A mapmaker’s knowledge of astronomy — {F}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…he was the first to realize that the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">earth revolves around the sun</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Kiến thức về việc Trái Đất quay quanh Mặt Trời thuộc về lĩnh vực thiên văn học (astronomy).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. A goal shared by ancient and modern mapmakers — {G}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Modern mapmakers… share with these early mapmakers the <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">desire to produce images that give a picture of the way the world is</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Goal” (mục tiêu) chính là mong muốn (desire) mô tả thế giới đúng như nó vốn có.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. A map with a different orientation to modern maps — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Instead of placing north at the top as modern maps do, this map places <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">east at the top</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Orientation” (sự định hướng) của bản đồ cổ này lấy hướng Đông làm chuẩn thay vì hướng Bắc như hiện nay.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. The first mapmakers’ symbols to represent military features — {B}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…showing the <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">defences</strong> of the kingdom… Army camps were shown as red and black rectangles… fortresses, supply depots and observation towers.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các biểu tượng (symbols) như hình chữ nhật đỏ đen đại diện cho doanh trại quân đội và pháo đài (military features).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. The first attempt to produce a map of the world — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The Babylonians may have been the <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">first to produce a map of the world</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khớp hoàn toàn với câu hỏi về nỗ lực đầu tiên tạo ra bản đồ thế giới.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. The first map to recognise that the earth was not flat — {F}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…used the mathematics of the circle to draw maps that showed the <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">curved surface of the earth</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Curved surface” (bề mặt cong) đồng nghĩa với việc công nhận Trái Đất không phẳng (not flat).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bdd9b3b1-9e17-46fa-aec3-d8a384c834da', '59db2669-a42a-49f1-8758-619030c8cfdb', 'matching', 'Questions 37–40', '', '<p data-start="810" data-end="872">Look at the following statements and the list of places below.</p>
<p data-start="874" data-end="923">Match each statement with the correct place, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>J</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="925" data-end="992">Write the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>J</strong>, in boxes 37–40 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_name', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "Sparta"}, {"optionText": "the Arctic"}, {"optionText": "the Pacific"}, {"optionText": "Persia"}, {"optionText": "the Middle East"}, {"optionText": "Mexico"}, {"optionText": "China"}, {"optionText": "Babylon"}, {"optionText": "Egypt"}, {"optionText": "Greece"}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "The first known maps were made here.", "correctAnswer": "E"}, {"questionPart": "Maps made here included shells and coral to indicate dry land.", "correctAnswer": "C"}, {"questionPart": "The location of mineral resources was shown on a map made here.", "correctAnswer": "I"}, {"questionPart": "An official mapmaker always travelled with the royal party here.", "correctAnswer": "G"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. The first known maps were made here. — {E} the Middle East</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“However, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">earliest direct evidence of mapmaking comes from the Middle East</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “First known maps” tương ứng với “earliest direct evidence”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. Maps made here included shells and coral to indicate dry land. — {C} the Pacific</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The Marshall Islanders of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">Pacific</strong>… shells and coral were inserted… to symbolize islands.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Vỏ sò và san hô đại diện cho các hòn đảo (đất khô giữa biển).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. The location of mineral resources was shown on a map made here. — {I} Egypt</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…an <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">Egyptian</strong> map of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">gold mines</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mỏ vàng (gold mines) chính là tài nguyên khoáng sản (mineral resources).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. An official mapmaker always travelled with the royal party here. — {G} China</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…a <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">royal geographer</strong> always accompanied the emperor on tours of his empire…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Royal geographer” (nhà địa lý hoàng gia) là người làm bản đồ chính thức, “accompanied the emperor” tương ứng với việc đi cùng đoàn của nhà vua.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b5779e9e-9d0e-4177-979f-f8f50aecd8c4', '13e9a725-cd54-4b54-a0af-f292c3d1193e', 'matrix', 'Questions 14–18', NULL, '<p>The reading passage has seven paragraphs, <strong>A-G.</strong></p>
<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
<p>Write the correct letter, <strong>A-G,</strong> in boxes 14-19 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p>NB You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "a weakness in some of Goya''s paintings", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "a reason that might explain why some artists did not enjoy painting portraits", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "a genre Goya did not paint", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "description of a reaction to a promotion", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": " a summary of the historical significance of Goya''s works", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">14. A weakness in some of Goya’s paintings</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>G</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “While <strong>not all his portraits are successful (some have a doll-like stiffness)</strong>, this is what Goya at his best could do…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả thừa nhận một <strong>điểm yếu</strong> (<em>weakness</em>) trong một số tác phẩm của Goya là sự cứng nhắc như búp bê (<em>doll-like stiffness</em>), cho thấy không phải bức chân dung nào của ông cũng thành công.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">15. A reason that might explain why some artists did not enjoy painting portraits</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>E</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…unlike Gainsborough, for example, he did not resent portraiture as an <strong>economically necessary chore that ate away at the time</strong> he could devote to higher art.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn E đưa ra lý do tại sao một số nghệ sĩ (như Gainsborough) không thích vẽ chân dung: họ coi đó là một <strong>công việc nhàm chán vì mục đích kinh tế</strong> (<em>economically necessary chore</em>) làm tiêu tốn thời gian dành cho nghệ thuật cao siêu hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">16. A genre Goya did not paint</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…there are <strong>no pure landscapes in Goya’s work</strong>, in that everything he ever painted deals with people.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn A khẳng định Goya <strong>không vẽ phong cảnh thuần túy</strong> (<em>no pure landscapes</em>). Mọi tác phẩm của ông đều tập trung vào con người.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">17. Description of a reaction to a promotion</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>D</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Не immediately spent some of his 15,000-reales salary on a <strong>two-wheeled gig</strong>… which he <strong>promptly crashed on his first outing</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Sau khi được bổ nhiệm làm phó giám đốc hội họa (thăng chức – <em>promotion</em>), Goya đã phản ứng bằng cách dùng lương mua ngay một chiếc xe ngựa hai bánh và nhanh chóng làm hỏng nó trong lần đầu cầm lái.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">18. A summary of the historical significance of Goya’s works</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “In the work of no other great portraitist are a <strong>nation’s people, history, traumas, folk traditions, and superstitions so comprehensively and relentlessly captured</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn A tóm tắt <strong>tầm quan trọng lịch sử</strong> (<em>historical significance</em>) của Goya, khẳng định tác phẩm của ông đã ghi lại một cách toàn diện lịch sử, con người và những biến động của đất nước Tây Ban Nha.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">19. (Câu hỏi bổ sung dựa trên Logic bảng Matrix) – A description of a technique used by Goya</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>E</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “When it came to clothing he allowed himself extraordinary freedom… sketched in <strong>thick impasto</strong>… from a distance, they coalesce into silks, braiding, and gauze.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn E mô tả chi tiết kỹ thuật vẽ của Goya, đặc biệt là cách ông xử lý trang phục bằng các lớp sơn dày (<em>impasto</em>) để tạo hiệu ứng từ xa.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a118c8f5-a08c-4c2b-a3ac-17c7c3340da7', 'e2cfb22b-fcdb-4358-b706-51e709554b50', 'radio', 'Questions 1–7', '', '<p data-start="105" data-end="307">Choose <strong data-start="112" data-end="120">TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong data-start="192" data-end="201">FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong data-start="258" data-end="271">NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "An inspection fee on fish oil was introduced in New York in 1818"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Samuel Judd argued that the inspection fee should exclude whale oil"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Judd had been in trouble with city officials before the inspection fee disagreement"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Many New Yorkers were interested in the court case at the time"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Traditionally, non-human creatures had been classified in one of three groups"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Generally speaking, ordinary people thought fish were the lowest form of life"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Whales were excluded from the Linnaean system in 1818"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-start=\"153\" data-end=\"168\"><strong data-start=\"156\" data-end=\"168\">1. FALSE</strong></h2>\n<p data-start=\"170\" data-end=\"198\"><strong data-start=\"170\" data-end=\"181\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 1, câu 2.</p>\n<p data-start=\"200\" data-end=\"299\"><strong data-start=\"200\" data-end=\"214\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"214\" data-end=\"217\">“The case involved an <strong data-start=\"239\" data-end=\"250\">old law</strong> requiring those who sold fish oil to pay a fee…”</p>\n<p data-start=\"301\" data-end=\"473\"><strong data-start=\"301\" data-end=\"316\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"316\" data-end=\"319\">Đề nói phí kiểm định được <em data-start=\"345\" data-end=\"365\">introduced in 1818</em>. Nhưng bài viết nói đó là <strong data-start=\"392\" data-end=\"403\">old law</strong> (luật cũ), tức không phải được ban hành vào năm 1818. Vì vậy → FALSE.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"475\" data-end=\"478\">\n<h2 data-start=\"480\" data-end=\"494\"><strong data-start=\"483\" data-end=\"494\">2. TRUE</strong></h2>\n<p data-start=\"496\" data-end=\"524\"><strong data-start=\"496\" data-end=\"507\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 1, câu 3.</p>\n<p data-start=\"526\" data-end=\"639\"><strong data-start=\"526\" data-end=\"540\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"540\" data-end=\"543\">“…claiming that no inspection was necessary because it was whale oil, and whales were not fish.”</p>\n<p data-start=\"641\" data-end=\"775\"><strong data-start=\"641\" data-end=\"656\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"656\" data-end=\"659\">Judd lập luận rằng vì đó là whale oil và cá voi không phải cá nên không cần đóng phí kiểm định. → Đúng với ý đề bài.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"777\" data-end=\"780\">\n<h2 data-start=\"782\" data-end=\"801\"><strong data-start=\"785\" data-end=\"801\">3. NOT GIVEN</strong></h2>\n<p data-start=\"803\" data-end=\"836\"><strong data-start=\"803\" data-end=\"814\">Vị trí:</strong> Không có thông tin.</p>\n<p data-start=\"838\" data-end=\"947\"><strong data-start=\"838\" data-end=\"853\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"853\" data-end=\"856\">Bài không đề cập việc Judd từng gặp rắc rối với chính quyền trước đó hay chưa. → NOT GIVEN.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"949\" data-end=\"952\">\n<h2 data-start=\"954\" data-end=\"968\"><strong data-start=\"957\" data-end=\"968\">4. TRUE</strong></h2>\n<p data-start=\"970\" data-end=\"998\"><strong data-start=\"970\" data-end=\"981\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 2, câu 2.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1000\" data-end=\"1090\"><strong data-start=\"1000\" data-end=\"1014\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"1014\" data-end=\"1017\">“The public debate in New York sparked off by the trial was sensational.”</p>\n<p data-start=\"1092\" data-end=\"1190\"><strong data-start=\"1092\" data-end=\"1107\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"1107\" data-end=\"1110\">“Public debate was sensational” → dư luận sôi nổi, nhiều người quan tâm. → TRUE.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"1192\" data-end=\"1195\">\n<h2 data-start=\"1197\" data-end=\"1211\"><strong data-start=\"1200\" data-end=\"1211\">5. TRUE</strong></h2>\n<p data-start=\"1213\" data-end=\"1241\"><strong data-start=\"1213\" data-end=\"1224\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 2, câu 4.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1243\" data-end=\"1360\"><strong data-start=\"1243\" data-end=\"1257\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"1257\" data-end=\"1260\">“…all non-human creatures had been organised according to the categories of birds, beasts and fish.”</p>\n<p data-start=\"1362\" data-end=\"1462\"><strong data-start=\"1362\" data-end=\"1377\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"1377\" data-end=\"1380\">Sinh vật không phải con người được chia thành 3 nhóm: birds, beasts, fish. → TRUE.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"1464\" data-end=\"1467\">\n<h2 data-start=\"1469\" data-end=\"1488\"><strong data-start=\"1472\" data-end=\"1488\">6. NOT GIVEN</strong></h2>\n<p data-start=\"1490\" data-end=\"1523\"><strong data-start=\"1490\" data-end=\"1501\">Vị trí:</strong> Không có thông tin.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1525\" data-end=\"1661\"><strong data-start=\"1525\" data-end=\"1540\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"1540\" data-end=\"1543\">Bài nói cá voi được xem là cá vì chúng bơi dưới biển. Không có thông tin nói cá là “lowest form of life”. → NOT GIVEN.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"1663\" data-end=\"1666\">\n<h2 data-start=\"1668\" data-end=\"1683\"><strong data-start=\"1671\" data-end=\"1683\">7. FALSE</strong></h2>\n<p data-start=\"1685\" data-end=\"1706\"><strong data-start=\"1685\" data-end=\"1696\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1708\" data-end=\"1793\"><strong data-start=\"1708\" data-end=\"1722\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"1722\" data-end=\"1725\">“…the Linnaean system controversially classified whales as mammals…”</p>\n<p data-start=\"1795\" data-end=\"1895\"><strong data-start=\"1795\" data-end=\"1810\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"1810\" data-end=\"1813\">Hệ thống Linnaeus không loại cá voi ra mà phân loại chúng là <strong data-start=\"1874\" data-end=\"1885\">mammals</strong>. → FALSE.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1f359482-f4aa-4f81-8d19-5098a9249f59', '13e9a725-cd54-4b54-a0af-f292c3d1193e', 'checkbox', 'Questions 19–20', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>statements are true about Goya’s tapestry cartoons?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "They featured lively civilians and labourers that he observed.", "correct": true}, {"option": "Individuals were portrayed without faces.", "correct": false}, {"option": "They were used to develop techniques for his future works.", "correct": true}, {"option": "People''s social standings were a secondary focus.", "correct": false}, {"option": "He avoided painting political controversies.", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">19. They featured lively civilians and labourers that he observed.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn B (Dòng 3-5)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…they do show types – the <strong>majos and majas</strong> who gave Madrid its street swagger, <strong>peasants</strong> and rich men, courting couples, singers, hunters, children…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> * Tác giả liệt kê một loạt các nhân vật dân dã như <strong>majos/majas</strong> (thanh niên đường phố Madrid) và <strong>peasants</strong> (nông dân).</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5,3,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,3,1,0,0\">Cụm từ “street swagger” (phong thái đường phố) và việc liệt kê các ngành nghề cho thấy đây là những <strong>dân thường và người lao động sinh động</strong> (<em>lively civilians and labourers</em>) mà Goya đã trực tiếp <strong>quan sát</strong> được khi sống ở Madrid.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">20. They were used to develop techniques for his future works.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn B (2 dòng cuối)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “But in them, Goya <strong>practised poses and groupings and a way of handling light</strong> on and around figures that was to be <strong>invaluable</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> * Đoạn văn khẳng định Goya đã <strong>thực hành</strong> (<em>practised</em>) các kỹ thuật về tạo dáng, sắp xếp bố cục nhóm và xử lý ánh sáng thông qua các bức vẽ thảm này.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7,3,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,3,1,0,0\">Từ <strong>“invaluable”</strong> (vô giá) nhấn mạnh rằng những kỹ năng này là nền tảng cực kỳ quan trọng, giúp ích cho sự nghiệp vẽ chân dung rực rỡ sau này của ông (<strong>future works</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d91cfb0e-ddec-4b0b-94a0-ffffec767320', '13e9a725-cd54-4b54-a0af-f292c3d1193e', 'checkbox', 'Questions 21–22', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>statements are true about Goya’s portraits?</p>', 'list_selection', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "His depiction of royalty was typical of the time."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "He was meticulous about the details when painting clothes."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "He generally avoided using the same pose."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "He paid very close attention to the background in his paintings."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "He did not believe in using the works of other artists as inspiration."}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">21. He generally avoided using the same pose.</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 36.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">·<span style=\"font: 7.0pt ''Times New Roman'';\">      </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Đáp án:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> C (Nếu xét theo thứ tự các ý trong câu hỏi)</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 36.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">·<span style=\"font: 7.0pt ''Times New Roman'';\">      </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Vị trí:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> Đoạn E (Dòng 5)</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 36.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">·<span style=\"font: 7.0pt ''Times New Roman'';\">      </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Dẫn chứng:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> “There is hardly any repetition in his poses (to help, he drew on prints of English portraits as well as classical statuary)…”</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 36.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">·<span style=\"font: 7.0pt ''Times New Roman'';\">      </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Giải thích:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> * Cụm từ “hardly any repetition” (hầu như không có sự lặp lại) đồng nghĩa với việc ông thường xuyên tránh (avoided) sử dụng cùng một tư thế cho các nhân vật khác nhau.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 36.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">·<span style=\"font: 7.0pt ''Times New Roman'';\">      </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Tác giả còn giải thích thêm là để tránh lặp lại, Goya đã chủ động nghiên cứu các bản in chân dung của Anh và tượng điêu khắc cổ điển để tìm kiếm sự mới mẻ.</span></p>\n<p><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">22. He paid very close attention to the background in his paintings.</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 36.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">·<span style=\"font: 7.0pt ''Times New Roman'';\">      </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Đáp án:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> D (Nếu xét theo thứ tự các ý trong câu hỏi)</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 36.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">·<span style=\"font: 7.0pt ''Times New Roman'';\">      </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Vị trí:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> Đoạn E (Dòng 7-8)</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 36.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">·<span style=\"font: 7.0pt ''Times New Roman'';\">      </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Dẫn chứng:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> “…and he defined them by the careful depiction of the space around them.”</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 36.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">·<span style=\"font: 7.0pt ''Times New Roman'';\">      </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Giải thích:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> * Trong hội họa, cụm từ “space around them” (không gian xung quanh nhân vật) chính là phần hậu cảnh (background).</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 36.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">·<span style=\"font: 7.0pt ''Times New Roman'';\">      </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Việc mô tả không gian này một cách “careful” (cẩn thận/kỹ lưỡng) cho thấy Goya dành sự chú ý rất lớn (paid very close attention) vào việc xử lý hậu cảnh để làm nổi bật và định nghĩa tính cách của người ngồi làm mẫu.</span></p>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f6251310-e774-4540-baaf-8abfb68fa99d', '13e9a725-cd54-4b54-a0af-f292c3d1193e', 'fillup', 'Questions 23–26', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Goya’s Artistic Duality</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Francisco Goya, in embracing the simplicity and truth in his art, masterfully navigated the delicate balance between idealism and reality. Among the many royal portraits of his career, his most significant {commission} was from Charles IV, in which he abandoned conventional majesty to faithfully reveal the monarch, whose depiction was later likened to a {butcher} . His subsequent royal paintings, including the 1815 unflattering portrait of Ferdinand VII, show that he was able to depict truth without jeopardizing his position.</p>
<p>However, Goya’s private portraiture revealed a different narrative, as exemplified by his 1820 double portrait with Dr. Arrieta, in which an ailing Goya is seen in the care of the good {doctor} . It serves as a testament to Goya’s pinnacle ability to portray humanity in both its finest and darkest moments, all while refraining from passing judgment; in the latter scenario, individuals may have to be dependent on the {kindness} of their fellow men.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">23. …his most significant {commission} was from Charles IV…</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>{commission}</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn F (Dòng 2)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “In the most important <strong>commission</strong> of his career, for example, the portrait of Charles IV and the royal family of 1800…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc đề cập đến việc vẽ chân dung gia đình Charles IV là một “commission” (bản hợp đồng/nhiệm vụ đặt hàng) quan trọng nhất trong sự nghiệp của Goya. Trong tóm tắt, từ “most significant” thay thế cho “most important”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">24. …whose depiction was later likened to a {butcher}.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>{butcher}</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn F (Dòng 5)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…a motley grouping (a French visitor had likened Charles and his queen Maria Luisa to a <strong>butcher</strong> and his wife) in fancy clothes.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Goya vẽ gia đình hoàng gia một cách thực tế đến mức một vị khách người Pháp đã so sánh vua Charles IV và hoàng hậu giống như một gã <strong>đồ tể</strong> (<em>butcher</em>) mặc quần áo sang trọng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">25. …in which an ailing Goya is seen in the care of the good {doctor}.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>{doctor}</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn G (Dòng 3-4)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…showing Goya with Dr Arrieta… the 73-year-old painter in the throes of a debilitating illness being tended by his <strong>doctor</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Trong bức chân dung kép năm 1820, Goya đang trong cơn bạo bệnh và được chăm sóc bởi người <strong>bác sĩ</strong> (<em>doctor</em>) của mình (Tiến sĩ Arrieta). Từ “doctor” xuất hiện trực tiếp trong văn bản để chỉ vai trò của Arrieta.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">26. …individuals may have to be dependent on the {kindness} of their fellow men.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>{kindness}</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn G (Dòng 6)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “If Ferdinand represents human malignity and Goya its frailty, then Arrieta stands for man’s innate <strong>kindness</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả đối lập sự độc ác của vua Ferdinand với lòng tốt bẩm sinh của con người được thể hiện qua bác sĩ Arrieta. Trong tóm tắt, ý nói rằng khi con người yếu đuối/bệnh tật, họ phải phụ thuộc vào <strong>lòng tốt</strong> (<em>kindness</em>) của đồng loại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d4761382-fe32-41f0-9c3a-4fa0139d68b5', '925555ea-9453-4ead-8d72-f1e6347e3a7d', 'radio', 'Questions 27-31', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B, C, or D.</p>
<p>Write the correct letter in boxes 27-31 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "It started earlier than previously thought."}, {"content": "Historians have overlooked its importance."}, {"content": "It impacts on research into the wider region."}, {"content": "Researchers have calculated its effects on the environment."}], "question": "In the first paragraph, what is the writer''s main point about migration to Patagonia?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "to challenge previous research"}, {"content": "to propose new areas to investigate"}, {"content": "to summarise a scholarly debate"}, {"content": "to suggest reasons for human migration"}], "question": "In the second paragraph, what is the writer''s purpose?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "compare it with another theory of migration."}, {"content": "evaluate the success of American migration."}, {"content": "criticise the speed of research into migration."}, {"content": "compare migration in different parts of the world."}], "question": "The writer refers to the \"late\" model in order to"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "Scholars support the idea of fast migrations."}, {"content": "It is too random to be a convincing theory."}, {"content": "South America was more habitable at an earlier time."}, {"option_text": "It is more consistent with the physical conditions of the land."}], "question": "What is the writer''s main point about the \"early model\"?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "It is much younger than researchers once estimated."}, {"content": "It provides supporting evidence for relatively early settlement."}, {"content": "Archaeologists believe the site is of questionable value."}, {"content": "Streams exposed the site, making new research possible."}], "question": "What does the writer suggest about the Monte Verde site?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">27. In the first paragraph, what is the writer’s main point about migration to Patagonia?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">C. It impacts on research into the wider region.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 1) “The earliest occupation of Patagonia carries </span><strong class=\"\">obvious implications for understanding when the North and South American continents were peopled</strong><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> because it gives a </span><strong class=\"\">baseline</strong><span class=\"\"> that all calculations…</span><span class=\"\"> must take into account.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Tác giả nhấn mạnh rằng việc nghiên cứu sự định cư sớm nhất ở Patagonia cung cấp một “baseline” (mốc cơ sở) quan trọng.</span><span class=\"\"> Mốc này giúp các nhà khoa học hiểu được toàn bộ quá trình con người di cư đến Bắc và Nam Mỹ (vùng rộng lớn hơn – </span><em class=\"\">wider region</em><span class=\"\">).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">28. In the second paragraph, what is the writer’s purpose?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">C. to summarise a scholarly debate.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 2) “However,</span> <strong class=\"\">fundamental disagreements developed</strong><span class=\"\"> concerning the length of time involved…</span><span class=\"\"> and the </span><strong class=\"\">debate is still with us today</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Mục đích của đoạn 2 là giới thiệu về sự bất đồng quan điểm giữa các học giả về thời gian con người bắt đầu định cư (người nói 20.</span><span class=\"\">000 năm,</span><span class=\"\"> người nói 8.</span><span class=\"\">000 năm).</span><span class=\"\"> Đây chính là hành động tóm tắt một cuộc tranh luận học thuật (</span><em class=\"\">scholarly debate</em><span class=\"\">).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">29. The writer refers to the ‘late’ model in order to</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">A. compare it with another theory of migration.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 3) “The late model demands a hypothetical migration…</span><span class=\"\"> many scholars now support the idea of an </span><strong class=\"\">early model</strong><span class=\"\"> that sees the migration as a less ordered migration,</span><span class=\"\"> and this is surely the </span><strong class=\"\">most realistic scenario</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Tác giả nhắc đến mô hình “muộn” (</span><em class=\"\">late model</em><span class=\"\">) chủ yếu để đặt nó cạnh mô hình “sớm” (</span><em class=\"\">early model</em><span class=\"\">) nhằm so sánh tính khả thi của chúng.</span><span class=\"\"> Tác giả cho rằng mô hình sớm thực tế hơn vì tính đến sự thích nghi dần dần với môi trường.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">30. What is the writer’s main point about the ‘early’ model?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">D. It is more consistent with the physical conditions of the land.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 3) “…</span><span class=\"\">this is surely the most realistic scenario as </span><strong class=\"\">migrants slowly adapted to the diverse natural habitats</strong><span class=\"\"> they would have met while travelling through the continent.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Điểm chính của mô hình “sớm” là nó phù hợp với thực tế địa lý và sinh học,</span><span class=\"\"> cho phép con người có thời gian thích nghi với các môi trường sống đa dạng khi di chuyển qua lục địa,</span><span class=\"\"> thay vì một làn sóng di cư nhanh chóng nhưng phi lý.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">31. What does the writer suggest about the Monte Verde site?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">B. It provides supporting evidence for relatively early settlement.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 4) “Nevertheless,</span><span class=\"\"> evidence for human occupation…</span><span class=\"\"> is now </span><strong class=\"\">securely dated to around 12,500 years ago at the Monte Verde site, which casts doubt on the late model</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Vì địa điểm Monte Verde có bằng chứng xác thực về con người từ 12.500 năm trước (vượt qua mốc 8.000 năm của mô hình muộn), nó đóng vai trò là bằng chứng ủng hộ cho lý thuyết định cư sớm (<em>early settlement</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('993bb8a6-3b5f-42f2-8846-8611588282fe', '09f1bdc2-7122-419c-8416-000c0ad0f7e0', 'matrix', 'Questions 31–35', '', '<p>Look at the following statements (Questions 31–35) and the list of people below.</p>
<p>Match each statement with the correct person,<strong> A–E.</strong></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Those children who are not part of the project have poorer social skills than those who are", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "A goal of the project is to enable children to express both agreement and disagreement", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "An excess of toys can lead to irritation in a child", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "People working in education may fail to appreciate the importance of children deciding themselves how to fill their time", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "People working in education may fail to appreciate the importance of children deciding themselves how to fill their time", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Gisela Marti", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Gudrun Huber", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Elke Schubert", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Klaus’s father", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "Elsa Davies", "categoryLetter": "E"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. Đáp án: {C} Elke Schubert</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “We find that children on the project… <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">communicate better than the children who didn’t take part</strong>.” (Đoạn 8)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Elke Schubert khẳng định trẻ tham gia dự án có kỹ năng giao tiếp tốt hơn những trẻ không tham gia (đồng nghĩa với việc trẻ không tham gia có kỹ năng kém hơn).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. Đáp án: {A} Gisela Marti</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The aim is to make the children… able to <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">say “yes” as well as “no”</strong>…” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khả năng nói “có” và “không” tương ứng với việc thể hiện sự đồng ý (agreement) và phản đối (disagreement).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. Đáp án: {D} Klaus’s father (Trong bài là mẹ của Klaus – đề bài có thể nhầm lẫn nhẹ về danh xưng nhưng đáp án nhắm vào gia đình Klaus)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Klaus used to… spread them all over the room… he gets <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">much less frustrated</strong> [now that we put them away].” (Đoạn 9)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc có quá nhiều đồ chơi làm Klaus bừa bãi và không chơi tử tế, dẫn đến sự bực bội (irritation/frustrated).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Đáp án: {E} Elsa Davies</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Teachers often <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">underestimate the power of that learning</strong> [freely chosen by the child].” (Đoạn cuối)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các nhà giáo dục thường đánh giá thấp (fail to appreciate) sức mạnh của việc trẻ tự chọn cách sử dụng thời gian của mình.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. Đáp án: {B} Gudrun Huber</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Initially it was <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">difficult for the staff</strong>, not just because it was unbearably noisy, but because… it was <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">difficult to hold back and let the children be</strong>.” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_70edbda4c1daf9a6-21\" data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"citation-5 citation-end-5\"> Gudrun Huber thừa nhận lúc đầu nhân viên rất khó để kìm chế và để trẻ tự do làm gì chúng muốn.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"3\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('85f86dd0-1559-4d02-9df7-19fae1650964', '925555ea-9453-4ead-8d72-f1e6347e3a7d', 'radio', 'Questions 32-35', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES </strong>if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The conditions encountered by the first migrants to Patagonia were unique."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In the high country the first migrants hunted wild animals for food."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Archaeologists have failed to draw conclusions from the evidence found at rock shelters in Argentina and Chile."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Archaeological evidence can be moved from place to place in a variety of ways."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">32. The conditions encountered by the first migrants to Patagonia were unique.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…allowed the initial human intrusion into a pristine environment, which was <strong>similar to that of early post-glacial Europe</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc cho biết môi trường nguyên sơ mà những người di cư đầu tiên gặp phải tại Patagonia <strong>tương tự</strong> (<em>similar</em>) như ở Châu Âu thời kỳ đầu hậu kỷ băng hà. Văn bản không khẳng định những điều kiện này là “duy nhất” (<em>unique</em>) hay chưa từng có ở nơi nào khác trên thế giới.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">33. In the high country the first migrants hunted wild animals for food.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “Human settlement of the vast horizontal expanse of treeless high country must have been tenuous at best, and the evidence for this occupation remains relatively scant…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Mặc dù bài đọc có nhắc đến việc tìm thấy xương động vật ở một số địa điểm khác (như Las Buitreras), nhưng tại khu vực <strong>vùng cao</strong> (<em>high country</em>), bằng chứng về sự cư trú rất ít ỏi (<em>scant</em>). Tác giả không đề cập cụ thể liệu những người di cư ở vùng này có săn bắt động vật hoang dã để làm thức ăn hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">34. Archaeologist have failed to draw conclusions from the evidence found at rock shelters in Argentina and Chile.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…most of it coming from rock shelters in Argentina and Chile. There is, however, <strong>reliable evidence from these sites to confirm the presence of humans</strong> by around 11,000 years ago in different habitats…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói các nhà khảo cổ đã “thất bại” (<em>failed</em>) trong việc đưa ra kết luận. Tuy nhiên, bài đọc khẳng định đã có <strong>bằng chứng đáng tin cậy</strong> từ các mái đá này để <strong>xác nhận</strong> sự hiện diện của con người cách đây khoảng 11.000 năm. Vì thông tin trong bài bác bỏ ý kiến “thất bại”, đáp án là <strong>NO</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">35. Archaeological evidence can be moved from place to place in a variety of ways.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…anthropologists have come to recognise that bones or other evidence may be <strong>deposited in caves by natural agency, in other words by other forces such as floods or predators</strong>, and not necessarily by humans.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc xác nhận rằng các bằng chứng khảo cổ (như xương) có thể được đưa vào hang động bởi các <strong>tác nhân tự nhiên</strong> (<em>natural agency</em>) như <strong>lũ lụt hoặc động vật săn mồi</strong> (<em>floods or predators</em>). Điều này đồng nghĩa với việc bằng chứng có thể bị di chuyển từ nơi này sang nơi khác bằng nhiều cách khác nhau, đúng với khẳng định của câu hỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f22bab8a-7a07-40e2-b969-8d86e2617385', '925555ea-9453-4ead-8d72-f1e6347e3a7d', 'matching', 'Questions 36-40', NULL, '<p>Complete the summary using the list of words and phrases, A-J, below.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The archaeological evidence from Patagonia</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br>Building remains and other evidence have been found in {D good condition} at the Chinchihuapi Creek site, and because of this it has been possible to date them to around 12,500 years ago. However, the {B random collection} of the samples taken from Los Toldos means that this site is of doubtful value. El Ceibo is a more promising dig, where the examination of artefacts would be beneficial in order to confirm the usefulness of discoveries there. The remains found at the Arroyo Feo site show {C similar properties} and date from around 9,000 years ago. Unfortunately no {H reliable connection} can be made between the samples taken from Las Buitreras and human presence. The findings of the work carried out at Cueva Fell cannot provide useful information beyond the {J immediate surroundings} In conclusion, though the evidence is mixed, it is believed that human population of Patagonia began about 11,000 years ago.</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A fixed date"}, {"optionText": "B random collection"}, {"optionText": "C similar properties"}, {"optionText": "D good condition"}, {"optionText": "E scientific evaluation"}, {"optionText": "F huge quantities"}, {"optionText": "G new samples"}, {"optionText": "H reliable connection"}, {"optionText": "I skilled preservation"}, {"optionText": "J immediate surroundings"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">36. Building remains and other evidence have been found in <strong>D. good condition</strong> at the Chinchihuapi Creek site…</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>D. good condition</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 6 (Dòng 1-4)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “At the site located beside Chinchihuapi Creek, excavations have produced convincing evidence… They were buried in layers of peat, which has the property of <strong>preserving wood remarkably well</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc đề cập rằng các hiện vật bằng gỗ tại địa điểm này được bảo quản rất tốt nhờ lớp than bùn (<em>preserving wood remarkably well</em>). Điều này đồng nghĩa với việc chúng ở trong <strong>tình trạng tốt</strong> (<em>good condition</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">37. However, the <strong>B. random collection</strong> of the samples taken from Los Toldos means that this site is of doubtful value.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B. random collection</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 6 (Dòng 6-8)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the evidence from this site [Los Toldos] has recently been called into question, because dispersed flecks of carbon… were taken <strong>unsystematically from many different places</strong> in the site.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc lấy mẫu một cách <strong>không hệ thống</strong> (<em>unsystematically</em>) từ nhiều nơi khác nhau tương ứng với ý nghĩa của một <strong>bộ sưu tập ngẫu nhiên</strong> (<em>random collection</em>), làm cho giá trị của địa điểm này bị nghi ngờ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">38. The remains found at the Arroyo Feo site show <strong>C. similar properties</strong> and date from around 9,000 years ago.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C. similar properties</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 7 (Dòng 1-2)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The artefacts from the earliest occupations [at Arroyo Feo]… have the <strong>same origins as those from Los Toldos</strong>, and have been securely dated to around 9,000 years ago.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các hiện vật tại Arroyo Feo có cùng nguồn gốc (<em>same origins</em>) với các hiện vật tại Los Toldos, điều này đồng nghĩa với việc chúng có những <strong>đặc tính tương tự</strong> (<em>similar properties</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">39. Unfortunately no <strong>H. reliable connection</strong> can be made between the samples taken from Las Buitreras and human presence.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>H. reliable connection</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 7 (Dòng 4-6)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…at Las Buitreras… anthropologists now believe that presumed cut marks on the bones are somewhat dubious… there is <strong>no way of securely relating</strong> any of these remains with human occupation.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản khẳng định không có cách nào để <strong>liên hệ một cách chắc chắn</strong> (<em>no way of securely relating</em>) các di cốt động vật với sự hiện diện của con người. Cụm từ “reliable connection” (mối liên hệ đáng tin cậy) là cách diễn đạt tương đương.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">40. The findings of the work carried out at Cueva Fell cannot provide useful information beyond the <strong>J. immediate surroundings</strong>.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>J. immediate surroundings</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 7 (Dòng 7-9)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the utility of this site [Cueva Fell] must be <strong>restricted to its direct vicinity</strong>, given changes to the nearby area… and findings cannot be freely extrapolated further afield.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tính hữu dụng của địa điểm Cueva Fell bị giới hạn trong <strong>vùng lân cận trực tiếp</strong> (<em>direct vicinity</em>). Trong danh sách từ cho sẵn, “immediate surroundings” có nghĩa tương đồng hoàn toàn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c2b4de95-7d9d-4ddc-a4ef-6d9083008787', '7895d3f0-d719-4736-8972-f6b58efe438d', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–3', '<p data-path-to-node="3">Complete the notes below.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="4">Choose <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="7">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="5">Write your answers in boxes 1–3 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="6"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="0">In the 1500s, Borrowdale graphite</strong></span></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="7">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,0,0">was used by farmers in the area to indicate which {sheep} they owned</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,1,0">was first believed to be a type of {lead}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,2,0">was encased in string to produce early pencils</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,3,0">was recognised by the English {government} as important in the manufacture of cannon balls</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. sheep — {used by farmers… to indicate which sheep they owned}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Then, as now, Cumberland was a farming area, and the locals found the mineral useful for <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">marking their sheep</strong> so they could <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"144\">identify the ones that belonged to them</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “identify the ones that belonged to them” trong bài tương ứng với “indicate which [they] owned” trong câu hỏi. Người dân địa phương (nông dân) dùng graphite để đánh dấu những con cừu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"200\">sheep</strong>) của họ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. lead — {was first believed to be a type of lead}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">It was thought to be a form of lead</strong>, and so was referred to as plumbago…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “It was thought to be” tương ứng với “was first believed to be”. Ban đầu, người ta nhầm tưởng khoáng sản graphite này là một dạng của chì (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"151\">lead</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. government — {was recognised by the English government as important…}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In England, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">government</strong> soon <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">realised the value</strong> of the Borrowdale find, particularly for national defence purposes, because graphite proved ideal for lining the moulds used in the making of <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"214\">cannon balls</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Realised the value” tương ứng với “recognised… as important”. Chính phủ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">government</strong>) Anh đã nhận ra giá trị của graphite trong việc sản xuất đạn bác (cannon balls).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('35a9697d-cf96-44de-8492-943e0a311f22', 'f54d7991-0dfd-4665-b354-03c42cba86d8', 'fillup', 'Questions 15–21', '<p data-start="107" data-end="132">Complete the table below.</p>
<p data-start="134" data-end="247">Choose <strong data-start="141" data-end="158">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9971%; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0); height: 64.1719px;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8607%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 64.1719px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="254" data-end="286"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Types of training in business</strong></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9971%; height: 167.361px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 33.2869%;"> <col style="width: 33.2869%;"> <col style="width: 33.2869%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 33.4722px;">
<td style="text-align: center; border-color: #000000;">
<p><strong>Type of training</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="text-align: center; border-color: #000000;">
<p><strong>Aim</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="text-align: center; border-color: #000000;">
<p><strong>Examples</strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 33.4722px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p>Examples</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p>To teach technological aspects of the job</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p>Consulting: keeping a record of the <strong>{hours}</strong> workedRestaurants: dealing with computerised <strong>{orders}</strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 33.4722px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p>Quality</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p>To avoid the production of non-quality items</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p>Factory workers: identification of low-quality products and the appropriate action resulting in lower production costs and more effective <strong>{marketing}</strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 33.4722px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p>Skills</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p>To teach necessary proficiencies for the job</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p>Administrative assistant: using the <strong>{phone}</strong>Sales: evaluating the <strong>{needs}</strong> of clients and providing assistanceCashier: using a cash till and dealing with an incorrect <strong>{price}</strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 33.4722px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p>Soft skills</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p>To teach skills that affect human relationships</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p>Skills in communication, e.g. <strong>{listening}</strong>Retail/restaurants: interacting effectively with customers</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p data-start="134" data-end="247"> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Đáp án: {hours}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…input the number of <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">hours</strong> that should be charged to a client.” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong ngành tư vấn (consulting), đào tạo kỹ thuật giúp nhân viên biết cách nhập số <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">giờ</strong> làm việc để tính phí khách hàng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Đáp án: {orders}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…trained on how to process customers’ <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">orders</strong> using a tablet.” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tại nhà hàng, nhân viên cần biết dùng máy tính bảng để xử lý các <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">đơn hàng</strong> của khách.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Đáp án: {marketing}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…result in cost savings in production as well as provide an edge in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">marketing</strong> of the product.” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đào tạo chất lượng giúp nhận diện sản phẩm lỗi, từ đó giảm chi phí và giúp việc <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">tiếp thị/marketing</strong> hiệu quả hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Đáp án: {phone}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…an administrative assistant might be trained in how to answer the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">phone</strong>…” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ví dụ về đào tạo kỹ năng cho trợ lý hành chính là cách trả lời <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">điện thoại</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Đáp án: {needs}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…salesperson might be trained in assessment of customer <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">needs</strong>…” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nhân viên bán hàng cần được đào tạo để đánh giá <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">nhu cầu</strong> của khách hàng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Đáp án: {price}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…but what to do if something has been given the wrong <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">price</strong>.” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thu ngân cần biết xử lý tình huống khi một món hàng bị dán sai <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">mức giá</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. Đáp án: {listening}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…necessary soft skills, such as being good at different types of communication, including <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">listening</strong> to colleagues and customers.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một ví dụ điển hình của kỹ năng mềm trong giao tiếp chính là việc <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">lắng nghe</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('27f9b291-e15a-40c5-8bd8-22bb2af98194', 'f54d7991-0dfd-4665-b354-03c42cba86d8', 'fillup', 'Questions 22–27', '<article class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" tabindex="-1" data-turn-id="request-692808c1-5324-8321-9241-cf1905753e43-11" data-testid="conversation-turn-329" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant">
<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:--spacing(4)] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(6)] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(16)] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn" tabindex="-1">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="0168742f-d114-4f82-a0d1-7ea9e79f24e6" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-2">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling">
<p data-start="2109" data-end="2391" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">Complete the flow-chart below.</p>
<p data-start="2109" data-end="2391" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">Choose <strong data-start="147" data-end="164">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<div class="flex flex-col text-sm pb-25">
<article class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" tabindex="-1" data-turn-id="request-692808c1-5324-8321-9241-cf1905753e43-12" data-testid="conversation-turn-331" data-scroll-anchor="true" data-turn="assistant">
<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto pb-10 [--thread-content-margin:--spacing(4)] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(6)] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(16)] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn" tabindex="-1">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="66bde07b-e850-430b-b1c4-23fbfd7cac29" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-2">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling">
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="255" data-end="286"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>The small business lifecycle</strong></span></p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 148.156px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8573%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 148.156px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Stage 1 Initial Development</strong></p>
<p>Once you have your business idea, ask for different people’s {opinions} about it.</p>
<p>You need to be clear about what you can do, whether your idea will find a market, and where the finance will come from.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h1 style="text-align: center;" data-start="322" data-end="529">↓</h1>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 33.375px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8573%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 33.375px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Stage 2 Startup</strong></p>
<p>Remember that {mistakes} at this stage can affect the future success of the business.</p>
<p>Listen to what your customers say and be prepared to adapt your original idea.</p>
<p>Don’t worry if you are {confused} by all the changes at this stage.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h1 style="text-align: center;" data-start="322" data-end="529">↓</h1>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8573%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Stage 3 Establishment</strong></p>
<p>You should now be seeing a steady increase in profits.</p>
<p>The demands of this stage mean you must be good at managing your time.</p>
<p>It’s particularly important to be personally involved with {recruitment} and to build up an effective team with clear goals.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h1 style="text-align: center;" data-start="322" data-end="529">↓ </h1>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8573%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Stage 4 Expansion</strong></p>
<p>It’s important to expand but the risks involved must also be considered.</p>
<p>Careful planning is necessary to ensure that {quality} is not affected.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h1 style="text-align: center;" data-start="322" data-end="529">↓ </h1>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 33.375px; border-spacing: 2px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8573%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 33.375px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Stage 5 Maturity</strong></p>
<p>To maintain growth rates, it may be necessary for the company to have a different {leader}.</p>
<p>Another possibility is to sell the business.<br> </p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="mt-3 w-full empty:hidden"> </div>
</div>
</div>
</article>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="z-0 flex min-h-[46px] justify-start"> </div>
</div>
</div>
</article>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. Đáp án: {opinions}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…get as many <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">opinions</strong> as possible from friends, family, colleagues…” (Giai đoạn 1)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trước khi bắt đầu, bạn nên hỏi xin <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">ý kiến</strong> từ nhiều người khác nhau.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. Đáp án: {mistakes}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…since <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">mistakes</strong> made then can have an impact many years later.” (Giai đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cần nhớ rằng những <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">sai lầm</strong> ở giai đoạn khởi nghiệp có thể ảnh hưởng đến tương lai lâu dài.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. Đáp án: {confused}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…start to feel a bit <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">confused</strong> about what you’re doing. Don’t worry—this feeling will soon disappear…” (Giai đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đừng lo lắng nếu bạn cảm thấy <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">bối rối</strong> do có quá nhiều sự thay đổi ở giai đoạn này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. Đáp án: {recruitment}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Employing the right people is essential, so you need to take a major part in <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">recruitment</strong>.” (Giai đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ở giai đoạn thiết lập, chủ doanh nghiệp cần trực tiếp tham gia vào việc <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"84\">tuyển dụng</strong> nhân sự.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. Đáp án: {quality}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…should keep an eye on how far expansion might affect the <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">quality</strong> of what you provide…” (Giai đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khi mở rộng, phải cẩn thận để không làm ảnh hưởng đến <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">chất lượng</strong> sản phẩm/dịch vụ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. Đáp án: {leader}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Many companies in this situation bring in a new <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">leader</strong> at this stage…” (Giai đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ở giai đoạn trưởng thành, để duy trì tăng trưởng, công ty có thể cần một người <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">lãnh đạo</strong> mới.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('47d28bcf-4c75-433f-bdb2-724323f9c197', '09f1bdc2-7122-419c-8416-000c0ad0f7e0', 'radio', 'Questions 28–30', '', '<p>Choose the correct answers</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A the length of time children spend there"}, {"option_text": "B the number of arguments children have there"}, {"option_text": "C the lack of physical space for children’s play there"}, {"option_text": "D the amount of organisation children are exposed to there"}], "question": "What does Gisela Marti criticise about nurseries in the third paragraph?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A learn how to reduce it"}, {"option_text": "B adjust their response to it"}, {"option_text": "C explore what causes it"}, {"option_text": "D agree when to avoid it"}], "question": "When talking about danger, Gisela Marti suggests that teachers may have to"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A They were impatient to get them back"}, {"option_text": "B They had not expected to get them back"}, {"option_text": "C They had lost interest in getting them back"}, {"option_text": "D They had mixed feelings about getting them back"}], "question": "How did the children feel about getting their toys back?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. Đáp án: {D} the amount of organisation children are exposed to there</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_70edbda4c1daf9a6-19\" data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"citation-7\"> “the children’s day is </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\"><span class=\"citation-7\">deliberately unstructured</span></strong><span class=\"citation-7\"> as one of the basic beliefs of the project is that children spend too much time being </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"146\"><span class=\"citation-7\">rushed around from one activity to another</span></strong><span class=\"citation-7 citation-end-7\">…” (Đoạn 3)<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_70edbda4c1daf9a6-20\" data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"citation-6 citation-end-6\"> Gisela Marti chỉ trích việc trẻ em bị ép vào một thời gian biểu quá chặt chẽ (rushed around from one activity to another).<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"2\"><!----></sup></span> Điều này tương ứng với việc trẻ bị tiếp xúc với quá nhiều sự tổ chức/sắp đặt (organisation).</p>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. Đáp án: {B} adjust their response to it</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Everyone has to work within <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">their own boundaries</strong> and some teachers will allow more dangerous and active play than others.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Marti gợi ý rằng mỗi giáo viên có một giới hạn riêng và họ cần điều chỉnh cách phản ứng (adjust their response) đối với những trò chơi nguy hiểm tùy theo mức độ tự tin và ranh giới cá nhân của họ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. Đáp án: {D} They had mixed feelings about getting them back.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The children were <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">happy to get their toys back</strong>, but they were <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">also aware that they had fun without them</strong>.” (Đoạn 7)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trẻ em vừa vui khi có lại đồ chơi, nhưng cũng vừa nhận ra rằng không có chúng vẫn rất vui. Đây chính là trạng thái cảm xúc hỗn hợp (mixed feelings).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b4e69fbb-e1f6-4e1c-abf9-1e84d44f582e', '7895d3f0-d719-4736-8972-f6b58efe438d', 'radio', 'Questions 4–8', '', '<p data-path-to-node="12,0,0">Choose<strong data-path-to-node="12,0,0" data-index-in-node="0"> TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information,<strong data-path-to-node="12,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information,<strong data-path-to-node="12,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Borrowdale graphite was superior to all other forms of graphite."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Pencil production in the Borrowdale area only lasted until the 1860s."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Cumberland pencil museum contains examples of pencils from different European countries."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "A technique which improved on the Bernacottis'' method of making pencils is still used now."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In 1662, manufacturers in Nuremberg made pencils with graphite imported from England."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Borrowdale graphite was superior to all other forms of graphite. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Although deposits of graphite existed in other parts of the world, they were <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">not of the same exceptional purity and quality as Borrowdale graphite</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định các mỏ graphite khác không có được độ tinh khiết và chất lượng đặc biệt như ở Borrowdale. Điều này đồng nghĩa với việc graphite ở Borrowdale vượt trội (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"183\">superior</strong>) hơn hẳn các loại khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Pencil production in the Borrowdale area only lasted until the 1860s. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The town of Keswick, <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">close to the Cumberland graphite find, still manufactures pencils today</strong>, the factory also being the location of the Cumberland pencil museum.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói rằng vào những năm 1860, thiết kế bút chì có sự thay đổi (modified), nhưng việc sản xuất tại khu vực này (thị trấn Keswick gần mỏ Borrowdale) <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"166\">vẫn tiếp tục cho đến ngày nay</strong> (still manufactures pencils today). Vì vậy, nói nó chỉ kéo dài đến những năm 1860 là sai.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. The Cumberland pencil museum contains examples of pencils from different European countries. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…the factory also being the location of the Cumberland pencil museum.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến sự tồn tại của bảo tàng bút chì Cumberland tại nhà máy, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">không hề cung cấp thông tin</strong> về việc bảo tàng này có trưng bày các mẫu bút chì từ các quốc gia châu Âu khác hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. A technique which improved on the Bernacottis’ method of making pencils is still used now. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Shortly thereafter, a <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">superior technique to that of the Bernacottis was adopted</strong>: two wooden halves were carved, a graphite stick inserted, and the halves then glued together – <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">essentially the same method in use to this day</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc mô tả một kỹ thuật ưu việt hơn (superior technique/improved on) cách của nhà Bernacottis (ghép hai nửa gỗ lại với nhau) và khẳng định phương pháp này về cơ bản vẫn được sử dụng cho đến ngày nay (in use to this day).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. In 1662, manufacturers in Nuremberg made pencils with graphite imported from England. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The first attempt to manufacture graphite sticks from powdered graphite was in <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">Nuremberg, Germany, in 1662</strong>, using a mixture of graphite together with the elements sulphur and antimony.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến sự kiện sản xuất lõi bút chì từ bột graphite tại Nuremberg vào năm 1662, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"111\">không hề nói rõ</strong> nguồn gốc của loại graphite đó có phải được nhập khẩu từ Anh (imported from England) hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d20b460a-6f29-4153-85be-20854e0860b2', 'ce575363-0ba6-4207-9704-02a1d7dbcaa6', 'fillup', 'Questions 1-10', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Information about School Registration</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Grade Level:</strong> kindergarten<br><strong>School:</strong> {Monterey} Heights Elementary School<br><strong>Registration:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Monday to Thursday from 9.00 to 1.30</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Can pick up packet from the school {library}  any afternoon up to 5.00</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Forms:</strong> Immunisation records</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Heal forms from doctor and {dentist}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Emergency contact information</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Residency verification form</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Original birth certificate</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Childcare:</strong> No {transportation} is provided</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>There is on-site licensed daycare for working {parents}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>This is organised by the City {Youth} Council</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Orientation:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Open house in July – details provided through the {mail} and on the school’s website</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Will tour the school, meet the {teacher} and schedule entrance testing</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Schedule:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>First day of school will be on {August 19|August 19th |19 August |19th August}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>First week is 8.00 to 12.30</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Regular schedule is 8.00 to {2.05|2:05}</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 1</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Good afternoon Lemon Grove School District.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Hi, I&#8217;m calling for information on school registration. I think my son should attend one of the schools in your district.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> What grade will your son be entering?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> He just turned 5. He&#8217;ll be starting school this year.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Oh okay. Um, one moment please. I&#8217;ll get the information for kindergarten registration.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Okay, thank you.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Uh, can you give me your address?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Yes, it&#8217;s 7 4 1 8 Dimarino street.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Okay thanks. Yes, at that address, your child should attend <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">(1) Monterey</strong></span> Heights Elementary.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Can you spell that please?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Yes, it&#8217;s M-O-N-T-E-R-E-Y heights.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Great. So how do I register him?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> We have registration at each school site Monday through Thursday from 9 to 1. Oh no sorry, 1:30. You&#8217;ll need to pick up a kindergarten registration packet from the school beforehand though. It has all the forms you&#8217;ll need to fill out.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Can I pick up the packet anytime?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Sure, the school office is usually open till 3:30 in the afternoons. Oh no, I can&#8217;t really get there that early. Well, the school has late office hours until 4 on Thursdays, or I think you can pick up a packet in the school <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"234\">(2) library</strong></span> any day before 5.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Oh okay. I&#8217;ll stop by there some day this week then before 5. Can you tell me what forms we&#8217;ll need?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> I&#8217;m sure you need his immunization records.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Yes those.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> And we also need a general health history signed by your child&#8217;s doctor, a form filled out by the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">(3) dentist</strong></span>, emergency contact information, and a residency verification form with proof of residence. Oh, and an original birth certificate.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> OK that shouldn&#8217;t be a problem. Can I ask one more question?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Sure, go ahead.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> I was wondering about before and after school care. Do you provide <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">(4) transportation</strong></span> after school?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> No unfortunately, we don&#8217;t. Parents or caregivers need to pick up the children. There is however, an on-site licensed daycare for working <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"148\">(5) parents</strong></span> who need after school care for their children. It&#8217;s housed within the school grounds and someone from the daycare will walk to the main school building to pick up your child each day. It&#8217;s run by the city <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"365\">(6) Youth</strong></span> Council and comes highly recommended.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Can I get information about that as well?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Yes, uh, flyers and contact information will be included with your packet.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Okay thank you.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Oh and one more thing. I saw a flyer recently for an introduction event for new students and parents—an open house I think it was called, but I can&#8217;t remember the date. Was it August 3rd?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> That must have been last year&#8217;s flyer. We haven&#8217;t put out information on this year&#8217;s open house yet, but it&#8217;ll probably be sometime in August. Ah no, actually it will be in July this year, since school starts a little early this year. Once your child is registered, you&#8217;ll get all that information in the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"315\">(7) mail</strong></span> and it&#8217;ll be on the school website as well.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Great. I&#8217;m assuming that during the open house we get to tour the school and meet our child&#8217;s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">(8) teacher</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Yes and you will set up a time for kindergarten entrance testing as well.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Wow, testing already. That starts early.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Well we want to make sure children are properly placed and qualified for special services if necessary.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Okay, I guess that makes sense. Oh, and the first day of school?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> The first day will be <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">(9) August 19</strong></span>. We start in the middle of the week to help with the adjustment. And for kindergartners, the first three days are half days from 8 to 12:30.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Oh okay.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"39\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"39\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> And then the next week the regular schedule, 8:00 to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"39\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">(10) 2:05</strong></span> will be in force.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"40\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"40\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Yes, and you can access the full school calendar of holidays and breaks on the school website. Oh yeah, I&#8217;ve seen that. The website is very helpful. Thank you so much for your time.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"41\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"41\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> You&#8217;re welcome sir.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b4bfe230-44fd-4346-a31b-b37ddfc07155', 'd42308ff-3867-4d32-ac6e-1fd1e0ecdf85', 'radio', 'Questions 11–14', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>The McFaddin hiking and nature trail</strong></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "provide secure parking facilities from cars."}, {"content": "are within easy access from public roads."}, {"content": "have a regular shuttle bus service."}], "question": "All entry points along the trail"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "electric recharge points"}, {"content": "picnic areas"}, {"content": "maps and other information"}], "question": "Which facilities at the trail rest stations has been added as a result of a user survey?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "see many different plants."}, {"content": "enjoy spectacular scenic views."}, {"content": "identify a wide range of birds."}], "question": "On the Red Rock Walk, hikers are easily able to"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "There are not many other walkers in the area."}, {"content": "The area does not get much ice and snow."}, {"content": "It may not be possible to use this section of the trail."}], "question": "What does the speaker say about the River Walk in wintertime?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 2</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Susan Meyer:</strong> Good morning. I&#8217;m Susan Meyer, trail warden for the McFadden Hiking and Nature Trail. Let me tell you a bit about the trail. The trail is 25 miles long, running roughly east to west. To hike it, you may start at either end of the trail or in between. You can hike the whole length of the trail or just a couple of miles, because <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"342\">(11) there are 20 entry points along the trail, each connected to public roads by short paths (B)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">For hikers coming from Johnson City, there&#8217;s a shuttle bus to each of the two end points every morning and evening, and four of the entry points have a free car park with television camera surveillance. At 1 mile intervals along the trail, there are rest stations providing picnic areas, water, toilets, and places where you can recharge your electronic devices. In response to a poll of walkers last year, we&#8217;ve <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"413\">(12) recently installed kiosks at each rest station with clear, easy to follow maps and other trail information (C)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">There are several distinct sections of trail. The Red Rock Walk offers a superb opportunity to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">(13) study a huge variety of vegetation along the way (A: see many different plants)</strong>.</span> There&#8217;s lots to look at, though you can&#8217;t see great distances. Birds are actually hard to spot, but with a pair of binoculars and at certain times of day, you may see some rare varieties.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">The River Walk comprises about 5 miles of trail, winding along the bank of the Moultrie River. Personally, I prefer this section of the trail in winter. The river does freeze over and the snow can accumulate, but that doesn&#8217;t always discourage visitors. Sometimes though, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"272\">(14) if the weather conditions are really unsuitable, we might have to close this walk to the public (C: It may not be possible to use this section)</strong></span>, but often it can get crowded with hikers who&#8217;ve discovered the attraction of the area.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Susan Meyer:</strong> Now let me tell you about the Halfway Hostel, located approximately midway along the trail. It has a range of facilities available to help make your walking experience memorable. Let me give you some information about the various facilities available there.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">Of course, there are beds in dormitories for use at a very reasonable $7 per person, weekdays or weekends. Unfortunately, we found that pre-booking beds just didn&#8217;t work, so <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"174\">(15) now we allocate them as people arrive (H: first-come-first-served basis)</strong></span>, but we have extra cots and sleeping bags to help with any overflow.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">There are two family rooms accommodating six people, each with private bathrooms. They are $35 per room and for them, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">(16) you will need to make arrangements ahead of time (F: advance booking required)</strong></span> as they&#8217;re very popular, especially at the weekends.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">A popular facility that <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">(17) we&#8217;ve recently added is coin-operated washing machines (G: new equipment)</strong></span> for your clothes. You can get awfully wet and dirty if you&#8217;re walking the trail in bad weather, and since we got these machines, you can put on clean gear when you set out in the morning.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">The hostel serves two meals a day—breakfast at $4 and dinner at $8, the same for adults and kids. There&#8217;s always a vegetarian and a non-vegetarian option, depending on your preferences. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"186\">(18) We do ask you to give a hand with serving and cleaning up after meals (D: help from guests requested)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">We have plenty of showers and unlimited hot water available, so <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">(19) you can have this luxury at no charge (E: provided free)</strong></span>, and you can enjoy it as long as you like.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">Now, some people like to spend time on the trail on mountain bikes, and maybe take a bit of a rest from all that walking, and that&#8217;s permitted as long as you observe basic safety rules. The hostel&#8217;s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"199\">(20) in the process of creating a bike rental scheme, which should be up and running next year (C: not yet available)</strong></span>. So if you think that&#8230;</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('84e69056-61b4-467b-9c12-3428aa7dab39', 'd42308ff-3867-4d32-ac6e-1fd1e0ecdf85', 'matching', 'Questions 15–20', NULL, '<p>Which information is given about each of the following facilities at the Halfway Hostel?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>SIX </strong>correct answers, <strong>A-I</strong>, next to questions <strong>15-20</strong>.</p>
<p class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: left;"><strong>Information</strong></p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Facilities at the hostel</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>dormitory beds {H available on first-come-first-served basis}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>family rooms {F advance booking required}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>clothes washing {G new equipment}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>meals {D help from guests requested}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>hot showers {E provided free}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>bicycle rental {C not yet available}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A only at weekends"}, {"optionText": "B voluntary donation expected"}, {"optionText": "C not yet available"}, {"optionText": "D help from guests requested"}, {"optionText": "E provided free"}, {"optionText": "F advance booking required"}, {"optionText": "G new equipment"}, {"optionText": "H available on first-come-first-served basis"}, {"optionText": "I special rate for children"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3fbba78c-df65-4281-a798-217a86116d43', 'a4ae58d8-b9de-4958-bb58-3fa9b298af2f', 'matching', ' Questions 21–26', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>SIX</strong> correct answers, <strong>A-I</strong>, next to questions 21-26.</p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Environmental Science modules</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Statistics for environmental research {F was too basic to be useful}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Sewage and drainage systems {A was surprisingly interesting}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Agriculture and food security {C included out-of-date materials}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Sustainable energy {D involved practical applications}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Government policy {I seemed too limited geographically}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Water management {G provided unnecessary detail}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A was surprisingly interesting"}, {"optionText": "B covered too many topics"}, {"optionText": "C included out-of-date materials"}, {"optionText": "D involved practical applications"}, {"optionText": "E supplied useful technical information"}, {"optionText": "F was too basic to be useful"}, {"optionText": "G provided unnecessary detail"}, {"optionText": "H was relevant to a topic in the news"}, {"optionText": "I seemed too limited geographically"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 3</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jamie:</strong> Hi Martha, do you have time to talk? We have to submit our evaluations of our course next week, and I thought it’d be useful to discuss what we both think.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Martha:</strong> Good idea. That would help refresh my memory, especially about things we did in previous years.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jamie:</strong> I agree. So let’s talk about the modules we took. What about <strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">Statistics for environmental research</strong>? I’ve always been hopeless with numbers, so I thought that I’d learn a lot, but you know <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"195\">(21) it wasn’t at a high enough level for me (F: too basic to be useful)</strong></span>. I actually had to do a lot of reading on my own.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Martha:</strong> Me too. I had to get an additional reading list from the tutor. Now <strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">Sewage and drainage systems</strong>. I wasn’t looking forward to that one. Not exactly a pleasant subject, but you know, the module convinced me that it’s an essential topic to understand for both cities and rural environments.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jamie:</strong> Right, and in the end, not a boring subject?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Martha:</strong> Not at all. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">(22) It was quite a revelation (A: surprisingly interesting)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jamie:</strong> The module on <strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">Agriculture and food security</strong> could have been good, but <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">(23) the assigned readings were only those ancient government publications and the lecture notes clearly hadn’t been updated for years (C: out-of-date materials)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Martha:</strong> I know. What about the module on <strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">Sustainable energy</strong>? I really got into the project we had to do to invent something functional. I devised a windmill to power my laptop.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jamie:</strong> Yep, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"16\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\">(24) projects were great, so hands-on (D: involved practical applications)</span></strong>. Though the personal battery charger I built never really worked.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Martha:</strong> Too bad, but I’m sure you learned a lot nonetheless.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jamie:</strong> I did. And the <strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">Government policy</strong> module. I wish it had included policy in other countries. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">(25) It was a bit inward-looking, I thought, focused just on this country (I: too limited geographically)</strong></span>. I mentioned that to the lecturer, but she said it was best to concentrate on one country in depth at first, maybe.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Martha:</strong> And there was that module called <strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">Water management</strong>. I must admit I got lost in the discussion about the issues of groundwater levels and flood risk management, which <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"173\">(26) weren’t that essential (G: provided unnecessary detail)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jamie:</strong> You weren’t the only one.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jamie:</strong> Okay, I thought some aspects of the course organization were particularly helpful. Can we talk a bit about that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Martha:</strong> Of course. Actually, I was disappointed that I couldn’t take any module whenever I wanted.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jamie:</strong> That’s true, but <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">(27/28) the variety of modules on offer was a strong point (D)</strong></span> and meant I managed to cover a lot of subjects.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Martha:</strong> Me too, more than I expected. And I was pleased that the course organizers were able to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">(27/28) provide modules focusing on real-life issues (E)</strong></span>, which we can apply later when looking for jobs.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jamie:</strong> True, and I would have hated it if it had all been theory. What about the written paper we had to do for Doctor Brown? Are there any things we could suggest to improve the way that’s handled?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Martha:</strong> Well, choosing a topic right at the beginning of the module was difficult. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">(29/30) Maybe he could postpone the decision until halfway through the term (A)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jamie:</strong> Good idea. I was happy with the word limit for the assignment, though. I wish I could have had a session with Doctor Brown after he’d marked my written paper.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Martha:</strong> I know it would be time-consuming, but it would have been really useful. Actually, I was satisfied with Doctor Brown’s written feedback. But <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"149\">(29/30) I wish they could arrange sessions where students get together and help each other before submitting their written work (C)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jamie:</strong> Good idea. If they provided time for that, it would be quite convenient. Right, now that we’ve almost finished our course, it’s time to think about our career prospects…</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a66ff181-ca2a-4693-b33a-cd2513003e69', '09f1bdc2-7122-419c-8416-000c0ad0f7e0', 'fillup', 'Questions 36–40', '<p data-start="94" data-end="121">Complete the summary below.</p>
<p data-start="123" data-end="178">Choose <strong data-start="130" data-end="147">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 85.4494%; border-spacing: 2px; height: 261.078px; border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 100%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 261.078px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<div class="flex flex-col text-sm pb-25">
<article class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" tabindex="-1" data-turn-id="request-692808c1-5324-8321-9241-cf1905753e43-16" data-testid="conversation-turn-339" data-scroll-anchor="true" data-turn="assistant">
<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto pb-10 [--thread-content-margin:--spacing(4)] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(6)] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(16)] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn" tabindex="-1">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="faa26b4c-e270-4714-af25-8dfdc9ebb3da" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-2">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling">
<p style="text-align: center; padding-left: 40px;" data-start="246" data-end="283"><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">The ‘nursery without toys’ project</span></strong></p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;" data-start="285" data-end="465">On the first day of the project, a video shows that the children at the nursery did not know what to do in the <strong>{classroom}</strong> because it contained no toys.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;" data-start="467" data-end="567">The next day, they used tables, blankets and <strong>{shoes}</strong> to build a den.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;" data-start="569" data-end="661">The excitement of doing this changed their mood and resulted in a lot of noise and activity.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;" data-start="663" data-end="1012" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">According to Gisela Marti, once they had adapted to the new approach, they began to make up <strong>{games}</strong> and do shows. They might have imagined they were in the <strong>{circus}</strong>, for example, or travelling on a train. All these activities taught them how to <strong>{socialise | socialize}</strong> .</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</article>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. Đáp án: {classroom}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…looking apprehensively around the <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">big, empty classroom</strong>.” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_70edbda4c1daf9a6-22\" data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"citation-4 citation-end-4\"> Ngày đầu tiên, trẻ đứng nhìn quanh lớp học trống không một cách lo lắng.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"4\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. Đáp án: {shoes}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “They make a den by draping the blankets over the tables and <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">weighing them down with shoes</strong>…” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trẻ dùng bàn, chăn và giày (shoes) để dựng lều.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. Đáp án: {games}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…once the children settled down to the new regime, <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">they invented games</strong>…” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sau khi thích nghi, trẻ bắt đầu tự nghĩ ra các trò chơi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. Đáp án: {circus}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…pretending to be in a <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">circus</strong> or on a train…” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trẻ tưởng tượng mình đang ở rạp xiếc hoặc trên tàu hỏa.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. Đáp án: {socialise} (hoặc socialize)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…all the time they were playing, they were learning to <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">socialise</strong>.” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tất cả các hoạt động này giúp trẻ học cách giao lưu/hòa nhập xã hội.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3231d89a-764b-448c-9842-76e2362207dd', 'a4ae58d8-b9de-4958-bb58-3fa9b298af2f', 'checkbox', 'Questions 27–28', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>aspects of the course organisation did both Jamie and Martha like?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "the amount of reading", "correct": false}, {"option": "the flexibility in the length of the course", "correct": false}, {"option": "the convenience of choosing when take modules", "correct": false}, {"option": "the range of different modules offered", "correct": true}, {"option": "the relevance of the module content", "correct": true}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('121ba83b-3d99-454a-ae9a-eac6399f1741', 'a4ae58d8-b9de-4958-bb58-3fa9b298af2f', 'checkbox', 'Questions 29–30', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>suggestions for written assignment do Jamie and Martha agree to recommend to Dr Brown?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "The time for choosing a topic should be changed.", "correct": true}, {"option": "The permitted word limit should be increased.", "correct": false}, {"option": "Discussions with fellow students should be arranged.", "correct": true}, {"option": "Face-to-face feedback sessions with the tutor should be scheduled.", "correct": false}, {"option": "Tutors should give more help in topic selection.", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b1b458eb-b9fb-4fd0-b825-aaec8c18da23', 'debecac1-3181-47a7-9e71-fc63f28948c0', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–10', '<p data-start="116" data-end="194">Write <strong data-start="149" data-end="177">ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="201" data-end="258"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-start="205" data-end="258">Morgan Recruitment Agency – Request for new staff</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="260" data-end="295"><strong data-start="260" data-end="271">Example</strong></p>
<p data-start="260" data-end="295"><em>Name: <strong data-start="280" data-end="295">Peter Smith</strong></em></p>
<p data-start="297" data-end="316"><strong data-start="297" data-end="314">Phone number: </strong><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">{0478883925}</span></p>
<p data-start="332" data-end="375"><strong data-start="332" data-end="349">Company name: </strong>{Vander} Transport</p>
<p data-start="377" data-end="459"><strong data-start="377" data-end="397">Type of company: </strong>trucking company – transports a lot of {frozen} food</p>
<p data-start="461" data-end="510"><strong data-start="461" data-end="489">Date employees required: </strong>from {28th August|28 August | August 28th | August 28}</p>
<p data-start="517" data-end="540"> </p>
<p data-start="517" data-end="540"><strong data-start="521" data-end="540">Details of Jobs</strong></p>
<p data-start="542" data-end="560"><strong data-start="542" data-end="560">Office Manager</strong></p>
<ul data-start="561" data-end="639">
<li data-start="561" data-end="611">
<p data-start="563" data-end="611">experience working with supermarkets is needed</p>
</li>
<li data-start="612" data-end="639">
<p data-start="614" data-end="639">must have <span style="background-color: #ffffff;">a {degree}</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="641" data-end="653"><strong data-start="641" data-end="653">Mechanic</strong></p>
<ul data-start="654" data-end="780">
<li data-start="654" data-end="735">
<p data-start="656" data-end="735">duties involve repairing trucks and waiting<span style="background-color: #ffffff;"> a {report} for ev</span>ery vehicle</p>
</li>
<li data-start="736" data-end="780">
<p data-start="738" data-end="780">the job will not involve much travelling</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="782" data-end="798"><strong data-start="782" data-end="798">Truck Driver</strong></p>
<ul data-start="799" data-end="966">
<li data-start="799" data-end="828">
<p data-start="801" data-end="828">will cover long distances</p>
</li>
<li data-start="829" data-end="911">
<p data-start="831" data-end="911">will need to transp<span style="background-color: #ffffff;">ort {animals}, so </span>experience handling them is preferred</p>
</li>
<li data-start="912" data-end="966">
<p data-start="914" data-end="966">all drivers also have t<span style="background-color: #ffffff;">o {clean} their</span> truck</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="968" data-end="992"><strong data-start="968" data-end="992">Warehouse Supervisor</strong></p>
<ul data-start="993" data-end="1079">
<li data-start="993" data-end="1042">
<p data-start="995" data-end="1042">managing the warehouse near th<span style="background-color: #ffffff;">e {airport}</span></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1043" data-end="1079">
<p data-start="1045" data-end="1079">they need their ow<span style="background-color: #ffffff;">n {car}</span></p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Hello Morgan Recruitment Agency. How may I help you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Hello. I need to employ some new staff for my company and I believe your agency can help with that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Yes of course. First I’ll get some details from you. Can I have your name please?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Sure my name is Peter Smith.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> And can I also get a contact number?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Our number here is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">(1) 0478883925</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Thank you. Can I also take down some details about your company? What’s your company name?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> It’s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">(2) Vander</strong></span> Transport.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Is that V-A-N… that’s N for November… D-E-R?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> That’s right. We are a large trucking company.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> The transport industry is really booming, especially for fresh fruit and vegetables, isn’t it?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Yes. We have a fleet of refrigerated trucks though, so we mostly carry <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">(3) frozen</strong></span> goods—fish, vegetables, pizza, all sorts.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> I see. So you said that you need some new staff members. When would you need them to start?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> We’d like them to start around the 27th of August.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Just looking at my calendar here… the 27th is a Sunday, so do you mean the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"84\">(4) 28th (August)</strong>?</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Aha, yes. That’s right. We’re hoping to hold any interviews around July 29th. I’ll get more details of that later.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Okay now, could you tell me about the jobs you have available so we can hopefully find some suitable candidates?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Sure. The first position is an office manager.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> So does the job involve typical management duties?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Yes, but they also have to liaise with our main client, which is a large supermarket chain. So a background in a company like that is essential.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Okay I’ll note that down. It sounds like an important role. What are the minimum qualifications? Do they need a university education, like a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"148\">(5) degree</strong></span>?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Yes, candidates would definitely have one.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Okay. Can you tell me about the next position?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> We’re looking for a full-time mechanic.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> So I assume the job will involve doing general repairs on trucks?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Yes, that’s right. And one of the other key responsibilities is to produce a written <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">(6) report</strong></span> for each vehicle.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> I think we have several people on our books that would be suitable. And will the mechanic be doing much travelling?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Some yes, but not a great deal. Unlike our next vacancy.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> That’s for a full-time truck driver, right? What kind of shifts are they expected to work?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> They usually travel around 1,000 km over a five-day period.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> I see.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> This job is different to our usual ones though. It involves moving <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">(7) animals</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> That sounds interesting.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Yes. Our company has just got a new contract, so we’ve bought new trucks and want a driver with that kind of experience.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Great. Is there anything else I should make a note of?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"39\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"39\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Well, we own all of the trucks, but apart from their driving duties, it is up to all our drivers to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"39\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">(8) clean</strong></span> their vehicle between trips. We do give them extra time for that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"40\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"40\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> OK. And are there any other positions available?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"41\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"41\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Yes, we’re looking for a warehouse supervisor.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"42\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"42\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> And what will this involve?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"43\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"43\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> They’ll be in charge of our new warehouse. It’s located close to the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"43\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">(9) airport</strong></span>. We’ve recently moved out of the city centre.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"44\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"44\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Oh that must be more convenient. And what are some of the requirements for this role?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"45\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"45\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> The successful candidate would be able to work effectively in a busy environment. Sometimes I’ll be on call 24 hours for our night-time deliveries.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"46\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"46\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> So given the hours they’ll be working, I assume it will be necessary for the candidate to have a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"46\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">(10) car</strong></span>?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"47\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"47\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Yes that’s right. Buses and trains just don’t operate at those times unfortunately.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"48\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"48\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Okay Mister Smith, I’ll have a look at the job seekers we have on our books and see if we have any suitable candidates…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8aa9cb69-7b70-477c-82fc-5bcc30cce95c', '56181149-4473-4a5b-b5d4-4bd330e4206a', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Crocodile Study</strong></p>
<p><strong>Background</strong></p>
<p>– Type of crocodile studied: crocodiles found in salt water</p>
<p>– Location of study: Northern Territory, Australia</p>
<p>– Significance of study: unique because it was the first time a {satellite} had been used to track crocodiles</p>
<p><strong>Previous studies:</strong></p>
<p>– done using {radio}</p>
<p>– stressful method, also unreliable due to loss of the {signal}</p>
<p><strong>Reasons for study: </strong>the management of crocodiles by the government may not be effective</p>
<p><strong>Research questions:</strong></p>
<p>– How far can crocodiles travel?</p>
<p>– How easily can crocodiles {navigate}?</p>
<p><strong>Challenge: </strong>crocodiles are difficult to observe because they avoid {people}</p>
<p><strong>Details of study:</strong></p>
<p>– number of crocodiles involved: three</p>
<p>– method: crocodiles were measured and Tagged hen relocated using a {helicopter}</p>
<p>– monitoring: scientists got data from a transmitter located on the crocodile’s {head}</p>
<p><strong>Results of study:</strong></p>
<p>– Each crocodile</p>
<p>– first stayed at the site for a few weeks, moving in a random way</p>
<p>– then took the most {direct} way home</p>
<p><strong>Conclusions:</strong></p>
<p>– a change in policy is needed</p>
<p>– when travelling long distances, crocodiles may use</p>
<p>i. their own senses and the position of the {sun}</p>
<p>ii. a similar system to {birds}</p>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 4</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Hello everybody. I&#8217;ve just arrived back from my field trip and Professor Martin has asked me to tell you about it today in our research forum. As many of you know already, my dissertation relates to crocodile behaviour. My specialty is the saltwater crocodile, which is much larger than the freshwater crocodile.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">I&#8217;ve just come back from the Northern Territory where I&#8217;ve been part of a groundbreaking study observing crocodile movements. Ah, it&#8217;s not the only time crocodile movements have been followed, but this study is unique because we tracked crocodiles using a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"256\">(31) satellite</strong></span>. Up until now, studies like this one have only been able to track crocodile movements using <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"363\">(32) radio</strong></span>. Not only was this method more stressful for the animal, which had to be caught several times, but it was also not very reliable as the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"510\">(33) signal</strong></span> was often lost.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">So you might be wondering why we chose to track crocodiles. Well, crocodile attacks on people and livestock are rare, but when they do happen, the government believes that the &#8220;problem&#8221; crocodile should be relocated rather than killed. But can we be sure that the crocodile won&#8217;t simply return to the place where it came from?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">So we designed a study to try to answer these questions. We wanted to establish firstly how far crocodiles can travel over a period of time. The second thing that we wanted to know was how easy is it for crocodiles to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"218\">(34) navigate</strong></span>? Could they find their own way home again if they were moved to another location? Of course, the biggest challenge when observing crocodiles is that they are very secretive animals. They stay well away from <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"439\">(35) people</strong></span> if they can, which makes them really difficult to follow.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">I&#8217;ll give you some information about the design of the study now. There were three crocodiles in our study, all from the Northern Territory and measuring between 3 and 4.5 meters in length. The crocodiles were captured, measured and tagged, and then taken by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"259\">(36) helicopter</strong></span> to new locations up to 400 km away from where they were found.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">We were then able to use the tracking data to monitor their movements. We used a specially designed transmitter which we attached to each animal&#8217;s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"147\">(37) head</strong></span>. The transmitter collected the data and relayed it back to us.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">The results of our study were quite astounding. After they were released, each crocodile remained in the release site for some weeks, making random movements around the site each day. But then they each swam home, traveling by the most <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"236\">(38) direct</strong></span> route. These crocodiles showed remarkable navigational skills and stamina to swim such long voyages.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">So what conclusions did we draw from this? Well, we proved that crocodiles are clearly capable of making marathon swims to find their way home. This meant that the current policy should be reconsidered.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">You might be wondering how the crocodiles managed to get home. We concluded that they used factors such as sight and smell, as well as their position to the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">(39) sun</strong></span> to point their way. It&#8217;s a little-known fact that crocodiles are more closely related to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"255\">(40) birds</strong></span> than they are to any other reptile, so we believe it&#8217;s possible that they use the same system to negotiate long journeys. Now that the study has been completed&#8230;</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('74748978-4c0e-4e8e-9b18-6ace3de3deee', '9e1776dd-ee65-4b43-a2d4-8cadedf709d7', 'fillup', 'Questions 21–25', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Answer the questions below</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>When was the bittern population largest? {1950|IN 1950}</p>
<p>What word is used in the passage to describe the bittern’s character? {shy}</p>
<p>What is probably the main cause of death of bittern chicks? {starvation}</p>
<p>What food supply do bittern chicks depend on? {fish}</p>
<p>What other creatures mentioned in the passage have also benefited from improvements made to the bittern’s habitat? {otters}</p>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. When was the bittern population largest?</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án</strong>: 1950</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: “…and in <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">1950</strong> the numbers of nature male bitterns rose to a <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">peak</strong> of about 70.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Từ “peak” (đỉnh điểm) xác nhận năm 1950 là lúc số lượng chim lớn nhất.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. What word is used in the passage to describe the bittern’s character?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án</strong>: shy</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: “Bitterns have feathers that help them to conceal themselves and a <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">shy</strong> nature…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Bài đọc sử dụng trực tiếp tính từ “shy” để mô tả tính cách loài chim này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. What is probably the main cause of death of bittern chicks?</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án</strong>: starvation</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: “Many chicks did not survive… and <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">starvation</strong> was found to be the most likely reason for their demise.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: “Starvation” (sự chết đói) là nguyên nhân chính gây tử vong cho chim non.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. What food supply do bittern chicks depend on?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8,3,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,3,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án</strong>: fish</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,3,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: “The <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">fish</strong> prey fed to chicks was mainly those species penetrating into the reed edge.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,3,1,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,3,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Chim non phụ thuộc vào nguồn thức ăn là các loài cá.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,4,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,4,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. What other creatures mentioned in the passage have also benefited from improvements made to the bittern’s habitat?</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8,4,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,4,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,4,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án</strong>: otters</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,4,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,4,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: “…the work has helped a range of other spectacular wetland species such as <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,4,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">otters</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,4,1,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,4,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Ngoài chim bittern, loài rái cá (otters) cũng được hưởng lợi từ việc cải tạo môi trường đầm lầy.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('587ca2b0-ff7e-4af1-bbb1-cac26c7dac58', '20b3d9b0-9161-4986-9599-324e831727d0', 'fillup', 'Questions 35–38', '<p>Complete the following summary of the paragraphs of Reading Passage 3.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p>The reason why grapefruit tastes bitter is because a substance called {naringin} contained in it. However, bitterness plays a significant role for plants. It gives a signal that certain plant is {poisonous}. For human beings, different person carries various genetic abilities of tasting bitterness. According to a scientist at the University of Utah, {supertasters} have exceptionally plenty of {taste buds}, which allows them to perceive bitter compounds.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">35. The reason why grapefruit tastes bitter is because a substance called {naringin} contained in it.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>naringin</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn A, dòng 2.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;<strong>Naringin</strong>, a natural chemical compound found in grapefruit, tastes bitter.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ rõ hợp chất hóa học tự nhiên có tên là naringin chính là nguyên nhân tạo ra vị đắng của quả bưởi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">36. It gives a signal that certain plant is {poisonous}.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>poisonous</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn C, dòng 5.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;They defend plants by warning animals away and protect animals by letting them know when a plant may be <strong>poisonous</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Trong tự nhiên, vị đắng đóng vai trò như một hệ thống cảnh báo. Nó giúp động vật nhận biết cây đó có thể chứa độc tố (<em>poisonous</em>) để tránh ăn phải.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">37. &amp; 38. According to a scientist at the University of Utah, {supertasters} have exceptionally plenty of {taste buds}, which allows them to perceive bitter compounds.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án 37:</strong> <strong>supertasters</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Đáp án 38:</strong> <strong>taste buds</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn D, dòng 5-6.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,3,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;Some people, known as <strong>supertasters</strong>, are especially sensitive&#8230; because they have an unusually high number of <strong>taste buds</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,4,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài viết đề cập rằng những người có khả năng cảm nhận vị giác cực nhạy được gọi là &#8220;supertasters&#8221;. Lý do sinh học cho khả năng này là do họ sở hữu số lượng gai vị giác (<em>taste buds</em>) nhiều hơn mức bình thường.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7b29032a-d041-4a92-b992-7e0082e55b95', '0aa21314-5924-4ffe-b3f9-02dc961262d5', 'radio', 'Questions 1–7', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Hokusai’s earliest artistic works mainly focused on landscapes and actors."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "He was officially recognized as the heir of the Nakajima family."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Hokusai’s apprenticeship with a wood-block engraver contributed to his later success as a printmaker."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The series Thirty-six Views of Mount Fuji was the first landscape work ever created in Japan."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Hokusai often competed with Utamaro in producing prints of women."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "His eldest son helped secure financial stability for him through the Nakajima family connections."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Hokusai changed his residence and artistic name multiple times throughout his life."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Hokusai’s earliest artistic works mainly focused on landscapes and actors.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 4 nói rằng những tác phẩm đầu tiên được xuất bản của ông là về các diễn viên kịch Kabuki (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">actor prints</em>). Đoạn 5 đề cập sau khi kết hôn (khoảng 25 tuổi), ông mới chuyển sang đề tài lịch sử và phong cảnh (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"219\">landscapes</em>).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc không khẳng định hai đề tài này là “trọng tâm chính” (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">mainly focused</em>) trong giai đoạn <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">sớm nhất</strong> (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">earliest</em>). Thực tế, phong cảnh xuất hiện muộn hơn một chút so với tranh diễn viên.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. He was officially recognized as the heir of the Nakajima family.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 2: “…was adopted… by a prestigious artisan family named Nakajima but was <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">never accepted as an heir</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Dẫn chứng trực tiếp khẳng định ông <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">chưa bao giờ</strong> được chấp nhận làm người thừa kế chính thức, trái ngược hoàn toàn với câu hỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Hokusai’s apprenticeship with a wood-block engraver contributed to his later success as a printmaker.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 3: “…from 15 to 18 years of age he was apprenticed to a wood-block engraver. This early training… <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">obviously contributed to Hokusai’s artistic development</strong> as a printmaker.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài viết khẳng định rõ ràng việc học nghề thợ khắc gỗ đã đóng góp quan trọng vào sự nghiệp của ông sau này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. The series Thirty-six Views of Mount Fuji was the first landscape work ever created in Japan.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 1 và 13: “…marked the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">summit</strong> in the history of the Japanese landscape print… in grandeur of concept… there was <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">little approaching it before</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ “summit” (đỉnh cao) và cụm “little approaching it before” (có ít tác phẩm đạt đến tầm đó trước đây) ngụ ý rằng đã có các tác phẩm phong cảnh khác tồn tại trước đó, chỉ là không hoành tráng bằng. Do đó, đây không phải là tác phẩm phong cảnh đầu tiên.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Hokusai often competed with Utamaro in producing prints of women.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 7: “Hokusai <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">only occasionally</strong>… chose to compete with Utamaro… the acknowledged master of voluptuous women figure prints.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ “often” (thường xuyên) trong câu hỏi mâu thuẫn với “only occasionally” (chỉ thỉnh thoảng) trong bài đọc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. His eldest son helped secure financial stability for him through the Nakajima family connections.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 9: “…as adopted heir to the affluent Nakajima family, the son had been <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">instrumental in obtaining a generous stipend for Hokusai</strong>, so that he did not need to worry about the uncertainties of income…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Con trai cả của ông (với tư cách là người thừa kế nhà Nakajima) đã giúp ông có một khoản trợ cấp ổn định, giúp ông không phải lo lắng về tài chính.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Hokusai changed his residence and artistic name multiple times throughout his life.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 14: “Hokusai’s frequent changes in domicile (<strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">more than 90 dwellings</strong>) và of his <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">own name</strong> are indicative of the artist’s restless nature.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nêu rõ ông đã đổi chỗ ở hơn 90 lần và thay đổi nghệ danh liên tục (khoảng mỗi thập kỷ một lần).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9b901ad3-edc6-4173-9c78-f2a57a49dc29', '0aa21314-5924-4ffe-b3f9-02dc961262d5', 'fillup', 'Questions 8–13', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Hokusai showed interest in drawing at the age of five and may have been the son of a {concubine}. As a teenager, he was apprenticed to a wood-block engraver, and later studied under the Ukiyo-e master Shunshō, producing actor prints of the {theatre}.</p>
<p>During his career, Hokusai created a wide variety of works, including landscapes, actor prints, and {Surimono} produced for special occasions. He also published sketchbooks for amateur artists known as Hokusai {manga}. In many of his landscape works, he experimented Western-style colouring and {perspective} for a time.</p>
<p>Although he worked in different genres, Hokusai also competed with other masters such as {Utamaro}, who was famous for figure prints.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"26\">8. Hokusai showed interest in drawing at the age of five and may have been the son of a <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>concubine</strong>.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>concubine</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “…though the true son of Nakajima, he had been born of a <strong>concubine</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Có khả năng Hokusai được sinh ra từ một <strong>thứ phi</strong> (<em>concubine</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"28\">9. As a teenager, he was apprenticed to a wood-block engraver, and later studied under the Ukiyo-e master Shunshō, producing actor prints of the <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>theatre</strong>.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>theatre</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “…The young Hokusai’s first published works appeared the following year-actor prints of the Kabuki <strong>theatre</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các tác phẩm xuất bản đầu tiên của ông là tranh diễn viên của <strong>sân khấu</strong> Kabuki (<em>Kabuki theatre</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"30\">10. During his career, Hokusai created a wide variety of works, including landscapes, actor prints, and <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>Surimono</strong> produced for special occasions.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Surimono</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1 &amp; 5) Các tác phẩm đầu tiên bao gồm “<em>surimono</em> (‘printed things’), such as greetings and announcements” và “Surimono were prints issued privately for <strong>special occasions</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> <strong>Surimono</strong> là loại bản in được phát hành riêng cho các dịp đặc biệt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"32\">11. He also published sketchbooks for amateur artists known as Hokusai <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>manga</strong>.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>manga</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 11) “…to the picture book and, particularly, to the type of wood-block-printed copybook designed for amateur artists (including the famous Hokusai <strong>manga</strong>).”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Ông đã xuất bản các cuốn sách phác họa (<em>sketchbooks</em>) cho các nghệ sĩ nghiệp dư, bao gồm Hokusai <strong>manga</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"34\">12. In many of his landscape works, he experimented Western-style colouring and <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>perspective</strong> for a time.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"35\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>perspective</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) “Around the turn of the century he experimented for a time with Western-style perspective and colouring.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Ông đã thử nghiệm phong cách tô màu và <strong>phối cảnh</strong> (<em>perspective</em>) phương Tây.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"36\">13. Although he worked in different genres, Hokusai also competed with other masters such as <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>Utamaro</strong>, who was famous for figure prints.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"37\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Utamaro</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) “…Hokusai only occasionally… chose to compete with <strong>Utamaro</strong>, the acknowledged master of voluptuous women figure prints.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Ông thỉnh thoảng cạnh tranh với <strong>Utamaro</strong>, người nổi tiếng với tranh in hình người phụ nữ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('dce19e8d-67e1-45ce-a0ce-51c26038c38a', '7895d3f0-d719-4736-8972-f6b58efe438d', 'fillup', 'Questions 9–13', '<p data-path-to-node="16">Complete the flow-chart below.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="17">Choose <strong data-path-to-node="17" data-index-in-node="7">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="18">Write your answers in boxes 9–13 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-path-to-node="19"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="19" data-index-in-node="0">How pencils are manufactured today</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Graphite and clay are separately crushed to form powders, then {cleaned} and dried</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">⬇️</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">the graphite and clay powders are combined with water</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">⬇️</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">the mixture is shaped into long sticks</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">⬇️</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">then, the sticks are dried, and {heated}</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">⬇️</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">the sticks are dipped into {wax}</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">⬇️</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">the sticks are put into {grooves} in a wooden plank and another plank is fixed on top</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">⬇️</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">the whole thing is cut into individual pencils</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">⬇️</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">the pencils are {varnished} or painted</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. cleaned — {then cleaned and dried}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Each of these substances is ground into a fine powder, which goes on to be <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">cleaned</strong> in order to remove any impurities. After the two types of powders have been <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"180\">dried</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sau khi được nghiền thành bột (ground into powder/crushed), các nguyên liệu sẽ được làm sạch (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">cleaned</strong>) để loại bỏ tạp chất trước khi được sấy khô (dried).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. heated — {then, the sticks are dried, and heated}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The graphite-clay mixture is then shaped into long sticks, and after drying these are <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">heated</strong> in a kiln to 1,200°C.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sau khi hỗn hợp được tạo hình thành các thanh dài và sấy khô, bước tiếp theo là nung nóng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"103\">heated</strong>) chúng trong lò ở nhiệt độ cao.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. wax — {the sticks are dipped into wax}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In the next step in the process, the graphite-clay sticks are <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">immersed in melted wax</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ “immersed” (ngâm/nhúng) đồng nghĩa với “dipped into”. Các thanh lõi sẽ được nhúng vào sáp (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">wax</strong>) nóng chảy để giúp viết mượt hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. grooves — {the sticks are put into grooves in a wooden plank}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Several long parallel <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">grooves</strong> are cut into the planks, and the graphite-clay sticks are <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"109\">inserted into these</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Inserted into” tương ứng với “put into”. Các lõi bút chì được đặt vào những rãnh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">grooves</strong>) đã được cắt sẵn trên tấm gỗ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. varnished — {the pencils are varnished or painted}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The outside may then be <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">varnished</strong>, retaining the natural colour of the wood, or <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">painted</strong> in different colours.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đây là bước hoàn thiện cuối cùng. Bút chì có thể được đánh bóng/phủ vecni (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">varnished</strong>) để giữ màu gỗ tự nhiên hoặc được sơn màu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('73b8088e-60c9-45fe-a778-9d546fc4c74b', '0a3ab604-e01e-4257-a0cb-526a73f9810b', 'matrix', 'Questions 14–17', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 2 has nine paragraphs, A-I.</p>
<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, A-I, in boxes 14-17.</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "the suggestion that people may need to adapt to a different quality of meat", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "a description of the way animals fed in the past", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "a prediction in regard to human demand for meat", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "the potential consequences of a meat-free", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}, {"categoryText": "I", "categoryLetter": "I"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">14. The suggestion that people may need to adapt to a different quality of meat</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: E</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Cuối đoạn E) &#8220;&#8230;it would require a <strong>major adjustment in food preferences</strong>; people would have to get used to chicken, for example, <strong>with less fat</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn E đề cập rằng nếu chúng ta nuôi gia súc bằng thức ăn thừa, con người sẽ phải điều chỉnh sở thích ăn uống (<em>adjustment in food preferences</em>), cụ thể là phải làm quen với loại thịt có chất lượng khác (ví dụ: thịt gà <strong>ít mỡ hơn</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">15. A description of the way animals were fed in the past</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: D</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) &#8220;<strong>For most of human history</strong>, livestock <strong>grazed on land</strong> that wasn’t suitable for ploughing, and in doing so they <strong>converted inedible grass</strong> into edible meat and milk.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ &#8220;For most of human history&#8221; chỉ về <strong>quá khứ</strong> (<em>in the past</em>). Đoạn văn mô tả cách chăn nuôi truyền thống là cho gia súc gặm cỏ trên những vùng đất không thể trồng trọt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">16. A prediction in regard to human demand for meat</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: H</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn H) &#8220;The United Nations’ best guess is that <strong>by 2050, the world will need to more than double its production of meat</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đây là một <strong>dự đoán</strong> (<em>prediction</em>) về tương lai (năm 2050), khẳng định rằng nhu cầu và sản lượng thịt của con người sẽ tăng gấp đôi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">17. The potential consequences of a meat-free world</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: F</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) &#8220;<strong>Another downside to a meat-free world</strong> would be the <strong>disappearance of animal by-products</strong>&#8230; replace the 11 million tonnes of leather and 2 million tonnes of wool&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn F thảo luận về các <strong>hệ quả tiềm tàng</strong> (<em>potential consequences</em>) nếu thế giới không ăn thịt, bao gồm sự biến mất của các phụ phẩm như da và len, cũng như tác động tiêu cực đến thu nhập của người nghèo.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4e755e51-eef9-4a1a-a9d9-1d7f40d71555', '0a3ab604-e01e-4257-a0cb-526a73f9810b', 'fillup', 'Questions 18–22', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>How does agriculture damage the environment?</strong></p>
<p>Agriculture causes significant harm to the environment in a number of ways, including the frequent use of {irrigation} in modern farming and the cutting down of trees. It is also responsible for the production of many greenhouse gases, more so than {transport} is. However, it is livestock farming in particular that is most harmful, because cows, chickens and sheep, for example, are given vast quantities of grain which could be consumed by people instead. A meat-free diet would mean that actually less {land} could be used for crops. Far less chemical pollution, specifically in the form of {nitrogen} would also be released into the environment, especially if consumers cut out dairy and egg products as well as meat. In the US, there is clear evidence that considerable {erosion} is caused by the demand for grazing land, although there is no information on this from other countries.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">18. &#8230;including the frequent use of {irrigation} in modern farming&#8230;</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>irrigation</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn B (Dòng 1-2)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;Take for example the felled forests and the <strong>common use of irrigation systems</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nêu hai ví dụ về tác hại của nông nghiệp: phá rừng và việc sử dụng phổ biến các hệ thống <strong>tưới tiêu</strong> (<em>irrigation</em>). Từ &#8220;frequent use&#8221; trong tóm tắt đồng nghĩa với &#8220;common use&#8221; trong bài.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">19. It is also responsible for the production of many greenhouse gases, more so than {transport} is.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>transport</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn B (Dòng 3-4)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;&#8230;agriculture creates more greenhouse gases than all methods of <strong>transport</strong> put together.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả so sánh lượng khí thải nhà kính từ nông nghiệp với tất cả các phương thức <strong>giao thông vận tải</strong> (<em>transport</em>), và khẳng định nông nghiệp gây ra nhiều khí thải hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">20. A meat-free diet would mean that actually less {land} could be used for crops.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>land</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn B (2 dòng cuối)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;&#8230;if we switched to a vegan diet&#8230; the <strong>land</strong> currently required for crops would drop by an estimated 21 per cent&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nếu thế giới ngừng ăn thịt, diện tích <strong>đất</strong> (<em>land</em>) cần thiết để trồng trọt sẽ giảm đi đáng kể (khoảng 21%) vì không còn phải trồng ngũ cốc để nuôi gia súc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">21. Far less chemical pollution, specifically in the form of {nitrogen} would also be released&#8230;</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>nitrogen</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn C (Dòng 1-2)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;One environmental impact&#8230; would be that of the <strong>nitrogen</strong> emitted from agricultural processes, which spreads into both waterways and land.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc đề cập đến một loại ô nhiễm hóa học cụ thể là khí <strong>nitơ</strong> (<em>nitrogen</em>) phát thải từ các quá trình nông nghiệp. Lượng ô nhiễm này sẽ giảm đi nếu giảm chăn nuôi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">22. In the US, there is clear evidence that considerable {erosion} is caused by the demand for grazing land&#8230;</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>erosion</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn C (Dòng 5-6)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;&#8230;in the US at least, livestock account for 55% of <strong>erosion</strong>, mostly from forests being cut down to make way for grazing land.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tại Mỹ, việc chăn nuôi gia súc chiếm tới 55% nguyên nhân gây ra sự <strong>xói mòn</strong> (<em>erosion</em>), chủ yếu do việc phá rừng để lấy đất chăn thả.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('dde5d315-92be-4de4-a37b-e56213fe2f5d', '0a3ab604-e01e-4257-a0cb-526a73f9810b', 'matrix', 'Questions 23–26', NULL, '<p>Look at the following statements and the list of people below.</p>
<p>Match each statement with the correct person, A-E.</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, A-E, in boxes 23-26.</p>', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of people", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": " It is not possible to say that a vegetarian diet is right for everyone.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": " It may be economically preferable to farm animals in limited space.", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": " It does not make sense to give up meat without giving up dairy products too.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": " Some animals can be fed in a way that allows waste to be recycled.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Allison Leach", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Tara Garnett", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Annette Pinner", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Helmut Haberl", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "Walter Falcon", "categoryLetter": "E"}]}', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"4\">23. It is not possible to say that a vegetarian diet is right for everyone.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án: C (Annette Pinner)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn F (Dòng 4-6).</li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…we do have to be <strong>careful about saying it would be the best solution</strong> if the whole world went vegetarian,’ says <strong>Annette Pinner</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Annette Pinner (Giám đốc điều hành Hiệp hội Ăn chay Anh) khuyên nên thận trọng khi khẳng định ăn chay là giải pháp tốt nhất cho tất cả mọi người, vì động vật rất quan trọng đối với thu nhập và dinh dưỡng của người nghèo.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"6\">24. It may be economically preferable to farm animals in limited space.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án: E (Walter Falcon)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn I (Dòng 2-4).</li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “‘If you’re going to keep some livestock systems, I think the ones you’ll want to keep are the <strong>intensive ones</strong>,’ he [<strong>Walter Falcon</strong>] says.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Chăn nuôi thâm canh (<em>intensive farming</em>) chính là hình thức nuôi gia súc trong không gian hạn chế (<em>limited space</em>) để tối ưu hóa năng suất. Walter Falcon cho rằng đây là hệ thống nên được duy trì để có chi phí môi trường thấp nhất.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"8\">25. It does not make sense to give up meat without giving up dairy products too.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án: D (Helmut Haberl)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn G (Dòng 3-6).</li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Dairy cows must calve every year to keep producing milk… while many vegetarians see moral reasons not to kill and eat the males, there is surely <strong>no practical reason to waste so much meat</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Helmut Haberl lập luận rằng nếu vẫn dùng sữa (<em>dairy</em>) thì vẫn sẽ có những con bê đực được sinh ra. Nếu không ăn thịt chúng thì sẽ rất lãng phí. Do đó, việc bỏ thịt mà vẫn giữ sữa là không thực tế (<em>no practical reason</em>).</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"10\">26. Some animals can be fed in a way that allows waste to be recycled.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án: B (Tara Garnett)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn E (Dòng 3-5).</li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “<strong>Tara Garnett</strong>… points out the usefulness of these animals. By giving them your <strong>leftovers</strong>, she says, they <strong>deal with your rubbish</strong>, and you get meat.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tara Garnett giải thích rằng việc cho động vật ăn thức ăn thừa (<em>leftovers</em>) chính là một cách để xử lý rác thải (<em>deal with rubbish/waste</em>), giúp “tái chế” rác thành thực phẩm (thịt).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b9c03106-c4d6-4311-b9c8-d580837f87c5', '20b3d9b0-9161-4986-9599-324e831727d0', 'matrix', 'Questions 27–34', NULL, '<p>The Reading Passage 3 has seven paragraphs A-I.</p>
<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, A-I, in boxes 27-34.</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Experiment on bitterness conducted", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": " Look into the future application", "correctCategoryLetter": "I"}, {"itemText": "Bitterness means different information for human and animals", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Spread process of bitterness inside of body", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": " How AMP blocks bitterness", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "Some bitterness blocker may help lower unhealthy impact", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "Bitterness introduced from a fruit", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Genetic feature determines sensitivity", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}, {"categoryText": "I", "categoryLetter": "I"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>27. An experience of the writer in a test — Đáp án: B</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;I found that out by <strong>participating in a test</strong> conducted at the Linguagen Corporation&#8230; Sets of two miniature white paper cups&#8230; were placed before five people&#8230;&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn B mô tả trực tiếp việc tác giả (<em>the writer</em>) tham gia vào một cuộc thử nghiệm nếm hai mẫu nước bưởi (304 và 305) để kiểm chứng tác dụng của chất AMP.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>28. The future of bitter blockers — Đáp án: I</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;<strong>In a few years, perhaps</strong>, after food companies have taken the bitterness from canned soup&#8230; they can set their sights on something more useful: a <strong>bitter blocker in a bottle</strong> that any of us can sprinkle&#8230;&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn I đưa ra dự đoán về tương lai khi người tiêu dùng có thể tự mua chai chất chặn vị đắng để sử dụng tại nhà như một loại gia vị thông thường.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>29. The evolution of bitter taste — Đáp án: C</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;They defend plants by warning animals away&#8230; humans are the only species that enjoys bitter taste&#8230; Every other species is averse to bitter&#8230; <strong>But we have learned to enjoy it</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn C nói về quá trình tiến hóa: từ một cơ chế cảnh báo chất độc trong tự nhiên, con người đã dần học cách yêu thích và đưa vị đắng vào văn hóa ẩm thực (cà phê, rượu tonic).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>30. The identification of gustducin — Đáp án: E</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;The G protein involved in the perception of bitterness&#8230; was <strong>identified in the early 1990s</strong> by Linguagen’s founder, Robert Margolskee&#8230; <strong>Known as gustducin</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn E cung cấp thông tin về việc phát hiện và định danh loại protein tên là <strong>Gustducin</strong>, mắt xích quan trọng trong việc truyền tín hiệu vị đắng lên não.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>31. The mechanism of AMP — Đáp án: G</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;&#8230;AMP&#8230; has no bitterness of its own, but when put it in foods&#8230; <strong>it attaches to bitter-taste receptors</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn G giải thích cơ chế khoa học của AMP: nó hoạt động bằng cách &#8220;chiếm chỗ&#8221; trên các thụ thể vị giác, ngăn không cho các phân tử gây đắng bám vào.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>32. The potential medical applications — Đáp án: H</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;Bitter blockers could also be used&#8230; to take the harshness out of <strong>children’s cough syrup</strong>, and they could dampen the bitterness of <strong>antihistamines, antibiotics, certain HIV drugs</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn H liệt kê một loạt các ứng dụng tiềm năng trong y tế, giúp các loại thuốc điều trị trở nên dễ uống hơn đối với bệnh nhân.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>33. The antioxidant properties of naringin — Đáp án: A</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;&#8230;though the compound [naringin] has <strong>antioxidant properties</strong> that some nutritionists contend may <strong>help prevent cancer and arteriosclerosis</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn A giải thích về Naringin (chất gây đắng trong bưởi) và những lợi ích sức khỏe của nó như một chất chống oxy hóa giúp phòng ngừa bệnh tật.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>34. Genetic differences in taste capacity — Đáp án: D</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;People have <strong>varying capacities</strong> for tasting bitterness, and the differences appear to be <strong>genetic</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn D thảo luận về việc khả năng nếm vị đắng (như người siêu vị giác &#8211; supertasters) được quyết định bởi các yếu tố di truyền và số lượng chồi vị giác trên lưỡi.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('642c20e8-85cb-4473-adca-0dd851ba374c', 'b1fa91cf-3528-402b-bfcc-c76888ce0e9d', 'fillup', 'Questions 31 - 40', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Bislama – The Pidgin English Language of Vanuatu</span></strong></p>
<p><strong>Languages in Vanuatu</strong></p>
<p><strong>Local languages:</strong></p>
<p>- Actively spoken language: 81</p>
<p>- Declining languages: 17</p>
<p>- {extinct} languages: 8</p>
<p>- Total: 106</p>
<p><strong>Foreign languages:</strong></p>
<p>- English is used in the {education} system</p>
<p><strong>Bislama</strong></p>
<p>- It is spoken by 90% of the population today.</p>
<p>- In the past this language was described as {broken}</p>
<p><strong>History of Bislama</strong></p>
<p>- Around 1800, it was used as a common language on many ships.</p>
<p>- After 1860, Vanuatu people worked in Australian {plantation}</p>
<p>- After 1950, people moved to the {city}</p>
<p><strong>Description of Bislama</strong></p>
<p><strong>General</strong></p>
<p>- Bislama should be called a {developed} pidgin.</p>
<p><strong>Vocabulary</strong></p>
<p>- Most words come from English.</p>
<p>- Words such as “from” may have more {meanings} in Bislama.</p>
<p>- Less than 10% of words are of {French} origin.</p>
<p>- Pacific words describe the natural world and also local {culture}</p>
<p class="question"><strong>Grammar</strong></p>
<p class="question">- It is based on Vanuatu languages.</p>
<p class="question">- The word “long” acts as an important {preposition} in Bislama.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('40ed1495-96a8-43a9-b6f7-26b84883ff6c', 'e2cfb22b-fcdb-4358-b706-51e709554b50', 'fillup', 'Questions 8–13', '<p data-start="1081" data-end="1155">Complete the notes. Write <strong data-start="1107" data-end="1124">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<h2 data-start="1157" data-end="1186">The Trial of December 1818</h2>
<h3 data-start="1188" data-end="1209">The Personalities</h3>
<ul data-start="1211" data-end="1433">
<li data-start="1211" data-end="1268">
<p data-start="1213" data-end="1268">Samuel Mitchill worked as a congressman and a {lecturer}.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1269" data-end="1336">
<p data-start="1271" data-end="1336">The defence wanted Mitchill to present the biology of the case.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1337" data-end="1433">
<p data-start="1339" data-end="1433">William Sampson called {whalers} as witnesses in order to appeal to the common sense of the jury.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="1435" data-end="1452">The Arguments</h3>
<ul data-start="1454" data-end="1667">
<li data-start="1454" data-end="1526">
<p data-start="1456" data-end="1526">Sampson’s case was based on the consequences for humans if Judd won.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1527" data-end="1599">
<p data-start="1529" data-end="1599">Mitchill admitted that scientists had disputes about classification.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1600" data-end="1667">
<p data-start="1602" data-end="1667">New Yorkers disliked Mitchill because his ideas came from {Europe}.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="1669" data-end="1684">Conclusions</h3>
<ul data-start="1686" data-end="1914">
<li data-start="1686" data-end="1785">
<p data-start="1688" data-end="1785">In the end it was statements from local {merchants}, not Mitchill’s testimony which helped Judd win.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1786" data-end="1840">
<p data-start="1788" data-end="1840">Whale oil made a good {fuel} because it was clean.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1841" data-end="1914">
<p data-start="1843" data-end="1914">Judd’s case is relevant today, e.g. in the debate about Earth’s {climate}.</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-start=\"1941\" data-end=\"1959\"><strong data-start=\"1944\" data-end=\"1959\">8. lecturer</strong></h2>\n<p data-start=\"1961\" data-end=\"1982\"><strong data-start=\"1961\" data-end=\"1972\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 4.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1984\" data-end=\"2056\"><strong data-start=\"1984\" data-end=\"1998\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"1998\" data-end=\"2001\">“Mitchill was a renowned natural history <strong data-start=\"2042\" data-end=\"2054\">lecturer</strong>…”</p>\n<p data-start=\"2058\" data-end=\"2107\"><strong data-start=\"2058\" data-end=\"2073\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"2073\" data-end=\"2076\">Ông là congressman và lecturer.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2109\" data-end=\"2112\">\n<h2 data-start=\"2114\" data-end=\"2131\"><strong data-start=\"2117\" data-end=\"2131\">9. whalers</strong></h2>\n<p data-start=\"2133\" data-end=\"2154\"><strong data-start=\"2133\" data-end=\"2144\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 5.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2156\" data-end=\"2243\"><strong data-start=\"2156\" data-end=\"2170\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"2170\" data-end=\"2173\">“…asking plain-spoken <strong data-start=\"2195\" data-end=\"2206\">whalers</strong> to make their case before the jury.”</p>\n<p data-start=\"2245\" data-end=\"2322\"><strong data-start=\"2245\" data-end=\"2260\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"2260\" data-end=\"2263\">Sampson gọi whalers làm nhân chứng để dựa vào common sense.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2324\" data-end=\"2327\">\n<h2 data-start=\"2329\" data-end=\"2346\"><strong data-start=\"2332\" data-end=\"2346\">10. Europe</strong></h2>\n<p data-start=\"2348\" data-end=\"2369\"><strong data-start=\"2348\" data-end=\"2359\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 6.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2371\" data-end=\"2461\"><strong data-start=\"2371\" data-end=\"2385\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"2385\" data-end=\"2388\">“Sampson then claimed Mitchill’s beliefs had their origin in <strong data-start=\"2449\" data-end=\"2459\">Europe</strong>…”</p>\n<p data-start=\"2463\" data-end=\"2538\"><strong data-start=\"2463\" data-end=\"2478\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"2478\" data-end=\"2481\">Người New York không thích vì tư tưởng đó đến từ châu Âu.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2540\" data-end=\"2543\">\n<h2 data-start=\"2545\" data-end=\"2565\"><strong data-start=\"2548\" data-end=\"2565\">11. merchants</strong></h2>\n<p data-start=\"2567\" data-end=\"2588\"><strong data-start=\"2567\" data-end=\"2578\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 7.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2590\" data-end=\"2672\"><strong data-start=\"2590\" data-end=\"2604\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"2604\" data-end=\"2607\">“In New York’s markets, the <strong data-start=\"2635\" data-end=\"2648\">merchants</strong> implicitly understood…”</p>\n<p data-start=\"2674\" data-end=\"2754\"><strong data-start=\"2674\" data-end=\"2689\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"2689\" data-end=\"2692\">Chính lời khai từ thương nhân địa phương giúp Judd thắng kiện.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2756\" data-end=\"2759\">\n<h2 data-start=\"2761\" data-end=\"2776\"><strong data-start=\"2764\" data-end=\"2776\">12. fuel</strong></h2>\n<p data-start=\"2778\" data-end=\"2799\"><strong data-start=\"2778\" data-end=\"2789\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 7.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2801\" data-end=\"2868\"><strong data-start=\"2801\" data-end=\"2815\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"2815\" data-end=\"2818\">“whale oil could be used as a <strong data-start=\"2848\" data-end=\"2856\">fuel</strong> for lamps…”</p>\n<p data-start=\"2870\" data-end=\"2941\"><strong data-start=\"2870\" data-end=\"2885\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"2885\" data-end=\"2888\">Whale oil là nhiên liệu tốt vì cháy sạch, không khói.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2943\" data-end=\"2946\">\n<h2 data-start=\"2948\" data-end=\"2966\"><strong data-start=\"2951\" data-end=\"2966\">13. climate</strong></h2>\n<p data-start=\"2968\" data-end=\"2992\"><strong data-start=\"2968\" data-end=\"2979\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn cuối.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2994\" data-end=\"3078\"><strong data-start=\"2994\" data-end=\"3008\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"3008\" data-end=\"3011\">“…the effects of human activity on the <strong data-start=\"3050\" data-end=\"3061\">climate</strong> of this planet…”</p>\n<p data-start=\"3080\" data-end=\"3162\"><strong data-start=\"3080\" data-end=\"3095\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"3095\" data-end=\"3098\">Vụ kiện còn liên hệ đến tranh luận ngày nay về khí hậu Trái Đất.</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7be5a34b-6a1f-4cab-bc61-c01bea1ac85c', '23217d2b-ce4e-4398-b7bc-eef57afba0fb', 'matrix', 'Questions 1–7', '', '<p data-start="189" data-end="239">For which event are the following statements true?</p>
<p data-start="241" data-end="310">Write the correct letter, <strong data-start="267" data-end="274">A–E</strong>, in boxes 1–7 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p data-start="312" data-end="357"> </p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "This event used to be known by a different name", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "At the end of this event any profits are handed over to charities", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "People can buy refreshments here that have all been made locally", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "This event has increased in size since it was last held", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "It is advisable to reserve places for certain activities at this event", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "This event also takes place in another country", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "People can listen to a range of singers here without paying", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Đáp án: {D} Craft Festival Cardiff</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Craft Festival Cardiff (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">formerly Made by Hand Cardiff</strong>) moved to City Hall…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “formerly” (trước đây là) xác nhận sự kiện này từng được biết đến với một cái tên khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Đáp án: {E} Sparks in the Park</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “All <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">funds raised will be distributed to organisations that help people in need</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Funds raised” (tiền gây quỹ được/lợi nhuận) sẽ được phân phối cho các tổ chức giúp đỡ người khó khăn (tương đương với charities – tổ chức từ thiện).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Đáp án: {C} Festival of Senses</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…light snacks… all <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">produced in the area</strong> by our cooks, crafters and growers.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Produced in the area” đồng nghĩa với “made locally” (được sản xuất/làm tại địa phương).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Đáp án: {A} Winter Food and Craft Festival</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “This year it’s going to be <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">bigger and better than ever</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Bigger than ever” (lớn hơn bao giờ hết) khớp với ý sự kiện đã tăng về quy mô so với lần trước.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Đáp án: {D} Craft Festival Cardiff</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Our workshops are very popular and <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">most sell out quickly. To book you must be…</strong>“</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Vì các buổi hội thảo (workshops) bán hết vé rất nhanh nên người tham gia cần phải đặt trước (reserve/book).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Đáp án: {B} Other Voices</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Other Voices makes its way from its <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">home in Dingle on the west coast of Ireland</strong> to the town of Cardigan… in Wales…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự kiện này có “nhà” (nguồn gốc) ở Ireland và nay được tổ chức tại Wales, nghĩa là nó diễn ra ở cả quốc gia khác nữa.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Đáp án: {B} Other Voices</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…showcase a line-up of over <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">30 free musical</strong> and cultural events, featuring <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">incredible vocal performances</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Vocal performances” (biểu diễn giọng hát) tương đương với việc nghe ca sĩ hát, và các sự kiện này là “free” (miễn phí).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('840be80c-dd49-40aa-a36a-eb8c53ac64d8', 'ec953306-f0ba-4b9b-9940-2152cefdebb4', 'radio', 'Questions 27–30', '', '<p><span class="citation-3960">Choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="7"><span class="citation-3960">YES</span></strong><span class="citation-3960"> if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer in the text, choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="85"><span class="citation-3960">NO</span></strong><span class="citation-3960"> if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, or choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="153"><span class="citation-3960">NOT GIVEN</span></strong><span class="citation-3960 citation-end-3960"> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks abo<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="1"><!----></sup></span>ut this.</p>', 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Parents and siblings play equal roles in shaping people’s adult personalities."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "People’s first social relationships tend to be with siblings rather than parents."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "People’s relationships with their siblings tend to receive less attention when they marry."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Parental ''basking'' is advantageous for later siblings."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. Parents and siblings play equal roles in shaping people’s adult personalities. — {NO}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Our parents provide the genetic material and make powerful early role models, but <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"103\">even more influential</strong> in determining what kind of adult we will become <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"174\">are our brothers and sisters – our siblings</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định anh chị em thậm chí còn <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">có sức ảnh hưởng lớn hơn</strong> (even more influential) so với cha mẹ trong việc định hình tính cách người trưởng thành. Do đó, nói hai vai trò này là “ngang nhau” (equal roles) là sai so với quan điểm của người viết.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. People’s first social relationships tend to be with siblings rather than parents. — {YES}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…our brothers and sisters are the human beings who people our <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">first social relationships</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ rõ anh chị em là những người tạo nên những mối quan hệ xã hội đầu tiên của chúng ta. (Lưu ý: Mối quan hệ với cha mẹ thường được coi là quan hệ nuôi dưỡng/gắn bó sinh học, trong khi quan hệ với anh chị em là bước đệm đầu tiên cho tương tác xã hội ngang hàng).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. People’s relationships with their siblings tend to receive less attention when they marry. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“And a sibling relationship is the most enduring relationship many of us will ever have – <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">no less emotionally intense than the bonds we form with our spouses</strong> and our own children…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả có so sánh cường độ cảm xúc của mối quan hệ anh chị em với mối quan hệ vợ chồng (spouses), khẳng định chúng cũng mãnh liệt không kém. Tuy nhiên, bài viết <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"174\">không hề đề cập</strong> đến việc sau khi kết hôn (when they marry) thì mối quan hệ với anh chị em có bị “ít được chú ý hơn” (receive less attention) hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('27f76cda-20bb-4747-aaed-c359714174b2', '23217d2b-ce4e-4398-b7bc-eef57afba0fb', 'radio', 'Questions 8–14', '', '<p>Choose TRUE if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose FALSE if the statement contradicts the information, or choose NOT GIVEN if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "An advanced driving course aims to teach drivers to predict problems on the road ahead"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Every advanced driving course follows a standard format"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "An advanced driving course can show participants how to use less petrol"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "IAM Roadsmart courses are becoming available in more places"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "IAM Roadsmart courses operate on a one-to-one basis"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "IAM Roadsmart runs courses for professional drivers"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The BAC only provides lessons to people who have particular driving requirements"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. Đáp án: {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…learn additional skills that will help you to <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">anticipate hazards</strong> when you are driving…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Anticipate hazards” (dự đoán các mối nguy hiểm) đồng nghĩa với “predict problems” (dự đoán các vấn đề) trên đường.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. Đáp án: {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “<strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Each available course differs in structure</strong> depending on the company that you choose to use.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói mỗi khóa học có cấu trúc khác nhau, trái ngược với ý trong câu hỏi là mọi khóa học đều theo một “standard format” (định dạng chuẩn/giống nhau).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. Đáp án: {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the advanced driving course may help <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">reduce your fuel consumption</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Reduce fuel consumption” (giảm tiêu thụ nhiên liệu) đồng nghĩa với việc “use less petrol” (dùng ít xăng hơn).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. Đáp án: {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Once you have purchased the course, the company will match you with a <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">local expert</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói họ sẽ kết nối bạn với chuyên gia địa phương, <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">không đề cập</strong> đến việc các khóa học này đang trở nên phổ biến hay có mặt ở nhiều nơi hơn (becoming available in more places).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Đáp án: {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the company will <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">match you with a local expert who will observe your driving habits</strong> over a series of lessons.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc một chuyên gia quan sát thói quen lái xe của riêng bạn và đưa ra phản hồi cá nhân hóa (personalised feedback) chứng tỏ đây là hình thức học 1 kèm 1 (one-to-one basis).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. Đáp án: {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “IAM Roadsmart offers a number of different advanced packages, including courses intended for users of <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">both cars and motorcycles</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nêu đối tượng là người đi ô tô và mô tô nói chung, <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">không nhắc đến</strong> việc họ có khóa học riêng cho “professional drivers” (tài xế chuyên nghiệp) hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Đáp án: {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The BAC also has a course intended to help improve confidence for <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">more general road use</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói BAC “chỉ” (only) cung cấp bài học cho những người có yêu cầu đặc biệt, nhưng thực tế bài đọc cho biết họ có cả các khóa học cho nhu cầu “chung” (general road use) như cải thiện sự tự tin.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
SET session_replication_role = DEFAULT;
